title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar. Add remaining ingredients. Roll into balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet and press flat with a fork. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: colorful kielbasa
directions: In a skillet, combine soup, water, and butter; bring to a boil.
Add Kielbasa and rice.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer about 18 minutes or until rice is almost tender. Stir in peas and mushrooms.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese. Cover and let stand until cheese is melted.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix as cake and roll in sufficient flour to make shaping possible.
Makes 1 double crust pie.

title: linguini and clams rockefeller
directions: Cook linguini according to package instructions.
Meanwhile, slice green onions finely, using the green tops as well, into the margarine, melted over low heat in skillet.
Mince garlic finely and add to margarine.
Stir constantly to avoid burning for a couple of minutes.

title: sour cream dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate 1 hour before serving. Great with raw vegetables.

title: sweet and sour ribs
directions: Combine all ingredients, but cornstarch, in a large casserole dish and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 hour covered. Let cool.
Skim off fat.
Add cornstarch to thicken.
Can be garnished with pineapple chunks.

title: stuffed flank steak
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In skillet over high heat, cook onion and orzo in 2 tablespoons oil for 5 minutes.
Stir in 2 1/2 cups water and soup mix.
Cover; simmer 10 minutes.
Remove from heat; add next 3 ingredients.
Spread orzo mixture on steak; roll and tie. Brush with remaining oil.
Roast 30 minutes or until thermometer reads 140°.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peach ice cream
directions: Mix milk and add whipping cream.
Add sugar and eggs; mix well.
Put peaches in blender or food processor.
Add to vanilla.
Mix well and fill freezer with mixture and as much whole milk as needed.
Freeze in electric freezer.

title: fresh peach pie filling
directions: Place peaches in a medium bowl; sprinkle with lemon juice, tossing gently. Set aside. Combine 1 cup sugar, 1/4 cup flour and 1/2 teaspoon ground cinnamon; sprinkle mixture over peaches. Toss gently and set aside. Line a 9-inch pie pan or pie plate with heavy-duty plastic wrap, allowing edges to overhang 6 to 8-inches. Spoon filling into pan and drizzle with butter; fold edges of plastic wrap over top and seal securely. Freeze until firm. Remove filling from pan and wrap in foil. Label and freeze for up to a year. Yield: Enough for 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: holiday smells
directions: Bring all to a boil.
Refrigerate.
Simmer whenever fragrance is desired.

title: spanish gazpacho(serves 4)
directions: Combine chopped tomatoes, zucchini and celery into a bowl and mix together.
Transfer 1/3 of this mixture to a blender.
Add some of the tomato juice and puree.
Pour the pureed vegetables back into the bowl and mix the remaining ingredients.
Chill. Serve garnished with lime slices.

title: apple-allspice muffins
directions: Cream 1/4 cup margarine in medium bowl; gradually add 1/2 cup brown sugar substitute.
Beat at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Add egg and mix well.

title: old fashioned egg custard pie
directions: Combine eggs and sugar; beating well.
Add salt, vanilla and 1/2 teaspoon nutmeg.
Gradually add scalded milk, stirring constantly.
Pour mixture into pie shell; sprinkle with additional nutmeg.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 325° and bake an additional 25 minutes, or until a knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Cool thoroughly before serving.

title: new potatoes in gravy(microwave)
directions: Arrange potatoes in an even layer in a microwave-safe dish. Stir together gravy, milk, poultry seasoning and pepper.
Pour evenly over potatoes.
Cover and cook on 100% power (High) for 8 or 9 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Stir gently and sprinkle with bacon before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cold pickle
directions: Mix well and place over pickles.

title: white cookies
directions: Mix butter, oil, sugars and eggs. Then add remaining ingredients. Chill. Roll into balls; place on ungreased cookie sheet and press with glass dipped in sugar. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. These cookies really melt in your mouth.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Beat all ingredients together.	Pour into pastry-lined pan. Bake at 425° for 45-55 minutes or until a silver knife inserted comes out clean.

title: oven stew
directions: Mix all ingredients well and put in roasting pan with a tight lid.
Bake at 225° to 250° for 5 hours.
Serve as is or in bread bowls.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Mix and bake until brown.

title: whole wheat brownies
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until fluffy.
Melt margarine and chocolate together, then add to eggs and sugar.
Next, add flour and mix well.
Bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes.
Let cool and frost.

title: kim's chicken dip
directions: Brown chicken (it dries).
Combine all ingredients and add chicken. Pour into 9 x 13 inch dish, sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven until cheese bubbles.

title: sesame  ginger  chicken
directions: Combine first four ingredients in a small bowl; stir well, place chicken into mix to marinate.
Grill or bake 15 to 20 minutes until done.

title: streusel coffee cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare Streusel.
Beat remaining ingredients in large mixer bowl on low for 30 seconds.
Beat on medium, scraping bowl occasionally, 2 minutes.
Spread half of the batter in an oblong pan, greased, 13 x 9 x 2-inch, or square. Sprinkle with half of the Streusel.
Top with remaining batter. Then sprinkle with remaining Streusel.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes

title: spinach casserole
directions: Place spinach in 1 1/2-quart greased casserole.
Combine onion, cheese and soup and mix well.
Spread over spinach. Sprinkle topping of stuffing, crackers or bread crumbs over mixture and dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lula bell special pie crust
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Spoon in water.
Roll out crust.
Cook pie crust alone.

title: sour cream delight
directions: Roll 1 package of crescent rolls onto a cookie sheet.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla well.
Spread on top of crescent rolls.
Cover with second pack of rolls.
Bake at 350° until rolls are done.
Mix a small amount of sugar and cinnamon together. Remove from oven and sprinkle with sugar mixture.

title: sweet and sour chicken wings
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a crock-pot.
Add chicken wings.
Cook at 350° for 3 hours or until chicken is done.
Can be done at a lower temperature.

title: one step pound cake
directions: Beat all ingredients for 3 minutes.
Bake at 325° for 60 minutes.

title: shrimp with sour cream
directions: Melt butter; add seasonings, garlic salt, crushed red pepper flakes and salt.
Saute 1 to 2 minutes.
Add shrimp; saute until pink.
Do not overcook.
Remove shrimp and add green pepper and onion to pan; saute until tender.
Add sour cream, mixing well; heat thoroughly.
Return shrimp, stirring to coat with sauce. Serve over rice.
Serves 2 to 4 people.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Cream the cream cheese, butter and vanilla until fluffy.
Add confectioners sugar and continue to beat until fluffy.

title: fay's cream cheese frosting
directions: Stir together all ingredients in a large bowl, blending well. Drop dough by teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased baking sheets. Bake at 325° for 18 to 20 minutes. Remove to wire racks to cool.

title: special k cookies
directions: Melt peanut butter, corn syrup and sugar.
Add Special K. Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool; cut in squares.

title: pasta salad
directions: Prepare pasta as directed.
Drain and cool.
To cool in a hurry, put ice cubes in pasta.
Once cooled, after a minute or so, drain again.
Slice and quarter the onion.
Dice the tomatoes or halve the grape tomatoes.
When pasta is ready, add remaining ingredients.
Mix together gently.
As a variation, cut up broccoli and add to salad.

title: no bake mini cheesecakes
directions: Mix crumb mixture as directed.
Press onto bottoms of 12 paper-lined muffin cups.
Prepare filling mix as directed on package.
Spoon over crumb mixture.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour. Garnish with fruit and walnut dipped in melted chocolate.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Mix hamburger, sauce, onions 3/4 of Rotel and olives.
Set aside.

title: watergate salad
directions: Drain pineapple and save the juice. Mix pineapple juice with dry pudding until smooth. Add pineapple, cherries, marshmallows and nuts. Fold in Cool Whip. Chill before serving.

title: apple butter cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together.
Grease and flour pans. Bake 50 minutes.
Sprinkle cake with confectioners sugar.
You can put nuts in if you want, about a cup.

title: chop suey casserole
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Cook until meat is brown.
Add onion and celery and continue cooking until celery is tender. Combine with bean sprouts, soup and half noodles and transfer to a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with remaining noodles.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until meat is tender.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream the eggs and sugar.
Slowly add oil; set aside.
Sift together the flour, baking soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add dry to creamed mixture.
Add zucchini.
Fold in raisins, walnuts and vanilla.
Pour into lightly greased and floured loaf pans. Bake 50-60 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: amish cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in ungreased pan.

title: gooey butter bars
directions: Melt butter and pour over cake mix; add eggs and mix well. Pour into greased 15-inch pan and spread evenly with spoon.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl and beat 2 minutes.
Grease and flour 2 large or small bread pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: banana chiffon cake
directions: Mix in bowl: flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Make a well in the mixture and add in order: oil, egg yolks, bananas, water and vanilla.
Mix well.

title: spinach balls(appetizer)
directions: Mix and roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Cover with wax paper.
Freeze until solid.
Transfer into plastic bag and freeze until ready to use.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Brown ground beef, salt and pepper; drain.
Add sauce, Ricotta cheese and egg.

title: chicken salad
directions: In medium bowl, combine chicken, grapes, celery and pecans. In small bowl, combine mayonnaise, sour cream, ginger and pepper. Blend well and stir into chicken.
Cover and refrigerate 1 to 2 hours before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: vegetable marinade
directions: Combine vegetables and marinade.
Chill and serve.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Mix in beaten eggs.
Mix together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with the milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix together the mashed bananas and soda; add to batter, stirring well.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350° in prepared loaf pan.
Remove from pan and cool completely.

title: 5 hour stew
directions: In a crock-pot or Dutch oven, place meat and veggies. Combine water and bouillon cube. Add to the pot along with remaining ingredients. Mix gently. Cook on low; Dutch oven, 5 hours or crock-pot, 8 hours.

title: wonderful dessert
directions: Mix flour, butter, salt and sugar as for pastry.
Add pecans. Put in bottom of pan (9 x 13-inch).
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: ham and potato casserole
directions: Cut the ham into pieces large enough for individual servings. Arrange ham, potatoes, onions, parsley and carrots in layers in a Dutch oven with some of the flour sprinkled on each layer.
Add the milk and water.
Cover tightly; simmer for 1 1/2 hours. Serves 6.
To serve 2 or 3, make 1/2 this recipe.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; refrigerate until firm enough to shape.
Roll in pecans.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Toss
sugar,
flour,
corn meal and lemon juice lightly with fork.
Add eggs, butter and milk and beat until thoroughly blended.
Pour
into unbaked pie shell.
Cook at 350° until set. It really takes from 45 minutes to an hour.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs for 5 minutes with mixer.
Add sugar, lemon and dry ingredients, mixing by hand.
Fold in pumpkin.
Place mixture in cookie sheet (10 1/2 x 16-inch) that is thoroughly greased and lined with wax paper.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until done.
When done, turn out onto dish towel that has been sprinkled thoroughly with powdered sugar and peel off waxed paper.
Sprinkle again with powdered sugar and roll in dish towel from short end, very carefully; refrigerate until cool.
When cool, unroll and spread with icing; re-roll and refrigerate.
Freezes well, too.

title: ginger-glazed chicken wings
directions: Pressure-cook chicken wings with 1/2 cup water, soy sauce, sugar, sake and ginger for 2 to 3 minutes.
Let steam 10 to 15 minutes thereafter.
Remove chicken from cooker.

title: no cook taco salad
directions: Tear lettuce to bite size pieces. Mix all together except Fritos and Catalina salad dressing.

title: pasta casserole
directions: Cook shells according to package directions.
Brown sausage. Add sauce.
Season to taste.
Combine with shells in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: miami beach birthday cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Prepare 2 (9-inch) layer pans (greased and floured).
Melt 1/3 cup chocolate chips.

title: jiffy cake(no muss!  no fuss!  made in the pan!)
directions: Sift dry ingredients into cake pan and flatten.
Make three holes in dry mixture.
Pour cooking oil in one hole, vinegar in another, and vanilla in the other.
Pour water over all and mix well with a fork, making sure that all dry ingredients are moistened.
Pay special attention to the corners.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
(Makes a very moist dark chocolate cake.)
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar (if desired), cut and serve.

title: italian wedding soup
directions: Boil chicken until thoroughly cooked.
Drain well and discard water.
Let cool and then shred.
Pour canned chicken broth into crock-pot, add shredded chicken.
Add seasonings, onion, carrots and chopped celery.
Stir well, then add frozen spinach.
Form ground round into tiny uncooked meatballs the size of your little fingernail and add to the mixture.
Cover and simmer for six hours, stirring occasionally.
Garnish with croutons and fresh grated Parmesan cheese.
This freezes well for a long time.

title: butter balls
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Add salt and extract, flour and nuts. Mix well.
Refrigerate until easy to handle.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 - 12 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Roll in powdered sugar while warm.

title: little smokies and sauce
directions: Brown Little Smokies in a skillet and drain on a paper towel. Place in a saucepan and add mustard and currant jelly.
Simmer for 45 minutes.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and spoon into crusts.
Makes 2 pies. Quick, easy and good!

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream together cream cheese, margarine and sugar.
Blend together pudding, milk and Cool Whip.

title: marshmallow icing
directions: Place sugar and water in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Pour sugar mixture into bowl with egg whites.
While still warm, add cream of tartar and vanilla.
Beat until icing is cool.
Frosts 2 (9-inch) layers.

title: sugared peanuts
directions: Cook all ingredients on medium heat until water cooks out and mixture looks grainy.
Place on cookie sheet in 325° oven.
Bake until lightly brown.
While mixture cooks on top of stove, stir constantly.
Cool and break nuts apart.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugar together.
Beat in egg, honey, vanilla and salt.
Add flour, oats and raisins.
Make 2-inch balls and flatten.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugars and Crisco.
Add other ingredients and mix well. Refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Roll in balls about the size of a nickle.
Place on cookie sheet about 1 inch apart.
Press 1/2 pecan on each cookie.
Cook in 325° oven until brown, about 12 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Cover sugar, water and cream of tartar.
Cook 5 minutes.
Take cover off and cook until golden.
Take off stove.
Add butter and soda and pour over corn.
Spread and dry.

title: pasta salad
directions: Sprinkle grated Parmesan cheese on top just before serving.

title: breakfast quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sprinkle sausage and cheese evenly over dough (dividing it up 1/2 to each pie shell), putting the sausage first and then cheeses on top of sausage.
Then beat remaining ingredients (eggs, milk, salt, pepper and oregano) together.
The egg mixture makes about 2 cups.
Pour 1 cup of this over the sausage and cheese in each pie shell and put in oven and bake for 35 minutes or until brown on top.

title: divinity
directions: Beat egg whites.
While beating, add vinegar and vanilla. Leave mixture stirring in electric blender.
Mix sugar, syrup and water.
Boil mixture until a drop of it in cold water pops lightly.
Turn blender to high and gradually pour in syrup mixture.
Beat until it begins to thicken.
Add nuts and mix by hand until mixture is thick enough to drop on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: "under the sea" salad
directions: Drain pears, reserving 1/2 cup syrup.
Dice pears and set aside.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add cold water and pear juice, vinegar and lemon juice.
Measure 1 1/4 cups into an 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Chill until set, but not firm (will be sticky to the touch).
Meanwhile, soften cheese.
Beat in remaining Jell-O. Blend in ginger.
Fold in pears.
Spoon over set Jell-O in pan. Chill overnight or until firm.
Unmold on crisp lettuce.
Makes 6 servings.

title: better than pumpkin pie
directions: Spray a 9x13 pan or glass baking dish with cooking spray. Set aside. Mix 1st eight ingredients in a large mixing bowl. Mix until well blended. Pour into baking dishTop mixture with the dry cake mix then with the chopped nuts. Top this by pouring the melted butter over the top of the mix. Bake in a preheated 350 degrees oven for 45-60 minutes until done. Serve warm
or cold.

title: braised pork chops
directions: Coat pork chops with mixture of flour, salt, mustard and garlic salt.
Brown on both sides in hot oil in large skillet. Put pork chops in crock-pot.
Add chicken soup.
Cover and cook on low for 6 to 8 hours or high for 3 to 4 hours.

title: cinnamon tea biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift together flour, baking soda and cream of tartar and set aside.
Using electric mixer on high speed in large mixing bowl, cream 1/4 cup sugar, the margarine and butter.
Add egg and vanilla and beat until light and fluffy, about 1 minute.

title: virginia's chicken
directions: Mix dressing, soup mix and preserves.
Marinate breasts in it overnight.
Cook covered in a 350° oven for 2 hours.
Turn chicken once.

title: refrigerator cucumber pickles
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients and pour over 1 gallon of sliced cukes (not peeled).
Shake for 5 days.
Keep in refrigerator all the time.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix well and refrigerate overnight.
This will keep for a week.
Serve with plain crackers, toast or veggies.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for about 60 minutes.

title: wild mushroom-sweet potato soup
directions: In a soup pot melt the butter; add the onions and cook until translucent.
Add the flour, stirring to form a paste.
Cook over low heat, stirring often for 5 minutes.
Add the chicken stock, stirring until smooth (no lumps).
Add the mushrooms that have been roughly chopped by hand or in a food processor.
Add the sweet potatoes that have been peeled and roughly chopped by hand or in a food processor.
Simmer the soup over medium heat, stirring often, for approximately 30 minutes.
Add the chopped parsley, brown sugar and heavy cream.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Serves 8.

title: shrimp and mushroom casserole
directions: Prepare wild rice according to directions.
Dice onion and green pepper.
Saute in butter.
Slice mushrooms and add; saute for 3 more minutes.
Add cooked rice, mushroom soup and Cheez Whiz. Stir well.
Add shrimp, white wine and fresh lemon juice.
Season with pepper.
Place in casserole.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken - dressing casserole
directions: Stew chicken, remove from bone, reserve 1 1/2 cup broth. Place chicken in a 9 x 13 oven proof dish.
Mix soups, butter, and sour cream together and pour over chicken.
Cover with stuffing mix, pour broth over all.
Bake 350° covered 40 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: daniel's favorite mussels
directions: Clean mussels.
Heat tomatoes to boiling; add wine and return to boil.
Add mussels; boil covered on medium-high heat, stirring occasionally, for 5 to 10 minutes, until mussels open.
Serve with broth in large bowls with bread to sop broth.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add molasses and egg.
Beat well. Add dry ingredients.
Form into balls (approximately 1/2 teaspoon and roll in hands) and dip in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: vegetable rice casserole
directions: Place onion and margarine in skillet.
Cook over medium heat until onion is soft.
Add remaining ingredients, except rice. Bring to a boil.
Place ribs in a greased casserole dish.
Pour liquid mixture over rice.
Stir well.
Cover and bake in preheated oven at 370° for 30 minutes.

title: pasta vegetable soup
directions: In large saucepan, over medium-high heat, heat chicken broth, red pepper, garlic, carrots, celery, onion, basil and black pepper to a boil.
Stir in macaroni; simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in corn; cook 5 minutes more.
Makes 8 servings.

title: special baked beans
directions: Cook ground chuck or fry bacon; drain except for 1 tablespoon. Cook onion and bell pepper until transparent.
Add beans, garlic powder, brown sugar, Worcestershire and mustard.
Mix well.
Pour into ovenproof bowl and bake at 375° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: cauliflower and cheese bake
directions: In a small skillet, melt the oleo over low heat.
Add the cracker crumbs and cook, stirring constantly, until the crumbs are lightly browned.
Remove the skillet from the heat and set aside. Spray a 1-quart casserole with Pam.
Arrange the cauliflower in the casserole, top with cheese and sprinkle with the crumb mixture. cover.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 20 minutes, until the cheese is melted.

title: oyster cracker snack mix
directions: Mix in shallow pan.
Drain on paper towels (this absorbs oil). No cooking needed.

title: sin
directions: Mix flour, sugar and oleo.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Mix cream cheese with powdered sugar; put on crust.
Mix pudding according to directions.
Spread on top of cream cheese mixture.
Top with Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: saltine candy
directions: Place saltines, salt side up, on cookie sheet. Boil butter and sugar for 3 minutes. Spread over saltines. Bake 5 minutes in 400° oven. Put chocolate chips on top for 5 minutes. Spread like frosting. Cool in refrigerator for 2 to 3 hours. Break it up. You may put fine nuts on top. You may freeze it also. Enjoy, you can't just eat one.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients in a baking dish. Cook 45 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: pickles
directions: Mix well; add well drained pickles.
Stir often for 2 hours. Place in a jar and put in refrigerator.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Combine until crumbly, pat in bottom of 8 x 12-inch or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 15 or 20 minutes until brown.

title: hoppin' john
directions: Soak peas in water to cover for 6 to 8 hours or overnight. Place bacon in a large pot and fry over low flame until almost done.
Add onion and cook until light brown. Add garlic seasoning and bring to a boil. Wash and drain peas.
Add to boiling mixture. Simmer gently over low flame for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Add rice and cook for 30 to 40 minutes more until peas and rice are tender and liquid has thickened.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: seafood spread
directions: Beat cream cheese 1 to 2 minutes with electric mixer until creamy.
Blend in remaining ingredients, except walnuts and paprika.
Spread mixture in 9-inch pie plate.
Top with walnuts and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake uncovered at 375° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes approximately 3 cups.

title: ground round casserole
directions: Lightly brown onion, pepper and meat.
Place in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Layer with green beans, closely layer Tater Tots.
Blend soup and milk.
Pour over Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into unbaked pie crust.
Cook at 325° until firm.

title: cracker snackers
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a bowl; add crackers, tossing well.
Drizzle oil over cracker mixture; stir well.
Place mixture in a large paper bag; fold bag to close and let stand 2 hours, shaking bag occasionally.
Store mixture in an airtight container.
Makes 11 cups.

title: speedy caramel frosting
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; blend in brown sugar and salt.
Cook over low heat for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add milk and continue stirring until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Blend in 4x sugar gradually.
Add vanilla and mix well. Frost 2 layers.

title: cherry cheese brownie bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare brownie mix according to directions.
Bake 20 minutes.
While baking, beat vanilla, egg, cream cheese and milk until smooth.
Pour over brownies and bake until set 25 minutes.
Cool 2 hours and spread pie filling over all.
Store in refrigerator.

title: pistachio pudding salad
directions: Mix together; then chill in refrigerator until firm enough to serve (several hours).

title: biscuit mix
directions: Sift dry ingredients. Cut in lard with knives or pastry blender until all are even and are size of small peas. Place in sack and roll up tight. Keep in refrigerator. Will keep at least one month and will yield 5 batches of 2 cups each.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Peel and slice fresh ripe peaches.
Place in oblong baking dish.
Blend all ingredients well.
Spread on top of peaches. Bake 40 minutes in a 350° oven.
Can be served with ice cream.

title: banana cake
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and vanilla, beat until fluffy.

Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with sour milk and mashed banana, beating well after each addition. Bake in greased 6 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch pan at 350° for 50 minutes. Frost with caramel frosting or eat plain.

title: secret cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar; set aside.
Melt and cook together margarine, water and cocoa.
Let come to a boil; pour over sugar and flour.
Mix well.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda, salt and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.
Do not overcook.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Beat Dream Whip and 1 cup milk until stiff. Mix the remaining 1 3/4 cups milk, Jell-O and coconut. Fold Dream Whip into coconut mixture. Pour into cooled pie shells. Top with more Dream Whip and garnish with toasted coconut. Chill 3 hours.

title: meatza pie
directions: Mix together the ground beef (uncooked), milk, crumbs and garlic salt.
Press into pie tin to make crust.
Layer ketchup, mushrooms and oregano over crust.
Sprinkle with cheeses.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cream the cream cheese.
Blend in the remaining ingredients well. Shape into large ball and roll in finely chopped nuts (pecans or walnuts). This will make 3 or 4 small balls or 1 large.

title: chicken-rice supper
directions: Heat margarine in a 2-quart saucepan until melted.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk and broth.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole or rectangular baking dish, 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch.
Bake uncovered in 350° oven until bubbly, 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.
Has 315 calories per serving.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Place tomatoes in greased baking dish. Add sugar, salt and pepper. Melt butter and into bread crumbs. Sprinkle crumbs on top of tomatoes and add cheese. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chicken tortilla soup
directions: To boil chicken, boil for 20 minutes, then cut up.
Mix all ingredients, except tortillas chips and cheese, for 30 minutes. Top with tortilla chips and cheese.

title: turkish crepes
directions: In a bowl combine eggs, milk, flour, salt and sugar.
Blend thoroughly.
Bake on a medium hot grill, spreading batter as thin as possible, until golden brown.
Roll up, sprinkle with powdered sugar and serve with honey or cheese.

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Peel and slice apples thin. Mix all ingredients together. Put in pie crust. Dab margarine on top of apples. Put top crust on. Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: orange balls
directions: Combine vanilla wafers, butter, 3/4 cup powdered sugar and pecans, if desired.
Add orange juice last.
Blend well.
Chill about 2 hours.
Roll into balls the size of a quarter.
Roll in the last 1/4 cup of powdered sugar.
Refrigerate 24 hours before serving.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine syrup, sugar and water in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and boil to 230° or until syrup spins thread, 15 to 20 minutes. Add peanuts and continue to cook to 300° (15 to 20 minutes). Remove from heat and add butter, vanilla, soda and salt.
Stir until blended.
Turn into a well-greased jelly roll pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch).
When cool, break into pieces.
Makes 1 1/2 pounds.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Take juice, mix flour and sugar; pour over pineapple and cheese.
Mix crackers with melted butter; sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350°.
Put cherries on top.

title: turkey sandwiches
directions: Combine butter and garlic.
Slice rolls in half.
Spread both halves with butter mixture.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake for 5 minutes at 450°.
Combine turkey, tomato, oregano and salt.
Heat oil in skillet.
Add mixture; cook until heated through.
Stir in half of cheese.
Spoon onto heated rolls.
Top with 3 slices of pepperoni.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Broil until cheese is bubbly and lightly brown.
Serve hot.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onion slices and garlic in butter in a Dutch oven over medium heat 10 to 15 minutes or until very tender. Add flour, stirring until smooth. Gradually add beef broth and water. Bring to a boil. Cover. Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes. Stir in pepper. Remove from heat. Place 6 ovenproof serving bowls on a baking sheet. Place 1 toasted French bread slice in each bowl. Ladle soup into bowls. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Broil 6-inches from heat for 1 minute or until cheese has melted.

title: skillet summer squash
directions: Heat oil in skillet over medium heat.
Add onions; saut until tender but not brown.
Add remaining ingredients.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 15 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Crush onion rings and set aside.
Mix all ingredients, except 1/2 cup of crushed onion rings.
Roll into a ball.
Coat with reserved 1/2 cup of crushed onion rings.

title: brown rice casserole
directions: Saute margarine and onion.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and bake at 400° approximately 1 hour or until done.
Stir before serving.

title: poppy seed muffins
directions: Mix flour, poppy seed, baking soda and salt together.
Set aside.
Beat sugar and butter until fluffy.
Beat in eggs, vanilla and lemon peel.
Add flour mixture and 1 cup yogurt.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Makes 18 muffins.

title: chicken and barley casserole
directions: Saute onion, garlic and celery in butter or oil on medium heat for 5 minutes.
Add wine; bring to a boil and stir until wine evaporates.
Add tomatoes, broth and barley; bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and cook 25 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add salt and pepper.

title: our favorite punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, sugar, pineapple juice and water together. Refrigerate for 3 hours.
Put 1/2 Kool-Aid mixture in punch bowl. Add ginger ale and pineapple sherbet.
Serves 60 people.

title: strawberry yum yum
directions: Put graham crackers in a large, oblong dish.
Dissolve jello into 1 cup hot water.
Add strawberries and refrigerate until jelled.
Follow directions on Dream Whip.
Cream the cream cheese and sugar and add to Dream Whip.
Spoon strawberry jello mixture onto crust and top with cream cheese and Dream Whip mixture. Refrigerate.

title: potato sour cream casserole
directions: Boil the potatoes in skin. Refrigerate overnight.
Peel and grate on large side of grater.
Add the sour cream, 1 1/2 cups grated Cheddar cheese, butter or margarine, onions, salt and pepper to taste.
Top with grated cheese.
Combine and bake in a large Pyrex at 350° for 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: elegant pound cake
directions: Beat egg whites until soft peaks form, gradually adding 6 tablespoons of the sugar, then beating until stiff.
Put in refrigerator.
In your largest mixer bowl, cream the butter, adding the remaining sugar.
Beat egg yolks well; add.
Sift flour 3 times; measure.
Add flour and cream alternately to your sugar mixture, beating until very light (at least 8 to 10 minutes in mixer).
Add vanilla.
Fold egg whites in by hand, using an over-and-under method.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix egg, milk, sugar and oil.
Add flour and baking powder. Blend in blueberries.
Bake in muffin pan at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: jewish coffee cake
directions: Add to creamed mixture.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all together in saucepan and cook until thickened.
Add half of the butter and stir until this melts.
Melt other half stick in pan and pour in mixture.
Cook slowly at 350° until done, 1 hour.
Brown on top.

title: diet peanut butter cookies
directions: Bake at 400° until done.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown beef, onions and pepper. Add both cans of soup and 1 can of water. Salt and pepper to taste. Let simmer 10 minutes. Cook noodles according to package directions. In a casserole dish, place a layer of noodles and a layer of beef mixture. Sprinkle cheese. Repeat for a second layer. End with cheese. Bake at 350° for 10 or 15 minutes.

title: fried cakes
directions: Roll into a soft dough, cut and deep fry.

title: bourbon hot dogs
directions: Mix all
ingredients.
Cover and simmer on low heat for 1 hour.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Put 1 package crescent rolls in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Brown hamburger and onion. Add pizza sauce and vegetable (optional).
Put hamburger mixture on pizza crust.
Add Mozzarella cheese on top of hamburger.
Put pepperoni on top of cheese. Top with 1 can crescent rolls.
Can add Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: hawaii spinach loaf
directions: Saute onion, celery, green pepper and rosemary in margarine. Cook spinach as directed on box.
Drain and squeeze all water out. Put Velveeta cheese in with sauteed onion, celery and green pepper.
Add spinach.
Mix.

title: quick quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Blend in filling.
Place in 9-inch or 10-inch quiche dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until golden brown.
When knife in center comes out clean, quiche is done.

title: rice salad
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar, mayonnaise and Cool Whip.
Fold in rice, cherries, marshmallows, crushed pineapple and pecans.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: pork chops and onions
directions: Brown the pork chops in a nonstick pan.
Top with onions.
Mix rest of the ingredients together and pour sauce over the chops. Heat to boiling, then reduce temperature to low and simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: catfish stew
directions: Cover catfish with water; add bacon and cook until done. Remove fish from liquid.
Cool.
To the liquid, add corn, tomato juice and onion.
Remove bones from fish.
Add flaked fish to liquids.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly, on low heat. Season to taste.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Mix the hash browns, soup, sour cream and Cheez Whiz in the pan.
Put in a preheated oven at 350° for 10 minutes.
Take from the oven and mix well.
Spread out evenly.
Sprinkle corn flakes on top.
Cut up the butter and lay on top.
Bake for about 50 minutes.

title: shoney's strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, water and cornstarch.
Boil until thickened. Remove from heat.
Stir in jello until smooth. Cool until room temperature.
Fill pie shell with strawberries.
Pour mixture over berries. Chill until firm.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: mock whipped cream icing
directions: Beat butter or margarine and sugar for 6 minutes. Boil milk, water and cornstarch until it makes a thick paste (cool).
Pour over butter mixture and beat at least 6 minutes.
Add vanilla. This is good on any cake.

title: creme brulee french toast
directions: In a small saucepan, melt butter and add corn syrup and brown sugar.
Simmer until bubbly.
Pour syrup into a bottom of 9 x 13 x 2 inch baking dish and spread evenly.
Thickly slice bread and arrange pieces over the syrup.
In a large bowl, beat together eggs, half and half, vanilla, salt and liqueur.
Pour evenly over bread, cover and refrigerate overnight.
In the morning, remove French toast from refrigerator and preheat oven to 350°.
Bake uncovered for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve hot with maple syrup.

title: cupcakes
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cream shortening; add sugar gradually and cream until light.
Add egg and beat well.
Add flour alternately with milk, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Pour batter into greased cupcake pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Frost and decorate.
Makes 12.

title: edward asner's ambrosia salad(makes 10 servings)
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl and refrigerate overnight.
Serve the next day.

title: "gotta try it" chicken
directions: You will need 4 aluminum foil squares.

title: pineapple bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix butter, sugar, cream and eggs.
Stir in pineapple and bread.
Cook 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: plum cake
directions: Put all ingredients in mixing bowl and beat 3 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: turkey-dressing casserole(low-cal)
directions: Place turkey on bottom of 10 x 8 dish.
Mix soups and milk and pour over turkey.
Place stuffing in bowl and mix with broth. Let stand until moist.
Crumble on top of soups.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: orange-mustard glazed turkey
directions: Cut turkey into four 1/2-inch slices.
Make glaze by combining remaining ingredients in small bowl.
Heat turkey over hot coals in covered grill, 8 to 10 minutes, turning once and brushing occasionally with glaze.
Serves 4.

title: caramel apple phyllo tart
directions: Melt margarine in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.
Add apples and saute 15 minutes or until tender.
Add raisins, sugar and cinnamon; stir well.
Remove from heat and let cool.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook beef and drain well.
Cook pasta; drain and rinse with cold water and drain well.
Mix together ground beef, pasta, 1 cup cheese sauce, salt and pepper.
Grease large glass 13 x 9-inch dish.
Put mixture in dish.
Add 1 cup cheese on top and lay pepperoni around the top to cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: candied peanuts
directions: Mix sugar, water and coloring in saucepan until sugar is melted.
Put peanuts and in and cook until the peanuts candy, stirring constantly.
When sugar candies on peanuts, pour out on baking pan and place in 300° oven for 30 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix
sugar,
oil
and
eggs together. Add flour, baking powder,
soda,
salt
and cinnamon.
Mix well, then add 1 teaspoon vanilla, nuts and chopped apples.	Spread all in a flat pan and sprinkle butterscotch bits on top.	Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: six-shooter corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter; add sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well.
Add green chilies.
Add corn and mix well. Add cheeses and salt.
Sift flour, re-measure and sift with corn meal and baking powder.
Add to previous mixture.
Pour into greased and floured glass baking dish (8 x 12-inch).
Reduce oven to 300° and bake 1 hour.
Serves 10.

title: walking taco
directions: In large skillet, saute ground beef and onion.
Drain off fat.
Add taco seasoning and chili salsa, and set aside.
Cream together refried beans and bean dip.
Spread mixture in a 9 x 13 casserole, top with meat mixture and cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes or until cheese has melted.
Remove from oven and top casserole with lettuce, tomato, green onions, ripe olives, chiles, avocado and sour cream.
Serve with tortilla chips.
This will feed 8 to 10 people, or can be made as a main dish for 4 to 6.

title: bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix bran with milk; let stand 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Bake approximately 20 minutes.

title: honey popcorn balls
directions: Combine honey and water.
Cook over high heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Reduce heat to medium.
Cook to soft ball stage, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla; cool slightly.
Pour over popcorn; shape into balls.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In medium saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in brown sugar and milk.
Bring to a boil; boil and stir 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix in confectioners sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Spread into buttered 9-inch pan. Cool.
Makes 3 1/2 pounds.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake pie for 30 to 35 minutes longer.
(Filling should appear slightly less set in center than around edge.)
Recipe of Doris Bowlin.

title: rotel chicken lasagna
directions: Mix chicken with onion and green pepper.
Mix olives, cheese and seasonings.
Mix Ro-Tel and soups.

title: luscious slush
directions: Mix all ingredients in a blender.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch freezer pan.
Freeze 30 minutes, until slushy.
Spoon into glass and serve.

title: holiday punch
directions: Dissolve drink mix in water in pitcher or bowl.
Add juices and chill.
Just before serving, stir in club soda.
Makes about 10 cups or 20 servings.

title: corn flake bars
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in saucepan.
When it starts to bubble, remove from heat and mix with peanut butter.
Add the vanilla. Place corn flake bars in pan and press down.
Pour mixture over corn flakes and mix well.
Then press down in pan and cool; cut in squares.

title: kahlua
directions: Boil water, sugar and vanilla bean 5 minutes; remove from heat.
Add instant coffee.
Stir.
Add brandy and vodka.
Let cool.
Pour into containers; seal.

title: parmesan onion bake
directions: In a large skillet, saute onions and celery in 3 Tbsp. butter until tender; drain and set aside.
In a saucepan, melt the remaining butter; stir in flour, salt and pepper until smooth. Gradually stir in milk.
Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes until thickened.
Pour over vegetables and toss to coat. Pour into an ungreased 2 quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and pecans.
Bake, uncovered at 350 degrees for 20 - 25 minutes or until heated through.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix together Raisin Bran, flour, salt, sugar and soda.
Add eggs, oil and buttermilk; mix well.
Pour into greased/floured muffin tins and bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Store unused batter in tight container until ready to use.
Will keep in refrigerator 6 weeks.

title: chocolate cake delight
directions: Melt cocoa in boiling water.
Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Add alternately with milk.
Add cocoa.
Beat 2 minutes.
Makes 2 (8-inch) layers or one 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Cream oleo and cream cheese; add sugar and cream well. Alternate flour and eggs, beating good.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 300° starting in cold oven.
Bake in tube pan, greased and floured, for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat and onion; add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 2 hours.
Serve on buns.

title: christmas salad
directions: Cook real slow sugar, eggs, lemon and pineapple juice until very thick.
Cool and pour over other ingredients.

title: cheese-pepperoni roll-ups
directions: Roll out whole sheet of crescent rolls or puff pastry until perforations are gone, as thin as possible.
Lay room temperature cheese on top and dot with thin slices of pepperoni or summer sausage.
Roll up, jelly roll style, carefully, sealing edges. Brush entire surface with egg white.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Only after cooled, slice in 1-inch pieces.

title: rolled chicken breast
directions: Mix the sour cream and lemon juice with seasonings.
Dip chicken in sauce and roll in stuffing.
Put in baking dish.
Pour 1/2 cup melted butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Roll crackers to make crumbs.
Combine crumbs and softened margarine.
Pat crust into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Reserve 1 tablespoon of crumbs for top.
Combine pudding and milk. Gradually add ice cream and blend until mixture is smooth.
Spread mixture over crust.
Spread Cool Whip on top and sprinkle remaining crumbs over Cool Whip.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Combine and pat into a 9 x 13-inch dish, the crushed pretzels, oleo and 3 teaspoons sugar.
Bake 8 minutes at 375°.
Cool.
Beat 1 cup sugar in the cream cheese.
Stir in the Cool Whip.
Spread mixture over cooled pretzels.

title: beef rolls
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Put small amount on slice of beef and roll jelly roll style.
Chill until firm.
Slice in bite-size pieces.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain. Add taco seasoning mix and follow directions on package. Set aside. Combine all ingredients just prior to serving. Makes a lot. Could prepare half and freeze half the meat for another meal.

title: mary anne's cocktail wieners
directions: Marinate all together.
Serve on toothpicks with crackers.

title: infallible rice
directions: Saute onion in butter until transparent.
Combine onion, rice and hot broth.
Bring to a boil on top of range.
Cover and place in 325° oven for 20 or 25 minutes until done.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: lemon zucchini bread(diabetic)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
With electric mixer, combine applesauce, apple juice concentrate, fructose, oil, eggs and lemon juice.
Beat until well blended.
In a separate bowl, combine lemon peel, flour, baking powder, salt, baking soda, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Add zucchini and nuts to dry mixture.
Add batter to dry mixture and blend well.
Pour into 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan which has been coated with vegetable cooking spray.
Bake for one hour or until inserted knife comes out clean.
Yields 16 slices.
Each slice contains 171 calories (41% from fat).

title: chunky potato soup
directions: In large saucepan, melt butter; add onions, bay leaf and thyme. Cook until onions are translucent.
Add potatoes, broth and pepper. Boil until potatoes are tender.
Remove bay leaf.
With slotted spoon, remove about 2 cups of the potatoes and onions to a bowl. Puree remaining soup in a blender and return to saucepan.
Stir in milk and the reserved potatoes and onions.
Season with salt and heat just to boiling.
Garnish with green onions, if desired.

title: cold poached salmon
directions: Heat water, wine, salt, thyme, tarragon, peppercorns, parsley, onion, celery and bay leaf to boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Place salmon steaks in skillet.
Add water if necessary to cover.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, until fish flakes easily with fork, 12 to 15 minutes. Carefully remove fish. Drain on wire rack.
Cover and refrigerate until cold.

title: mexican layer dip
directions: Layer in order:
beans, avocado dip, sour cream (mixed with taco seasoning), chopped tomatoes, cheese, black olives and jalapeno peppers.
Keep chips in a bowl next to dip.
Serve cold.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: Mix together onion, celery and butter.
Simmer until soft, not brown.
Add flour and milk and bring to a boil.
Turn down heat and add cheese and beer.
Stir until thick and bubbly. Add potatoes, chicken broth and dry mustard.
Cook until potatoes are soft, about 1 hour.

title: crisp wun tun
directions: Use 1 package Wun
Tun	Pi
(allowing 1 teaspoon of the mixture
from
the	6
ingredients	shown
for
each
square). Moisten 2 corners; fold in half to form triangle.
Fry in deep fat until brown.

title: garlic herb bread
directions: Combine cooled oatmeal mixture to the creamed mixture. Add dry ingredients and mix well. Pour into greased loaf pan. Bake for 50-60 minutes. Muffins, bake 20-25 minutes.

title: black devil's food cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Separately blend the flour, salt, soda and baking powder together.
Add 1 cup of hot water to cocoa.
Mix together the flour mixture and egg mixture, alternating adding hot water and cocoa.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix cake mix, water, oil and eggs well.
Stir oranges in batter and bake in 3 layers at 350°.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, butter and milk.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add oatmeal, vanilla and peanut butter.
Drop on waxed paper and let cool 1 hour.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions.
Chill.
Cut layers in half to make 4 thin layers.
Spread mixture of sour cream, sugar and coconut (chilled) between layers, reserving 1 cup.
Mix the cup with Cool Whip and ice top and sides of cake.
Extra coconut may be sprinkled on top.
Store in refrigerator in airtight container. May be frozen until needed.

title: creamed spinach over noodles(david's favorite)
directions: Cook spinach (do not add water) 3 to 5 minutes.
Drain spinach well.
Squeeze in a towel, if necessary.
Chop spinach and set aside.
Cook bacon until crisp; crumble and set aside.
Reserve half of the bacon drippings.
Add flour to drippings.
Cook over medium heat for 1 minute, until smooth (stir constantly). Gradually add milk; cook, stirring constantly, until thick and bubbly.
Stir in chopped spinach, onion, salt and pepper; set aside.
Arrange noodles on a serving platter; top with spinach mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese and crumbled bacon.
Serve immediately.

title: light crisp waffles
directions: Heat oven to 200°.
Mix flour, cornstarch, salt, baking powder and baking soda in a medium bowl.
Measure buttermilk, milk and vegetable oil in a 2-cup measuring cup; mix in yolk and set aside.

title: grand marnier french toast
directions: Cut Italian bread on a slant into 12 slices about 1 1/2-inches thick.
Arrange in single layer in three 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dishes.
Beat eggs with milk.
Add Grand Marnier, orange peel, sugar, vanilla extract and salt.
Mix well or blend on medium speed.
Pour mixture over bread, turning slices to coat both sides.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: creamside milk punch
directions: In a large punch bowl, place ice cream and sherbet.
Pour in milk and lemon-lime soda.
Stir gently.
Serve immediately.
Makes approximately 24 servings.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix oleo and sugar together.
Add flour and vanilla and mix well. Fold in crushed potato chips.
Roll into small balls. Place on a cookie sheet that has been sprayed with Pam.
Use a fork that has been dipped in flour to press down on the cookie or use fingers to press in thinner and more rounded shapes.
Bake in 300° oven for about 15 to 20 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar when cool.

title: gobs
directions: Mix all together and drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.

title: crumb-coated potato halves
directions: In a shallow bowl combine the bread crumbs, paprika, salt and pepper.
Brush potatoes with butter, roll in crumb mixture until coated.
Place in a greased 9x13-inch pan or baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour or until tender.

title: diabetic pound cake
directions: Measure Bisquick and pour in large bowl.
Cut in margarine until size of small peas.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding and sugar in bowl and stir with a wire whisk to remove large lumps.
Add oil, water, eggs and sour cream, stirring until smooth.
Stir in chocolate morsels.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 12-cup Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from pan.
Cool completely.
Sprinkle with sifted powdered sugar.

title: date-nut cake roll
directions: Grease and flour bottom and sides of a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jellyroll pan; set aside.
Combine dates, water and 1/4 cup sugar in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until thickened (about 10 minutes); cool.
Beat eggs in a large bowl at high speed of an electric mixer for 5 minutes.
Gradually add 1/2 cup sugar, beating until smooth.
Add date mixture.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar together.
Add eggs, vanilla, oleo and milk. Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients, except chocolate chips. Mix together.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top of batter.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
When cooled, sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Heat soup.
Add softened or dissolved gelatin.
Beat cream cheese and mayonnaise until smooth.
Add to soup.
Add shrimp and seasonings.
Spray mold with Pam and place all ingredients in the mold.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Combine pineapple (reserve natural juice) and miniature marshmallows.
Chill.
In saucepan, combine sugar, pineapple juice, flour, vinegar and eggs.
Cook until it thickens.
Cool and add 8 ounces Cool Whip.
Blend together and refrigerate overnight. Before serving, add 1 1/2 cups Spanish peanuts and 2 cups chopped apples.

title: shrimp toast
directions: Thaw shrimp; chop very fine.
Mix with water chestnuts.
Add salt, sugar, cornstarch and egg; mix.

title: divinity candy
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and water in pan and cook until mixture forms a hard ball in cold water.
Then beat egg whites and add jello. Mix well and beat until mixture holds a peak.
Pour syrup over mixture slowly and beat.
Add coconut and nuts.
Pour into a large greased pan.
Cut in squares when cool.

title: baked beans
directions: Place all ingredients, except bacon, in a large bowl.
Lightly grease a 2-quart baking dish.
Cover bottom of dish with bacon strips.
Pour 1/2 bean mixture in dish.
Cover with layer of bacon strips.
Add remaining beans; top with any bacon left over.
Bake in a preheated oven at 425° for about 40 minutes, or until bacon is done.

title: fried peach pie
directions: Cover peaches with water in saucepan on medium heat. Cook for 1 1/2 hours or until tender. Add sugar. Drop 1 serving spoon of filling on each rolled out biscuit. Crimp with fork. Place skillet on low heat; pour oil in skillet. Cook pie until brown on both sides. Makes 12 servings.

title: play clay
directions: In saucepan, stir together baking soda and cornstarch; add water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture is consistency of moist mashed potatoes.
Turn out on a plate and cover with damp cloth until cool enough to handle.
Roll to 1/4 inch thickness.
Cut shapes with cookie cutters.
If making ornaments, press hole near top of each ornament with toothpick. Allow to dry on flat surface and harden overnight.
Paint, decorate and protect with a shiny glaze.

title: hush puppies
directions: Place all ingredients in a bowl, then add enough milk to make this mixture of a thick consistency, because you don't want this to be thin.
Drop by teaspoon into hot oil and cook until brown in color.

title: mushroom chicken
directions: Boil chicken breast.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add cream of mushroom soup and butter.
Serve over white rice.

title: basic dump cake
directions: Have bed of coals.
Line a 12-inch Dutch oven with foil. Place on coals.
Spread the pie filling in bottom of Dutch oven. Sprinkle cake mix over pie filling.
Slice margarine over cake mix.
Leave alone for 20 minutes.
If still bubbly, cover for 5 more minutes.
Done after 25 minutes.

title: cinnamon-apple breakfast quesadilla
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place one tortilla on ungreased baking sheet.
Spread half applesauce over tortilla; reserve half for garnish.
Sprinkle half of cinnamon-sugar over applesauce.
Top with cheese and second tortilla.
Sprinkle remaining cinnamon-sugar on top.
Bake at 400° for 6 to 8 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool 2 minutes.
Cut into quarters and serve with reserved applesauce and vanilla yogurt.

title: creamy garden wedges
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Stir bisquick, boiling water and onions in medium bowl until soft dough forms; beat vigorously 20 strokes. Press dough onto ungreased 12 inch pizza pan; pinch edges to form 1/2 inch rim.
Bake 10 minutes; cool 10 minutes.
Stir together cream cheese, sour cream, dill, and garlic powder until well blended.
Spread evenly over crust.
Chill 1 hour.
Just before serving top with vegetables and cheese.
Cut into wedges.
Makes about 18 appetizers.

title: ham soup
directions: Bring just to a boil.
Simmer, uncovered for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Mix butter, sugar and vanilla thoroughly.
Measure flour and mix with salt.
Blend all ingredients together.
Mix in nuts; chill dough.

title: anise toast
directions: Sift together flour, salt and baking powder three times.
Beat oleo and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each egg.
Add anise extract, seed and flour.
Beat at slow speed until well mixed.
Add almond slivers.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread dough on a well-greased and floured cookie sheet. Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from oven and cut into 1-inch squares.
Rebake 10 to 15 minutes.
Squares will be crisp.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine the soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper.
Stir in beans and half can Durkee French fried onions.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until hot and bubbling; stir.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake 5 minutes or until onions are golden brown.
Serves 6.
Preparation time: 10 minutes; cooking time: 30 minutes.

title: baked grits souffle
directions: Cook grits according to traditional recipe.
Mix with soup. Add well beaten eggs.
Place mixture in baking dish, greased with bacon drippings.
Cover with cracker crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: swedish nuts
directions: Brown nuts in oven. Beat egg whites until stiff. Add sugar, a little at
a time, and continue beating. Add salt.
Spread over melted butter.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°, turning every 10 minutes.

title: hot turkey salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together except crumbs and put in large baking dish.
Sprinkle crumbs over top.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°. Serves 8 to 10 generously.

title: crunchy vegetable spread
directions: Drain vegetables well.
Beat cream cheese and lemon until smooth.
Stir in vegetables and pepper.
Yields 2 cups.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Add eggs and pumpkin.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, soda and spices.
Add alternately with water to sugar, etc., mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: cream vegetables
directions: Cook veggies according to pkg direction.

title: congealed salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Cool slightly.
Add condensed milk.
Mix well.
Add pineapple, cherries and cottage cheese or sour cream.
Add nuts.

title: pecan turtles
directions: Heat caramels (after removing cellophane wrapping) on low heat.
Add hot water, little by little.
(Follow recipe on bag for candy apples.)
Heat chocolate chips slowly. While caramels are melting, spread pecan pieces on cookie sheet.
Spoon caramel on pecan pieces.
(Not too close to each other.)

Chill cookie sheet (with caramel drops on pecan pieces) in refrigerator or freezer. Remove cookie sheet from chill and "lift" caramel out with a fork and place on empty cookie sheet or plate. Use the back of a spoon to "paint" the chocolate on top of the caramel. Chill or eat 'em while they are warm.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Add hot water to jello; let partly jell.
Mix cream cheese with half and half.
Add to jello.
Let partly jell.
Add nuts, pineapple and celery.
Let jell.

title: homemade tortillas
directions: Warm water to make soft dough.
Knead with very small amount of flour - let dough rest a few minutes - roll small balls out thin to look like tortillas.
Fry in dry heavy skillet.
When they are cooking just right they will bubble.
Place each one between tea towels to cool.
Use the same dough to cup up into small triangle and fry in hot oil for sopaipillas.

title: maple bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan with 1 tablespoon butter.
In a large mixing bowl, beat together butter and sugar.
Add vanilla, maple syrup and eggs.
In a medium bowl, sift together flour and baking powder; add to maple mixture. Blend in oats, coconut and walnuts.
Spread the batter evenly in pan and bake for about 30 minutes, until lightly browned and wooden pick comes out clean.
Cool on a rack, then cut into bars. Makes 2 dozen bars.

title: mom's texas hash
directions: In large skillet, saute onions and green peppers in shortening until onions are yellow. Add ground beef, saute until mixture breaks into little pieces. Add tomatoes, rice and seasoning. Place in casserole dish & cover tightly. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until rice is done.

title: dump salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk together.
Then add cherry pie filling, pineapple, coconut and pecans.
Amount of pecans is up to you.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Melt margarine, oil and cocoa in large saucepan.
Add sugar, flour, eggs and salt.
Stir.
Add buttermilk, soda and vanilla. Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350° in sheet cake pan.

title: tortilla wheels
directions: Cream softened cream cheese and sour cream together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spread on flour tortilla and roll. Refrigerate until firm.
Slice and serve.
Serves lots.

title: baked eggplant slices
directions: Peel eggplant and slice 1/2-inch thick.
Beat egg and add milk; dip slices into egg and milk mixture and cover slices well with cereal flakes.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Heat butter or margarine in large shallow pan.
Place slices in pan and bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Turn slices and bake for 5 minutes or until tender.
Serves 6.

title: date roll
directions: Boil sugars, milk and corn syrup until it forms a stiff ball when dropped in cold water. Remove from heat and add dates, vanilla,
butter,
cherries
and
nuts. Mix all ingredients well and form into roll. Chill before slicing to serve.

title: poppy chicken
directions: Line casserole dish with chicken.
Make sauce of sour cream and soup.
Pour over chicken.
Make topping of cracker crumbs and margarine.
Sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: party snacks
directions: Mix first four ingredients together. Roll into small balls. Roll the balls in cereal. Put on waxed paper.
Chill 1 hour and serve.

title: classic raisin pie
directions: In saucepan, combine raisins, orange juice and water; bring to boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 5 minutes.
Combine sugar and allspice; stir into raisin mixture.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened, about 1 minute.
Remove from heat; stir in nuts and lemon juice.
Cool 10 minutes; pour into pastry-lined pie plate. Cover with top crust; seal and flute edges.
Cut slits for steam. Brush with beaten egg; sprinkle generously with sugar.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: beer batter chicken
directions: In a medium bowl, mix the first 3 ingredients with a fork.
In another bowl, beat together beer, egg and 2 teaspoons salad oil. Stir liquid into flour mixture.
Coat half of chicken pieces with batter.

title: french apple cake
directions: Beat together eggs, oil and vanilla. Mix dry ingredients together.
Mix in half dry and then other half.
Stir in apples. Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Test for doneness.
Let sit for 20 minutes.

title: four-layer delight
directions: 1st Layer:
Melt butter; mix in flour.
Work into a dough and press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Cool.

title: chicken soup
directions: In Dutch oven, mix water and chicken; bring to a boil and cook 30 minutes.
Debone chicken and throw skin away.
Shred chicken with fork and place back into boiling water.
Add onion, salt, pepper, garlic and spaghetti.
Cook another 15 minutes, then add cream of chicken soup.
Stir with fork until dissolved.
Cook on low to medium for 15 minutes.
Serve hot with buttered toast or French bread.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: shannon's favorite stuffed mushrooms
directions: Steam mushrooms for 5 minutes.
Cool and remove stems.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add drained crab meat, half of the cheese and bread crumbs.
Heat through.
Stuff mushrooms with crab mixture and place on baking dish, crab-side up.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and drizzle with melted butter.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Serve immediately.

title: the ruby slipper
directions: Combine cake mix, sour cream, water and eggs in large bowl. Blend, then beat at medium speed 2 minutes until creamy.
Spoon 1/3 of batter into well-greased and floured 10-inch fluted tube pan (Bundt).
Sprinkle with 1/2 the gelatin.
Repeat layers. Spread remaining batter over gelatin to cover.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes until cake springs back when lightly pressed. Cool in pan 5 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar, if desired.

title: hoe cake
directions: Moisten cornmeal and salt with hot water and let stand 1 hour. Shape with hands into flat cakes, about 1/2-inch thick.
Fry on hot greased griddle until brown.
Turn and brown on other side. Serve hot with bacon and syrup.
A delicious treat for breakfast.

title: fruit pudding
directions: On wax paper, stir together the flour, baking soda and salt. In a 2-quart souffle dish (about 8 x 3-inches) or a similar casserole, thoroughly beat together the egg, granulated sugar and vanilla; stir in the fruit cocktail.
Add the flour mixture and stir until moistened.
In a small bowl, stir together the brown sugar, cinnamon and pecans; sprinkle over top.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean and pudding is well browned, 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve warm topped with vanilla ice cream.
Makes 6 servings.

title: harvey wallbanger cake
directions: Mix together in a bowl; beat with electric mixer for 4 minutes.
Pour into well-greased, lightly floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, then let cool for 40 to 45 minutes. After it is done, sift powdered sugar all over it.

title: crock-pot pot roast
directions: Place roast in crock-pot containing a couple of spoonfuls of water.
Pour onion soup mix over roast.
Place carrots and potatoes in pot.
Cover and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours.

title: dilly bread
directions: Combine sugar, onion, butter, dill seed, salt, baking soda and egg with cottage cheese.
Add yeast mixture to cottage cheese mixture and 2 to 2 1/2 cups flour.
Beat to make dough stiff.
Let rise until light and double in size (50 to 60 minutes).
Stir down, turn into well-greased bread loaf pan or casserole dish.
Let rise 35 to 40 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Brush with butter; sprinkle with salt.

title: quick mexi dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread chili over cheese.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 400° until cheese melts.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: bavarian mints
directions: Melt chocolate chips, baking chocolate square and butter in a double boiler or microwave.
Blend in vanilla, milk and peppermint.
Mix well.
Refrigerate for5 minutes.
Beat with electric mixer for 1 minute and refrigerate for 5 minutes.
Do this a total of 3 times.
Press into a 7 x 10-inch buttered dish and let harden.
It can be refrigerated but it is not necessary.

title: brown sugar nut cake
directions: Cream the first 4 ingredients until like ice cream, then add eggs one at a time.
Beat well after each.
Add milk and flour; mix well.
Add vanilla, then add nuts.
Bake in a tube pan 2 hours and 15 minutes at 274°.

title: diabetic applesauce cookies
directions: Combine the flour, cinnamon, soda, salt, nutmeg and allspice. Blend the oats, raisins, applesauce, oil, egg, vanilla and sweetener into mixture. Mix until moist. Drop by teaspoon onto lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Keep in a cool place.

title: sunday chicken
directions: Put chicken breasts in a baking dish (I use a 9 x 13-inch dish).
Lightly sprinkle salt and garlic salt on chicken.
In a bowl, mix the next 3 ingredients and pour mixture over chicken. (Robert and I enjoy this sauce so much that I double the quantities.)
Bake, covered, at 300° for 2 hours.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Fruit garnishes make this dish pretty.

title: mexican bean spread
directions: Put into blender or food processor.
Use as a dip or spread on bread and broil in oven with sliced tomato.

title: jogging in jug
directions: Mix all ingredients together; drink 1/4 cup a day.
Helps lower high blood pressure and keeps vital organs clear.

title: merlin's fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease a baking pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch). Put flour, paprika and salt in a clean plastic or paper bag. Shake it to mix the ingredients.
Place chicken in bag. Shake to coat chicken.
Coat all chicken pieces.
Bake for 55 minutes or until chicken is golden brown.

title: apple date cake
directions: Combine first six ingredients, beating well.
Add soda to flour and add to first mixture.
Beat well.
Add apples, dates and nuts.
Mix well.
Batter will be very thick.
You may have to mix with your hands.
Spoon into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Melt in saucepan the first 4 ingredients.
Mix flour and sugar.
Add chocolate mixture, buttermilk with soda dissolved in it, eggs and vanilla.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: carrot cake
directions: Blend together sugar, oil and eggs.
Sift salt, flour, baking powder, soda and cinnamon together.
Add to sugar mixture and beat for 1 minute.
Add pineapple, coconut, vanilla, carrots and pecans. Pour mixture into lightly floured Bundt pan and bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Test by toothpick.

title: quick pizza casserole
directions: Cook ground beef in a skillet over medium heat until browned, stirring to crumble.
Drain off drippings.
Spoon beef into an 8-inch square baking dish.
Top with pizza sauce and cheese.
(You can add onions, peppers or mushrooms.)
Combine biscuit mix, milk and eggs; heat until smooth.
Pour mixture over casserole, covering evenly.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes. Yield: 6 servings.

title: mother's patience candy
directions: Melt 1 cup sugar in a pan.
Stir as needed to keep mixture from sticking to the pan.
In a saucepan, combine remaining sugar and milk.
Bring to a boil; then, reduce heat.
When the first sugar is melted, pour it slowly into the milk mixture and cook to a soft ball stage.
Remove pan from the heat.
Pour in the vanilla.
Stir thoroughly.
Cool for ten minutes.
Stir until the candy mixture loses its gloss and begins to get firm.
Pour onto a buttered cookie sheet or into a rectangular casserole dish.
Let the candy harden; then cut into small squares.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix pineapple (juice and all), sour cream and dry pudding. Pour into pie crust. Top with softened Cool Whip. Refrigerate until served.

title: bran muffins(may refrigerate for 1 month)
directions: Alternately add flour and bran mixture.
Bake 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Cook first 9 ingredients until all vegetables are done.
Then make a paste of remaining ingredients.
Add to the mixture and allow to cook until smooth.

title: good broccoli casserole
directions: Soften Cheez Whiz and mix with mushroom soup.
Add remaining ingredients and mix all together.
Bake 1/2 to 3/4 hour or until done at 350°.

title: lake martin banana pudding
directions: In a saucepan, blend together 3/4 cup sugar (remainder to be used later), flour and salt.
Slowly stir in 2 cups milk (remainder to be used later).
Cook on medium heat, adding remainder of milk.
Stir often as custard thickens, being careful to mix in the bottom of the custard that tends to stick to the saucepan.

title: deb's fancy gorp
directions: Mix and store in an airtight container.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Blend ingredients together in blender until smooth.
Chill and use for dip.

title: parsley noodles with beef & mushroom
directions: Heat oven to 375 degrees.
Cook ground beef and onion, drain. Combine sauce mix, 1 1/2 C. water, beef mixture, mushrooms and paprika in a 1 1/2 qt. casserole dish.
Cover and bake until hot and bubbly.
Cook and drain noodles.
Toss with butter and parsley.
Serve beef sauce over the noodles.

title: swedish nuts
directions: Toast almonds and pecans in slow oven (325°) until light brown.
Fold sugar and salt into egg whites.
Beat until stiff peaks form.
Fold nuts into meringue.

Melt butter in a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan; spread nut mixture over butter. Bake in slow oven (325°) about 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes, or until nuts are coated with a brown covering and no butter remains in pan.
Cool.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: not so rich pecan pie
directions: Cream butter.
Slowly beat in brown sugar and salt.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat briskly.
Add pecans and blend into mixture. Pour into pastry shell.
Bake about 30 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven until pie is set.
Serve plain or with whipped cream.

title: chicken casserole
directions: (Use 8 1/2 x 11 Pyrex dish.)
Mix all and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: carolers crunch
directions: Combine evaporated milk, sugar and butter in a medium saucepan.
Bring to a full boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add butterscotch pieces and vanilla and stir until smooth. Combine 1 quart popcorn and 1 cup pecans.
Add to mixture; toss lightly.
Drop by teaspoons on wax paper.
Enjoy!
Nice for a holiday gift.

title: polynesian hot dogs
directions: Slice the hot dogs lengthwise to form a pocket.
Fill hot dogs with drained pineapple. Wrap bacon around stuffed hot dog; secure ends with toothpick.
Barbecue on grill over medium heat, turning several times until bacon is crisp.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except nuts, with hands.
Shape into a ball.
Roll in pecans.
Parsley or chopped dried beef may be used instead of nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: mexican "hot dip"("teenagers devour")
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Chop green onions and green pepper; add to meat.
Cut Velveeta cheese into pieces and add to meat.
Add all other ingredients at this time, too.
Mix in a slow cooker for about 3 hours.
Serve with chips.

title: burgers
directions: Mix together and make into patties.
Fry in a small amount of oil until brown.
Serve on hamburger buns and garnish as desired.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Make a layer with each ingredient in a glass bowl.
Start with a layer of lettuce, then onions, tomatoes and green peas.
Spread Miracle Whip over peas; sprinkle the cheese on top of the Miracle Whip and then top with bacon bits.
You can substitute any of the ingredients with other things if you do not like some of these ingredients.
Mushrooms, green pepper or red peppers are also good in this salad.

title: banana split delight
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cake according to package directions.
Pour into greased jelly roll pan and bake 20 minutes. Cool.
Combine pudding, cream cheese and milk.
Beat until smooth.
Spread on cooled cake.
Sprinkle drained pineapple on top of filling.
Slice bananas and arrange on pineapple.
Spread whipped topping on top of bananas.
Garnish with cherries, nuts and chocolate syrup.

title: pumpkin - raisin bread
directions: Beat together the oil, sugar, eggs and pumpkin until light and fluffy.
Combine the flours, baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon and raisins in bowl.
Stir into the creamed mixture with the milk or orange juice.
Pour into an oiled 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serves 15.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.

title: fruit bars
directions: Cook raisins and save 1 cup liquid.
Dissolve soda in liquid after raisins are cooked.
Cream the sugar, eggs and shortening. Add dry ingredients, raisins and liquid.
Bake in a greased and floured thin sheet pan. Sprinkle top with sugar and walnut nutmeats.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: goo-goo cake
directions: Stir together 2 eggs, butter and cake mix.
Add the nuts (will be stiff dough).
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan (like a crust).
Mix the cream cheese, confectioners sugar and 2 eggs; beat well.
Pour over crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: humdingers
directions: Mix dates, sugar and margarine and cook 10 minutes.
Add vanilla, Rice Krispies and nuts.
Form into balls and roll in powdered sugar.

title: raspberry salad(german)
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; add the raspberries with juice.
Pour into pan or mold and chill in refrigerator until firm. Combine marshmallows and cream cheese; mix together.
Add whipping cream and beat with beater until thick or stiff.
Spread over gelatin mixture.
Chill thoroughly.
Decorate top with candies. This looks great at Christmastime.

title: broccoli-cheese whiz
directions: Bring water, onions and butter to boil.
Add broccoli; cook 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add rice.
Let stand 5 minutes. Add cheese and soup.
Turn into casserole.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 325°.
If desired, top with croutons last 5 minutes of baking for crunchy topping.

title: rachel's sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients together and add to mixture.
Roll out on floured cloth or board.
Cut as desired.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.
Glaze with powdered sugar mixed with water and food coloring.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan.
Add potatoes, onion and celery.
Cook over low heat for 15 to 20 minutes or until tender, stirring frequently; do not brown.
Add half and half, milk, bacon, salt, bouillon, pepper, garlic powder, bay leaf and cayenne pepper; mix well.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Simmer, covered, over low heat for 30 to 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove bay leaf.
Pour half the soup into blender container.
Puree until smooth.
