Return to saucepan.
Cook until heated through, stirring.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef; mix in tomato sauce and taco sauce.
Set aside.
Place a large spoonful of cottage cheese in each tortilla and roll like a burrito.
In a 9 x 12-inch baking pan, alternate layers of filled tortilla and sauce mixture.
Cover the top of pan with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and let stand for 15 minutes to set.

title: cherry cream cheese salad
directions: Blend condensed milk and cheese until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Fold together and chill.

title: crock-pot chicken
directions: Mix cream cheese, chicken soup and Italian dressing mix. Pour over frozen chicken breasts in crock-pot.
Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: prune cake
directions: Stir together until dissolved over medium heat; cook until soft ball.
Pour over hot cake left in pan to cool.

title: stuffed manicotti
directions: Brown and drain ground beef with garlic.
Place in a mixing bowl.
Stir in the following: cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese, salt and mayo.
Stuff mixed ingredients into cooked manicotti shells.

title: pizza dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix salt, sugar and oil into yeast mixture.
Mix into flour, mixing well. Let rest 10 to 20 minutes.
Spread out on well-greased large cookie sheet or two 10-inch pizza pans.
Pinch up edges.
Put on your favorite toppings.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Crumble raw biscuits with hands, or cut into little pieces with scissors.

Place in a tube pan in layers, sprinkling between each layer with mixture of white sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon. Place brown sugar, oleo and 1 tablespoon cinnamon in a saucepan and bring to a boil on range.
Pour hot mixture over biscuits in tube pan and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes, or until browned and done.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: If using whole chicken, boil until done and debone.
Put soup and 1 cup (soup can) of milk and onion in pan and cook until onion is clear.
Add a can of chopped green chilies and chicken.
Cook about 5 minutes.
Let simmer.
Dip tortillas in hot oil, then layer mix, tortillas and cheese.
Repeat.
Cook in oven until cheese melts at 350°.
Let stand 30 minutes, then serve.

title: baked egg dish
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray bottom and sides of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Line bottom of pan with hash browns.
Crack eggs on top of hash browns and break yolks (do not scramble).
Sprinkle with salt and pepper, then 1/2 of the cheese.
Pour milk over the layers in the pan; sprinkle with onion, green peppers, meat and remaining cheese.
Cover; refrigerate overnight.
Bake about 40 minutes.

title: marinating sauce for steak
directions: Combine ingredients and marinate meat overnight.

title: tomato soup(canning)
directions: Put the first 5 ingredients in pot and cook until tender, about 45 minutes. Run through a sieve. Put juice back in pot. Add the flour mixed with water, butter or margarine, salt, sugar and black pepper. Cook together about 20 minutes. Put in jars and process in pressure cooker for 20 minutes at 5 pounds pressure. Makes 18 pint jars.

title: crispy kraut salad
directions: Chop onion, celery and green pepper.
Drain kraut well.
Make dressing from sugar, salad oil and vinegar.
Mix all ingredients together.
Marinate for an hour.
Put some pimentos in also (makes it look pretty).
Makes 6 servings.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain well.
Stir in both soups.
Mix well. Pour in casserole dish.
Cover with grated Cheddar cheese.
Top with Tater Tots.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: eagle brand milk
directions: Pour in blender and mix.

title: fudge
directions: Cook sugar and evaporated milk in a heavy saucepan until mixture boils.

Turn heat low and continue cooking for 10 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and immediately add chocolate chips, Karo syrup, butter and vanilla. Stir well until chocolate has melted and fudge is smooth and creamy. Add nuts and mix until blended.
Immediately pour into buttered 8-inch pan. Surface will set rapidly so spread quickly. Chill 1 to 2 hours or until firm.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook hamburger and onion together for about 10 minutes. Drain.
Add to other ingredients.
Mix and bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: garden relish
directions: In a large bowl, combine vegetables. In a jar with a tight fitting lid, combine other ingredients.
Pour dressing over vegetables.
Toss until well coated.
Refrigerate, covered, about 2 hours before serving.
Makes 5 cups.

title: cottage cheese dip
directions: Place all ingredients for a few seconds in a blender until creamy, smooth and fluffy.
Arrange on tray with raw vegetables.

title: kringle
directions: Mix flour and margarine together.
Put in sour cream like a pie crust.
Refrigerate overnight in aluminum foil and flour. Take out 1 hour and knead about 30 times.
Cut in half.
Roll out long ways.
Use one-half cup pie fruit filling on each half.
Fold dough over filling.
Put on cookie sheet pan.
Bake at 425° until brown.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Stew chicken in salted water until tender.
Remove meat from bones.
Soak tortillas in hot broth until wilted.
Line a 9 x 12-inch layer pan with tortillas.
Add diced chicken.
Mix other ingredients and pour over chicken.
Spread Ro-Tel tomatoes over soup mixture.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown beef and onions in 10 or 12-inch skillet.
Add all cans of ingredients (5); let simmer.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, lay 6 corn tortilla shells.
Cover shells with half the meat mixture. Sprinkle top with cheese, then repeat shells, meat, then cover good with cheese.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: betsy's grilled marinated pork chops
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chops, and mix well.
Pour marinade over pork chops and marinate at least 3 hours.
Grill over medium coals, basting with remaining marinade.
Unused marinade will keep in refrigerator for two weeks.

title: easy cheese pie
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Gradually add Eagle Brand milk; mix well.
Add the vanilla; mix.
Add lemon juice; hand mix until fluffy.
Pour into pie shell; let set in refrigerator overnight. Top with cherry pie filling before serving.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add water and oil.
Add eggs, beating after each addition.
Pour into well-greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with powdered sugar.

title: petite cheese cakes
directions: You will need 24 or 50 paper bake cups.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Slice cake and line a 9 x 13-inch pan with cake.
Mix jello, using package directions.
Pour over cake.
Chill until set.
Mix pudding, using package directions.
Pour over jello.
Chill.
Top with Cool Whip and garnish with fresh strawberries.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add applesauce and then dry ingredients which have been sifted together.
Then add raisins and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan and bake for about 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Combine with other ingredients.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce to 350° and bake 20 to 30 minutes. Cool.
Beat egg whites for the meringue.

title: velma's custard pie
directions: Mix thoroughly eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Slowly stir in hot milk.
At once pour into shell.
Dash top with nutmeg.
Bake in hot 475° oven for 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to 425° and bake 10 minutes longer or until knife comes out clean.
Cool on rack.

title: strawberry jello
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water. Add strawberries and stir to thaw.
Add bananas and pineapple with a little juice.
Spray jello mold with cooking spray. Fill mold half full of jello mixture. Refrigerate.
When firm, spread sour cream on top. Fill mold the rest of the way with jello mixture.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: pecan pie(for diabetics)
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; beat in sweetener and baking powder.
Stir in cracker crumbs and chopped pecans.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: jelly centers - thumbprints
directions: Mix ingredients and rest dough for one hour.
Pinch off dough and form small ball.
Lay on cookie sheet and depress center with your thumb.
Bake until half done at 375°, about 5 to 10 minutes, then add a dab of jelly to center.
Finish baking.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Combine biscuit mix, milk and butter in large bowl and stir until blended. Refrigerate 30 minutes. Divide into 2 portions. Roll out 1 portion on floured surface to 1/8-inch thick rectangle, about 10 x 7-inches. Spread with half the sausage. Roll lengthwise into long roll. Repeat with remaining dough and sausage. Place rolls in freezer until hard enough to cut easily. Cut rolls into thin slices. Place on baking sheets. Bake 15 minutes or until golden brown. Serve hot and refrigerate leftovers.

title: quick batch pudding cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients; form dough into small balls.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet for 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Makes about 2 dozen small (1 1/2-inch) cookies.

title: shrimp butter
directions: Blend in butter, lemon juice and onion.
Chop and add shrimp (drained).
Mix all together well.
Serve with plain crackers.

title: pumpkin crunch goody
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add pumpkin, sugar, cinnamon, milk and salt.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over top.

title: chicken rollatini
directions: Chicken cutlets should be cut to approximately same size (8 to 10 pieces).
Dip each cutlet in bread crumbs and cover.
Bring broccoli to boil and simmer for 10 minutes.
Let cool and chop into bite size pieces.
Cut Mozzarella into thin strips (one strip per cutlet), approximately 1/2 x 3 inches.

title: baked beans
directions: Wash beans.
Cover with cold water and bring to a full boil. Remove from heat and let stand covered for 1 hour.
Dice onion and add to beans.
Add salt pork and cook until beans are tender. Remove pork.
Add sugar, catsup and molasses.
Put in baking dish. Slice salt pork and place on top.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 350° or until browned.

title: european cheese cake
directions: *Available from Rita Ramuno, phone #524-1492.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Combine soups, milk and melted butter.
Place raw rice in bottom of pan.
Pour 1/2 liquid over rice and mix.
Place chicken on top of rice and pour remaining liquid over chicken.
Sprinkle almonds on top, then sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake, uncovered, 3 hours at 275°.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cut unpared squash into bite size pieces.
Lightly cook and drain.
Mix dressing with butter.
Mix all ingredients with 1/2 dressing mixture.
Put in buttered casserole and top with remaining dressing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix all in order.
Add to pie crust.
Bake at 350° until it sets firm (toothpick comes out clean).

title: cornbread salad
directions: Cook cornbread according to directions.
Cool and crumble into fine crumbs.
Mix other ingredients with cornbread.
May be made the night before.
When ready to serve, mix in enough of mayonnaise or salad dressing to make mixture moist.
May be served cool or warm.

title: cowboy soup
directions: Brown meat and onion, stirring with a fork to break up meat. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bring to a boil.
Cover. Reduce heat and cook until tender.
You will need a large pot to cook in.

title: garlic roasted potatoes
directions: Cube potatoes (1-inch).
Combine all ingredients and bake at 400° for 40 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serves 6.

title: chicken bake
directions: Flour
chicken
with dry pancake mix.
Brown in skillet until just
starting
to
brown;
remove chicken and place in casserole dish.
Pour
can
of mushroom soup mixed with water over
chicken. Add
salt,
pepper
and paprika to taste.
Add slices of onion. Cover and bake at 350° until tender.

title: apple dumplings(simple, easy dessert)
directions: Prepare pie crust; put in ball and wrap in wax paper. Refrigerate.

title: christmas punch(fresno county historical society)
directions: To one quart of apple cider add cloves, cinnamon and allspice. Simmer for 5 minutes in a covered container.
Add 1.3 cups brown sugar.
Simmer for 5 minutes and then add 1 quart of cranberry juice.

title: cheese danish
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 baking dish.
Unroll 1 can crescent rolls and put in the bottom of the baking dish, pressing perforations together.
Ease the dough up the sides a little bit.
Combine the cream cheese, 1 cup sugar, 1 egg and the vanilla.
Mix until smooth with a mixer.
Pour over the dough. Unroll the second package of crescent rolls.
Lay on top and pinch the sides together, top and bottom.
Mix together the remaining sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Melt the butter and combine with the sugar mixture.
Pour over the top.
Bake for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Put meat in oven and bake at 400° for 40 minutes.
Add sauce mixture and reduce heat; bake until tender.

title: baked salmon
directions: Rinse and pat dry large piece of fish.
Rub inside and out with your choice of herbs, salt and pepper.
Lay slices of onion and lemon within body cavity.
Lay salmon on large piece of heavy-duty foil and place in roasting pan.
Fold foil loosely over salmon and crimp top, making airtight.
Bake in 375° oven for thirty minutes. Fold back foil and continue baking until it flakes, approximately 40 minutes longer.
Remove skin, lift out backbone and serve.

title: easy chicken and dressing
directions: Saute onion and celery until tender.
Mix all the ingredients and pour into greased casserole.
Pour 1/2 stick melted margarine over top of dressing.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, Jell-O, food coloring and water; heat to boiling.
Boil 1 minute.
Cool.
Arrange berries in pie shell. Pour cooled mixture over berries.
Chill 2 hours.

title: pineapple bars
directions: Press into 8 x 11-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes in 350° oven.

title: chocolate coconut cake(no sugar)
directions: Beat egg and butter; mix with milk and flavorings.
Mix together flour, cocoa, baking powder and soda.
Add milk and flour mixture to butter mixture.
Beat on low speed; add coconut.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 8-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spinach roll-ups
directions: Mix all ingredients except for the tortillas.
Spread the spinach mixture evenly over the tortillas.
Roll up tortillas like a jelly roll. Wrap in waxed paper and chill.
Cut into 1-inch slices and place on a platter.

title: roquekraut
directions: Cook onion in fat until soft.
Add cabbage and steam on medium with needed water for 15 minutes.
Add apples, vinegar, sugar and salt.
Turn heat to low and cook about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: homemade peanut butter cups
directions: In 1 quart saucepan, combine chocolate chips and shortening. Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until melted and smooth (3 to 5 minutes). Loosen top paper cup from stack, but leave in stack for greater stability while being coated. With small paint brush coat inside top cup evenly with about 1 Tbsp. melted chocolate to about 1/8-inch thickness, bringing coating almost to the top of cup, but not over edge. Repeat until 30 cups are coated; refrigerate cups. In 2 quart saucepan, combine butter or margarine and peanut butter. Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until melted (4 to 6 minutes). Stir in confectioners sugar and graham cracker crumbs. Press about 1 1/2 tablespoons filling into each chocolate cup. Spoon about 1/2 tsp. melted chocolate on top of filling; spread to cover. Freeze until firm (about 2 hours). Carefully peel off paper cups. Store refrigerated.

title: collard greens and ham hocks
directions: Cover ham hocks with water in large pot.
Bring to a boil, then simmer, covered, for 1 to 2 hours or until tender.
Saute salt pork until crisp on both sides.
When ham hocks are done, stir in salt pork and its fat with 1 cup onion, sugar and greens (washed and cut up).
Cover pot and simmer for 45 to 60 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease two 8-inch round pans.
Mix all dry ingredients.
Mix all wet ingredients.
Combine and pour into pans.
Bake for 35 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: brownie cupcakes
directions: Combine sugar, flour and eggs. Stir to blend. Melt butter and chocolate in saucepan. Add nuts and stir to mix. Combine the flour and butter mixtures; add vanilla. Blend only to mix well.
Pour into 24 paper-lined muffin tins. Spray liners with Pam! Bake at 325° for 23 minutes. These travel and freeze well.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions; drain.
Place spinach on paper towels; squeeze until barely moist.
Combine with remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into a buttered 2 1/2 quart casserole.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour or until center is set.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients and pile into a buttered baking dish. Sprinkle cinnamon on top, if desired.
Bake for 30 minutes at 450°.
Serves 6.

title: no bother cookies
directions: Beat egg whites stiff.
Add sugar gradually.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Add vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Put in preheated 400° oven.
Turn off oven.
Leave cookies in overnight (or a few hours).

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chips and butter in a pan.
Pour over Rice Chex cereal. Make sure the cereal is mixed real well.
Pour powdered sugar over cereal mixture.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Blend the first 4 ingredients together.
Mix the pudding and milk.
Add to the strawberries and jello.
Fold in the Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: sausage balls
directions: Crumble, cook and drain sausage.
Drain sauerkraut.
Combine with sausage and cream cheese.
Refrigerate until cool.
Roll into balls.
Dip in egg and milk mixture.
Roll balls in bread crumbs and parsley mix.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 30 to 40 balls.

title: lemon filling for pies
directions: Mix cornstarch and sugar thoroughly.
Pour boiling water over mixture; boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add butter, lemon juice and rind.
Pour this
mixture over beaten eggs.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Add meringue.

title: adriane's turkey chili
directions: Heat olive oil in skillet.

Add minced onions, garlic and green peppers and saute, stirring constantly for about 3 minutes. Add turkey and brown. Transfer turkey mixture into large saucepan and add all remaining ingredients, except arrowroot and optional kidney beans. Bring to a boil, and let boil for 10 minutes. Reduce to a simmer, uncovered, until the sauce is thick, about 20 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Stir in arrowroot.
Add kidney beans, if desired.
Put top on saucepan.
Cook an additional 5 minutes. Turn off saucepan.
Leave top on saucepan for at least 10 minutes. Serve good with rice, baked potato or hot dogs on a bun.

title: caraway cabbage and kielbasa
directions: Cut kielbasa lengthways and brown to taste.
Cut kielbasa into 1-inch pieces.
Set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Cook 12 to 14 minutes on High in microwave.
Add kielbasa and cook until heated.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottoms only of loaf pans, 9 x 9 x 3-inch, or 3 loaf pans, 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inches.
Mix soy margarine and dry sweetener in large bowl.
Add eggs, zucchini and water. Blend in flour, baking powder and cinnamon.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Pour into pans.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean or about 60 to 70 minutes; cool slightly. Loosen sides of loaves from pans.
Cool completely before slicing.

title: skillet spinach
directions: Spray skillet with 2 to 4 squirts of olive oil spray.
Heat minced garlic, raisins, pine nuts and fresh mushrooms for approximately 3 to 5 minutes until mushrooms release their moisture.
Add spinach and continue heating on medium until spinach is wilted, stirring all the while to prevent sticking.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Serve immediately.

title: kisses
directions: Beat
egg
whites,
salt,
cream
of tartar and vanilla until soft
peaks
form.	Add
sugar gradually, beating until stiff. Fold
in chocolate chips and nuts.	Cover cookie sheet with brown paper and drop by teaspoon onto brown paper.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.
Cool completely and remove.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a tube pan.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake for 1 hour or until a toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: lemonade cookies
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar.
Add egg; beat until light and fluffy.
Sift together the flour and soda; add alternately to mixture with 1/4 cup of lemonade concentrate.
Drop dough from teaspoon, 2 inches apart, onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes, or until lightly browned around edge.
Brush hot cookies with lemonade concentrate.
Sprinkle with sugar. Cool.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: jan's hashbrown casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients except Rice Krispies and 1/3 cup margarine.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread over hashbrowns.
Bake 40 - 45 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease baking sheet with Crisco.
Combine Crisco, granulated sugar, brown sugar, eggs, vanilla and maple flavor in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed until well blended. Combine oats, flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture at low speed.
Beat until blended.
Increase speed to medium; beat 2 minutes.
Drop by tablespoon on baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Cook ground beef; season to taste.
Drain.
Add onion and sauces; simmer for 10 minutes, then add butter.
Mash boiled potatoes, adding butter, salt, pepper and milk to taste.
Add cans of vegetables.
Put hamburger mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, then add layer of vegetables.
Spread mashed potatoes on top, then grated cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: chicken dumplings
directions: Cook chicken until done.
Let chicken cool and remove it from the bones.
To chicken broth from cooking chicken, add the remaining ingredients and some water.
Then add salt and pepper to fit your taste.

title: meatball skillet
directions: You can substitute ground turkey.

title: barbecued tuna
directions: Trim crust from thinly sliced bread.
Cut bread into various shapes (circles, hearts, triangles, etc).
Top with the following spreads.
Place on a damp cloth and refrigerate, covered, until serving time.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: In a deep cast-iron skillet, fry sausage until done.
Reserve 2 to 3 tablespoons of drippings after draining.
Combine corn meal, flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
In a separate bowl, combine eggs, peppers, onion, corn, buttermilk and cheese.
Add to corn meal mixture.
Stir in sausage and reserved drippings.
Pour into greased skillet and bake at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve warm from skillet.
Yields 12 servings.

title: ragout
directions: Cover pork with water.
Cook until tender, about 1 hour.
Cool and skim off fat.
Mix ground beef with eggs, bread crumbs, salt and pepper.
Shape into tiny meatballs.
Roll in flour.

title: ratatouille
directions: Saute carrot, zucchini, onion, mushrooms and olives until tender.
Add lemon, salt, pepper, parsley, sweet basil and oregano.
Layer mixture with cheese and wheat germ or bread crumbs, ending with cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: blue ribbon apple pie
directions: Cut 5 tablespoons butter and Crisco into flour.
For TOPPING: combine 1 cup of flour mixture with sugars, cinnamon, and 3 tablespoons butter; reserve for pie crust.
Mix remaining flour mixture with 1 1/2 cups cheddar cheese and water.
Roll dough out on floured board; line 8 inch pie place forming standing rim.
Mix apple slices with lemon juice.
Fill pie shell with apples, mounding in center.
Combine 1 tablespoon flour with nutmeg; sprinkle over apples.
Cover apples with 1/2 of crumble mixture; sprinkle with remaining cheese and top with remaining crumble mixture.
Bake at 375 degrees for 40 minutes.
Makes one pie.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Soak crumbs in 1 quart chicken broth.
Saute onions and celery over low fire.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 325°.

title: strawberry-rhubarb pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, tapioca and salt together.
Line a 9-inch pie plate with shell.
Mix strawberries, rhubarb and sugar mixture together and place in pie shell.
Dot with butter and cover with top crust.
Bake in very hot oven at 450° for 10 minutes.
Then reduce heat to 350° and bake about 30 minutes longer.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Chop pepper, onion and cabbage.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased casserole dish. Cook 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Place sliced cheese on top about 15 minutes before it is done.

title: whole wheat grilled cheese sandwich
directions: Spread margarine on both sides of bread.
In a skillet toast one side of bread.
Remove bread from skillet.
Place 1 slice of American cheese and 1/2 slice of Swiss cheese on toasted side of 2 slices of bread.
Cover with toasted side of remaining 2 slices. Toasted sides of bread should be on the inside of sandwich. Return sandwich to skillet and toast on both sides until cheese melts.
Makes two delicious grilled cheese sandwiches.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Add chicken wings; marinate at least 24 hours.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: date-bran muffins
directions: Grind oats
in blender to make a coarse flour.
Mix all ingredients and
let stand to wet oats and bran.
Pack lightly into greased
and sprayed muffin tin.
Heap into muffin shapes as they do
not
rise.
Bake
at
for
35 to 40 minutes. Makes 12 muffins.

title: banana nutmeg cookies
directions: Cream sugar, egg and oil; add soda, salt, cinnamon, and nutmeg, mix well.
Add flour mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop mixture by teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 350° oven for 12-15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and place into a buttered 2 qt baking dish. Combine eggs, soup, cheese, onions and mayonnaise.
Pour over broccoli. Sprinkle with croutons.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: "tea" cakes
directions: Cream butter and shortening well.
Add sugar and cream well. Add eggs and cream well again.
Sift all dry ingredients together and add to the creamed mixture by 1/4 cup intervals until all flour is used.
Add vanilla.

title: microwave peanut clusters
directions: 1. Place chips in a medium, microwave-safe bowl. Cover and microwave on medium for 3-1/2 to 5-1/2 minutes, until chips are melted. Stir until smooth. (Or melt using a double boiler.)

title: million dollar pie
directions: Combine all ingredients well and pour into two graham cracker crust pie shells.
Chill until firm, about 2 or 3 hours.

title: salsa
directions: The first 7 ingredients, either chop up finely or put through food processor.
Add tomato juice.
Add salt, pepper and red pepper (enough until desired taste achieved).

title: world's lightest biscuits
directions: In a bread tray, sift generous amount of self-rising flour. Make an indention in the center.

In indentions, place shortening. Work this into the flour, adding flour as needed, using fingers. Add buttermilk until it forms the consistency of biscuit dough and can be handled without being sticky.
Roll out by hand and shape into biscuits on biscuit pan.
Bake about 10 minutes at 400°. Handle dough as little as possible.

title: broccoli soup
directions: In a large boiler, boil potatoes in water (half full of water).
When tender, add
broccoli and continue to cook until tender.
Turn heat to low and add soup and milk.
Thicken with flour.
Add salt to taste.	Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add vanilla, flour, nuts and salt.
This will be rather dry, but you just work it with your fingers until blended.
Roll into small balls and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, but not too brown.

title: fresh lemon pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients together; add boiling water.
Cook until thick (medium heat).
Mix a little mixture with beaten egg yolks and add to mixture.
Cook 3 minutes longer; cool.
Beat 3 egg whites until stiff; gradually add 2 tablespoons of sugar.
Beat again until stiff.
Pour filling in pie crust.
Spread meringue to very edge.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: blueberry jello salad
directions: Use a variety of fruit such as crisp pears and apples.
Peel and cut into bite-size pieces.
Add 1 can of drained pineapple chunks.
Add 1 to 2 small oranges, peeled and cut into bite-size pieces.
If in season, add green grapes or peaches or nectarines (peeled and cut into bite-size pieces).
Use your imagination! After mixing together, add low-fat lemon yogurt to act as dressing.
Top with slivered almonds if desired.
Keeps for several days in Tupperware.

title: marshmallow sauce (for fruit)
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and water.
Heat, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Then boil without stirring to firm ball stage (244° to 248°), about 10 minutes.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Slowly add hot syrup, beating at high speed until thick and fluffy. Add salt and vanilla.
Gently fold in mayonnaise and orange rind. Makes about 3 cups.

title: fruit cake
directions: Sprinkle 1/2 cup flour over nuts and fruit and set aside.
Mix sugars, margarine and cream.
Add eggs and mix.
Add wine and applesauce and mix.
Add flour and spices.
Mix and then add nuts and fruit.
Bake at 275° for about 1 hour or so.
Grease and flour bread pan.

title: reese's peanut butter cup oatmeal cookies
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat butter and peanut butter until light and fluffy.
Add sugars, eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Stir together flour, baking soda and salt; blend into peanut butter mixture.
Stir in oats.
Cover dough.
Chill until firm enough to handle.
Heat oven to 350°.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 9 to 11 minutes.
Remove wrappers from peanut butter cups and place one on each cookie, pressing down gently.

title: pepper relish
directions: Chop fine and put in boiling water and let stand 15 minutes. Put in colander and drain.
Put in cold water and let stand for 15 minutes.
Drain again.
Mix in sugar, salt and vinegar and cook until tender.
Place in canning jars.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine and bake at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese danish
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 1/2 c. sugar and vanilla.
In a 9x13 in. pan layer: 1 pkg. rolls, cream cheese mixture, 2nd pkg. rolls, sprinkle 1/4 c. sugar on top and drizzle melted butter on top. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: banana raisin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray loaf pan.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon in small bowl; set aside.
In large mixing bowl, combine margarine and sugar.
Beat until creamy and light.
Add egg and vanilla; beat thoroughly.
Add sifted ingredients alternately with bananas, beating gently (do not overbeat).
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Bake for 50 minutes.

title: fried zucchini squash
directions: Slice squash in thin lengthwise slices.
Roll in a mixture of flour, salt and pepper.
Deep fry until golden brown.

title: peach jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O, marshmallows, softened cream cheese and water over low heat.
Combine bananas and lemon juice.
Add milk, mayonnaise, pineapple and pecans.
Combine with Jell-O mixture and place in refrigerator until firm.

title: blini
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour 1/2 cup at a time into hot oil.

title: au gratin - beef bake(country supper)
directions: In a large skillet, cook beef over medium heat until no longer pink; drain. Stir in the potatoes and contents of the sauce mix. Add corn, tomatoes, milk, water and taco seasoning. Transfer to a greased 2-quart baking dish. Bake, covered in a 350° oven for an hour or until potatoes are tender. Sprinkle with cheese; bake an additional 5 minutes, until cheese is melted.

title: norwegian wafers
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine butter, egg yolks, honey and vanilla; blend well.
Add flour and chocolate chips.
Divide dough in half and roll between 2 sheets of waxed paper to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut in 2-inch circles. Bake 8 minutes.

title: liverwurst spread
directions: Combine all the ingredients together.
Tastes similar to pate.

title: apple bread
directions: Cream together the sugar, eggs and butter.
Add soda to dissolve in sour milk.
Add salt and vanilla.
Blend in flour. Fold in finely cut apples (leave peeling on).
Put in 3 greased loaf pans.
Top with brown sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Bake at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: fancy slaw
directions: Toast sesame seeds and almonds in 350° oven until light brown. Mix cabbage, Ramen noodles and onions together in bowl and refrigerate until ready to serve. Combine sugar, vinegar, pepper, oil, Ramen seasoning and salt. Pour over cabbage mixture just before serving. Then add toasted seeds and almonds. Toss until coated.

title: scalloped potatoes and ham
directions: Place potatoes and ham in long baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over potatoes and ham.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or 25 minutes on High in microwave oven.
Stir midway. Serves 4 to 6.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt. Add sugar, eggs and vanilla to melted butter or margarine. Blend in dry ingredients. Mix with nuts. Spread thin and evenly in a well-greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool and then cut into squares.

title: french vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix and freeze in ice cream freezer.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Drain well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and simmer.

title: chili con queso
directions: Brown the chopped onions with the meat.
Add chili pepper, tomato sauce and tomatoes.
Simmer for 5 minutes and then add the grated cheese.
Blend until melted.
Serve immediately.

title: chicken-mushroom rice
directions: Empty soup into boiler.
Add can of water; stir until blended. Bring to boiling point.
Add 1 can Minute rice, mushrooms (drained) and chicken with its liquid.
Stir until well blended. Remove from heat.
Cover; let sit until rice is tender.
(It will need to be stirred a couple of times while it is sitting.)
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: crush punch
directions: Mix
jello
and hot water together.
Chill for 2 hours. Mix the rest of the ingredients together and freeze in 4 equal parts. Remove
hours
before serving.
Pour 1 quart ginger ale over frozen punch before serving (1 quart ginger ale per 1 part punch).

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Brown ground beef and chopped onion.
Simmer until meat is done.
Add tomato sauce, rice, salt and pepper.
Slice top off bell peppers and core.
Fill each pepper equally with meat mixture until it reaches top.
Place upright in buttered casserole dish. Cover with foil.
Cook at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Makes 3 or 4 servings.

title: golden coconut balls
directions: Spread coconut in a large shallow pan.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes until golden brown.
Turn into a small pie pan.
Cool.

title: baby ruth cookies
directions: Sift together the flour, soda and salt.
Cream together the margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg.
Stir in Baby Ruth pieces and dry ingredients.
Add vanilla; blend well. Chill dough for 30 minutes.
Drop by half teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until done.
Remove from baking sheets; place on wire racks to cool.

title: oriental skillet chicken
directions: Coat chicken with flour, salt and pepper.
Heat
oil in large skillet and stir-fry 3 to 4 minutes.
Push chicken aside and add green pepper, onions and garlic.
Saute until onions are soft, stirring frequently.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Melt jello in 1 cup hot water.
Add 1 cup cold water.
Stir in pineapple (with juice), cranberries and 1 cup nuts.
Pour into mold or Pyrex dish.
Chill until set.

title: syrup cake
directions: Beat the egg until foamy.
Combine syrup and boiling water; when well mixed, add the shortening and stir until well blended. Mix in eggs.
Stir the dry ingredients together.
Set aside 1/2 cup of the dry mixture.
Combine the flour mixture and syrup mixture; beat until there are no lumps.
Dredge raisins in the flour mix and add to the batter.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan in a moderate 350° to 375° oven until done.
Test at 1 hour to see if done.
It will pull away from pan (slightly) and spring back when touched lightly on top.

title: christmas salad
directions: Mix ingredients and congeal in a casserole dish.
When congealed, top with topping mixture.

title: frosted strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve 2 packages strawberry jello in 1 3/4 cups boiling water.
Stir in frozen strawberries.
Stir until berries are thawed and jello begins to gel.
Stir in crushed pineapple, banana and chopped nuts.
Put in glass baking dish; when set frost with following:

title: pesto
directions: Combine oil, pepper and garlic in blender.
Add some basil and blend.
Add the rest gradually until thin.
If too thick, add more oil.
Pour into bowl and add cheese and pine nuts.
Mix well.
Put in small containers and drizzle oil onto the back of a spoon to form a protective layer on top of pesto.
Store in refrigerator or freezer.
Do not heat pesto.
(One cup of pesto for 1 pound pasta.)

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs and bananas.
Combine dry ingredients; sift into mixture alternately with sour milk.
Fold in nuts.
Bake in an 8 x 4 x 3-inch greased pan at 325° to 350° for one hour.
Remove loaf from oven; cool and then wrap in foil. Keep in refrigerator.

title: carmen's candy cane cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Thoroughly mix margarine, butter, confectioners sugar, egg and flavorings.
Blend in flour and salt. Divide dough in two portions.
Blend food color into half of dough.
Shape 1 teaspoon dough from each half into 4-inch rope.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream sugar and softened margarine.
Add eggs and vanilla. Mix well.
Mix flour, cream of tartar, soda and pecans.
Add to sugar-egg mixture.
Mix until blended.
Roll into rolls about 1 1/2-inch in diameter and place and wrap in wax paper or foil.
Put in the refrigerator at least 4 hours or may be kept in freezer and baked when you want.
Cut 1/4-inch thick slices and bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 8 to 10 minutes in a 425° oven.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix cheese, margarine and pepper.
Add flour and mix well. Add Rice Krispies and mix.
Shape into small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten balls with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed.
Drain and put in large mixing bowl. Add rice, butter, onion, milk, cheese whiz, and soup.
Mix and pour into casserole dish.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix 1/2 cup water and cornstarch to a thin paste.
Combine 1 1/2 cups water and sugar in top of double boiler and bring to a boil over direct heat.
Add cornstarch paste and cook until mixture thickens a little; return to double boiler and continue cooking until thick and smooth (15 minutes).
Pour over slightly beaten egg yolks and cook 1 minute longer.
Add lemon rind, juice and butter.
Blend well.
Cool and pour in pie shell.
Top with meringue made with 3 egg whites, 9 tablespoons sugar and 1 teaspoon lemon juice.

title: cowboy cornbread
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain off fat and discard.
Blend cornbread mix, corn, peppers, eggs and milk.
Spread 1/2 mixture in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Layer meat and cheese.
Pour rest of cornbread mixture on top and spread out evenly.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: blackberry cobbler(double crust)
directions: Roll 1/2 pastry thin; line 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Roll other half thin; cut into 2-inch strips.
Bake half the strips at 375° for 5 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: spicy chops and cabbage
directions: Trim fat from meat; cook fat in skillet to oil surface. Discard trimmings.
Brown chops in skillet.
Add the first 2 tablespoons water, the first 1/2 teaspoon salt, the cloves and bay leaf; cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Remove chops from skillet; discard cloves and bay leaf.
Add cabbage, apple and onion. Combine sugar, flour and the second 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Stir in vinegar and the remaining water.
Pour over cabbage, stirring to mix.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Return pork chops to skillet; cover and cook 20 minutes more or until chops and cabbage are tender.

title: green pea salad
directions: Prepare the petite peas as instructed on package.
Slice the chestnuts into shoestrings.
Mix all the ingredients together, chill and serve.

title: the ultimate cheese cake
directions: Cream softened cheese and sugar.
Add eggs, beating after each, sour cream, lemon juice, vanilla flavoring and whipping cream. Spread into pan with prepared crust.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 1 hour.
Turn oven off and leave in closed oven for another hour.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine eggs, flour and sugar. Mix well. Add cheese and both cans of corn, stirring to blend well. Pour into a lightly greased 2-quart casserole dish. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: monkey bread
directions: Separate the biscuits and mix into melted margarine.
Mix the sugar, nutmeg, cinnamon and nuts thoroughly, then mix together with margarine and biscuits.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
(Check center with fork to see if biscuits are done, not gooey.)

title: potatoes in sauce
directions: Melt fat in a heavy pan and saute onion and green pepper.
Do not brown.
Slice potatoes in thick slices and add to onion.
Add parsley, seasonings to taste and gravy or broth.
Cover pan and simmer until most of the liquid has evaporated.
Serves 4.

title: greek fish appetizers
directions: Mix flour, salt and paprika in small saucepan.
Stir in oil; mix until smooth.
Add milk; mix well.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until thick and smooth.
Remove from heat; stir in Worcestershire sauce, onion and whitefish.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Beat egg with 2 tablespoons water.
Shape fish mixture into balls using a teaspoon for each.
Roll in flour.
Dip in egg. Roll in bread crumbs.
Cook in deep fat at 350° until well browned. Drain on paper toweling.
Place on serving plate.
Insert end of small skewer or pick in each ball.
Makes 48 balls.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Bake on greased cookie sheets at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Shred cabbage in small pieces. Scrape carrots. Chop onions small. Sometimes she puts a little radishes. Mix salad dressing with a little milk, salt and pepper to taste. Mix until smooth. Pour over slaw. Enjoy.

title: boiled pot pie
directions: Combine flour, salt and baking powder.
Cut in shortening. Then add egg and water.
Mix to form a stiff dough.
Roll thin onto well floured surface; cut in 1/2-inch squares and drop into rapidly boiling meat broth.

title: spanish cream
directions: Keep 1/2
cup
milk
and
some
sugar
to mix with egg. Scald remaining milk and add gelatin.
Add egg mixture to milk and gelatin in
a double boiler.
Let come to boiling point or until egg custards.
Do not actually boil.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Mix well; then add the rest.
Mix well; pour in a well-greased and floured Bundt pan and bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: easy stew
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add soup and water.
Simmer for an hour. Serve with French bread.

title: sour cream salad
directions: Drain all ingredients except oranges and mix together. Refrigerate and serve.

title: borden's chocolate candy
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water.
Stir in milk.
Add nuts and raisins.
Drop on oiled paper.
This candy will harden without further cooking.
It will remain soft several days.

title: oyster soup
directions: Over medium heat, melt butter and cook celery until tender. Shake in flour, stirring constantly.
Pour in a little milk; stir until smooth, then slowly add remainder of milk.
Add dry seasonings; cook until boiling point is reached.
Add oysters, oyster liquid and onion.
Serve as soon as oysters are thoroughly hot and plump

title: bouquet garni
directions: Place parsley sprigs, celery leaves, thyme leaves and bay leaf on a square piece of cheesecloth. Bring the ends of the cheesecloth together and tie securely with string. To flavor foods such as soups, stews and sauces, add the bouquet garni to the foods as they cook.
Remove the cheesecloth bag before serving. Excellent!

title: pork steak casserole
directions: Brown pork steak.
In large casserole dish, place sliced potatoes, onion and green beans.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Place pork steak on top.
Add a little water to drippings in pan and pour over top.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for about 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.

title: mama's old fashioned banana pudding
directions: Mix above ingredients in 3 quart boiler (double).
Cook on medium high until thickened.
Line a big ovenproof bowl with layer of vanilla wafers.
Layer sliced bananas over wafers.
Pour a layer of pudding over the bananas.
Continue in layers until all used. Beat egg whites, gradually adding 1/2 cup sugar until whites stand in peaks.
Spread over top of pudding.
Brown slightly in 450° oven.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix ingredients together with a large heavy spoon in large bowl by hand or low speed on mixer.
Mixture will be stiff.
Pour into Bundt pan and bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.

title: orange salad supreme
directions: Dissolve jello with 1 cup very hot water, add only 2 more cups of water.
Mix in pineapple and congeal.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs and syrup together.
Add sugar, butter, vanilla and pecans.
Mix well and pour into pie shell that has been heated in pie pan and pressed down.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Stew chicken and bone (save broth).
Mix onion soup in chicken broth (should have at least 5 cups of liquid).
Add rice and boned chicken.
Cook as for rice, on low for about 30 minutes, or until rice is done, stirring occasionally.
You can cook in oven at 325° for 1 hour.
(If you cook in oven, you don't have to watch as closely.)

title: chicken cilantro
directions: Cook and stir onion and garlic in oil in 10-inch skillet until onion is tender.
Add chicken, salt and pepper.
Cook and stir over medium-high heat until done, about 5 minutes.
Stir in cilantro. Pour pan juices over chicken to serve.
Garnish with lemon wedge if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cranberry muffins
directions: In large bowl, stir yogurt, oat bran, sugar, egg white, oil, vanilla and lemon.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and cinnamon in a small bowl.
Stir flour mixture into the yogurt mixture until incorporated but not overmixed.
Fold in cranberries.
Divide batter among 12 cups of standard greased or nonstick muffin tin.
Sprinkle 1 teaspoon sugar over muffin mixture.
Bake at 400° for 13 to 16 minutes until brown and springy.

title: chicken n' gravy
directions: You also need 1 Reynolds oven bag, large size, 14 x 20-inch.

title: stir-fry chicken and broccoli
directions: Stir-fry chicken in oil until browned.
Add broccoli, pepper and water chestnuts.
Stir until tender.
Mix broth, soy sauce, cornstarch, sugar, garlic powder and ginger.
Add to skillet. Bring to boil; boil 1 minute.
Prepare rice as directed on package.
Serve chicken and vegetables over rice.

title: chicken pasta salad
directions: Bake chicken on broiler with Season-All sprinkled on top on both sides until chicken is tender.
Boil noodles in water until tender.
Drain and rinse with cool water.
Chop lettuce in a large bowl.
Mix lettuce, chicken, noodles and chopped carrots.
Serve with Ranch salad dressing or dressing of your choice.
Top with cheeses.

title: no oil mayonnaise
directions: Stir the 1/2 cup water and arrowroot powder.
Add to boiling water; boil again.
Put 1 cup of water in blender with oatmeal and cashews.
Blend.
Add the remaining ingredients and cornstarch mixture.

title: christmas nut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat after each addition.
Add lemon rind, juice and vanilla. Mix well.
Mix 1/4 cup flour with nuts and cherries.
Sift the remaining flour with baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Fold in nuts and cherries.
Pour into greased tube pan. Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 50 minutes or until cake tests done. Cool completely.
Freezes well.

title: strawberry-pretzel delight
directions: Break up pretzels.
Add 3/4 cup margarine to 3 tablespoons sugar.
Cream this.
Press mixture into broken pretzels in a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: banana-apple caterpillar
directions: Place lettuce leaf on salad plate; top with banana.
Cut 1/4-inch V-shaped slices halfway through the banana, spacing about 1-inch apart.
Place an apple slice, peel side up, in each cut. For eyes, gently press raisins into one end of banana.
Serve immediately.

title: peanut butter crisscross cookies
directions: Measure flour, soda, baking powder and salt into a sifter. Cream shortening and peanut butter with brown and granulated sugars until fluffy in a large bowl; beat in egg.
Sift in flour mixture, adding alternately with orange juice and blending well to make a stiff dough.
Chill until firm enough to handle.
Roll dough a teaspoon at a time into balls.
Place 3 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet; flatten, crisscross fashion with a fork. Bake 8 or 10 minutes at 375°.
Cool on racks.

title: hot punch
directions: In basket of percolator, place first 5 ingredients.
Add juices and water and let come to a boil.
Tastes good; smells wonderful.

title: fettucini alfredo
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Add cream and cheese.
Cook on low, stirring constantly until thickened.
Serve immediately over drained pasta.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Add onions sauteed.
Add mushrooms, garlic, spinach and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook until spinach loses its color.
Add cream cheese, half and half and seasonings.
Cook until cream cheese is melted.
Stir in bread crumbs and Tabasco. Grease casserole and pour in mixture.
Sprinkle with grated Gruyere cheese.
Bake uncovered for 15 minutes at 375°.

title: green  bean casserole
directions: Combine milk, soup and pepper; pour over beans.
Add 1/2 can onions and stir.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Garnish with remaining 1/2 can onions and pimentos.
Bake 5 minutes more.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken; pull off bone.
Mix soups and broth together. Heat until mixed together good.
Put a layer of chicken, then layer of stuffing, then layer of broth mixture on top.
Put second layer of each.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° or 400°.

title: easy stir-fry
directions: In medium frypan, saute sliced onion until translucent.
Add pepper, zucchini and mushrooms.
Stir and shake pan until veggies are just crisp-tender.
Sprinkle garlic salt and soy sauce.

title: chicken puffs
directions: Saute onion in 2 tablespoons margarine.
Blend in cheese.
Add salt, pepper, milk and chicken; mix well.
Separate rolls into 4 rectangles.
Seal center seam.
Place 1/4 mixture into each rectangle and pull up corners and seal closed.
Brush with remaining margarine and sprinkle with croutons.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden.

title: peter paul mounds cake
directions: Cool. Split layers and make filling.

title: cabbage and mixed pineapple
directions: Combine the cabbage, pineapple, salt, coconut and salt. Add the salad dressing gradually mixing as the salad dressing is being added.
A little more, or a little less salad dressing may
be needed.
Serves
6 to 8.
A nice appetizer before any meal.

title: sour cream chicken
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces, rinse in water, dip in flour and egg and bread crumbs.
Brown chicken in skillet on both sides.
Combine soup, sour cream, and dressing.
After chicken is browned, place in buttered casserole, pour mixture over chicken, uncovered bake at 350° for 1 hour or 1 1/2 hour.

title: marie's apple crumble cake
directions: Place sliced apples in an 8 x 8-inch greased baking pan. Sprinkle the water over top. Mix together the flour, sugar, salt, cinnamon and butter. Sprinkle over top of apples. Bake in preheated 350° oven about 30 minutes or until apples are tender and crust is brown.

title: pear relish
directions: Bring ingredients to a boil; cook 30 minutes after it starts to boil.
Remove spice bag.
Pack in hot jars with seals.

title: okra stew
directions: If using meat, cook until tender seasoned with small onion, salt and pepper.
Make sofrito (see sauces).
Add cooked stew beef.
Mix well and add okra.
Add water and 1/2 lime juice. Cover and cook on medium-high until tender (about 30 minutes).

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together, saving the oranges to add last. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes in two 9-inch pans or three 8-inch pans.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix in large mixing bowl.
Pour in greased 9-inch pie plate. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Allow to cool 10 minutes before slicing into wedges.

title: fruit salad
directions: Pour all fruit (juice, too) in large bowl.
Add dry instant pudding.
Chill overnight.

title: breakfast rolls
directions: Cream together sugar and oleo.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Stir in flour and vanilla.
Spread on greased and floured jelly roll pan.
Top with pie filling. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Spread powdered sugar icing over rolls while warm.

title: five flavor cake
directions: Cream together margarine, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Stir together the flour and baking powder; add alternately to batter with milk. Add flavorings last and beat well.

title: aunt mary's banana-chocolate chip bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream sugar and shortening.
Beat in eggs, vanilla and bananas until thoroughly blended.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture and stir just until combined. Fold in chocolate chips.
Spoon into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes or until bread tests done with a wooden pick.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes before removing to a wire rack to cool completely.
May freeze slices in bags or wrapped in foil.
Yield:
1 loaf.

title: baked sweet potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes.
Place on cookie sheet lined with foil.
Bake at 400° until soft, about 20 minutes.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix butter, sugar, peanut butter and Rice Krispies well.
Form mixture into balls about 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Melt chocolate chips and wax in a double boiler.
Dip balls into this mixture and put on wax paper to cool.

title: "dr.  ed's" barbecue rub
directions: Combine all the ingredients.
Rub generously on skinless chicken or pork ribs.
Excellent flavor.

title: pan burritos
directions: In a saucepan, combine the first 6 ingredients; simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
In a skillet, brown the beef.
Drain.
Stir in 1/3 of the sauce.

title: ugly duckling cake
directions: Combine cake mix, fruit cocktail with syrup, 1 cup of coconut and eggs in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour in oblong pan.
Sprinkle top with brown sugar.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Bring butter, granulated sugar and milk to a boil. Cook 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add rest of coconut and spread over top of cake in the pan.

title: pecan pie
directions: Add ingredients together.
Slightly beat eggs.
Pour in unbaked pie shell (9-inch).
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: green beans deluxe
directions: Stir together beans and soup and pour into ungreased casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle top with fried onions.
Bake 5 minutes more.

title: date roll
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Cool over low heat for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and let cool.
Add nuts and Rice Krispies.
Make into rolls and roll in flaked coconut, powdered sugar or nuts.

title: hamburger-tater tot casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Crumble up raw hamburger and place in bottom of pan.
Sprinkle chopped onion on top of hamburger.

title: coffee-sauced rump roast
directions: Dredge roast in flour, garlic powder, salt and pepper, then brown on all sides in large skillet in hot olive oil.
(You can skip browning, but it adds flavor and helps thicken.) Combine remaining ingredients in crock-pot.
Add browned roast, turning to coat with liquids.
Cover and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chili bean surprise
directions: Brown hamburger; add spices.
Mix in tomatoes, beans and barbecue sauce.
Let simmer for about 25 minutes.
Add cooked macaroni.

title: grandma morrison's potato dumplings(kartoffel klosse)
directions: Boil potatoes with skins on.
When tender, peel and put through ricer or mash.
Place potatoes on clean towel to dry out excessive moisture.

title: valorie's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix and bring to a boil.
Great for meat balls and Little Smokies, or use as a marinade.

title: pretzel pie crust dessert
directions: Mix pretzel crumbs, margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Put in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°; cool.
Beat 1 cup sugar with cream cheese; add Cool Whip.
Spread on crust; let stand for 4 hours or so in refrigerator.
Dissolve jello in hot water; add raspberries and let stand until it starts to set.
Pour over other mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream butter and cheese. Add other ingredients. Fill cookie press and press through the "star" design in long strips. Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes. Cut into 3 inch strips when they come from oven.

title: red enchiladas
directions: Mash and cook beef on medium, drain oil.
Add frozen chili, stir well.
(If using powdered chili, sprinkle on meat and stir well.
Add water and stir to desired consistency; more for thin sauce, less for thicker gravy sauce.)
In separate pan with hot oil covering bottom of pan, lay corn tortilla, turning over immediately to keep soft and transfer to serving plate.
Top with mixture, cheese and onions.
Repeat for 3 or 4 layers.
Heat plate in oven at 350° for five minutes, or micro for 2 minutes.
Top with egg and garnish with lettuce and tomato around edges.
Serves approximately 4.

title: dump cake(so easy, yet so delicious!)
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In layers (do not mix), spread the pie filling.
Pour the crushed pineapple on top.
Sprinkle the cake mix on top.
Chip the butter or margarine on top.
Sprinkle chopped nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for about 60 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Combine dry ingredients together and mix well.
Add 3 cups milk and vanilla.
Cook in iron skillet until thick stirring constantly.
Eat it over biscuits for breakfast.

title: spiders
directions: Melt the butterscotch chips on low heat. Remove from the heat and add the chow mein noodles and cashew nuts. Drop by teaspoons onto wax paper.

title: mountaineer slaw
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar and water and boil 3 minutes.
Cool. Add salt to shredded cabbage and let stand for 1 hour.
Add rest of ingredients to cabbage and pour cooled liquid mixture over the slaw.
Refrigerate.
Lasts 3 weeks in refrigerator.

title: party broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Simmer onion in butter until tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sour cream, sugar, vinegar, seeds and spices.
Pour this over the broccoli; top with cashews.
Serve.

title: potatoes and mushrooms
directions: Peel potatoes, cut into cubes.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Cut up pieces of margarine, mushrooms, onion and cheese.
Mix together and wrap in aluminum foil tightly.
Bake at 400° or on charcoal grill 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Blend at low speed. Beat 3 minutes
at
medium
speed
Pour into greased and floured tube
pan.
Bake
in
oven for 60 to 70 minutes. Cool upright in pan for 15 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Beat in eggs, milk, vanilla and butter thoroughly.
Fold in nuts and pour into pie shell.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes in a preheated oven at 375°.
Serve warm, either plain or with whipped cream.
Serves 6.

title: quiche for brunch
directions: Brown bacon (cut into 1 inch pieces), sausage (broken up) or ham (need not be browned).
Take everything but cheese and meat and put in blender for a few seconds.
Pour into 9-inch greased Pyrex pan.
Sprinkle meat and cheese on top and press down into batter with spoon until covered.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°; let stand 10 minutes.
Can add onion, green pepper and mushrooms, if desired.

title: amish hot potato salad
directions: In large skillet, dice bacon and pan fry.
Add onion and pepper and cook 3 minutes.
Add vinegar, salt, pepper, sugar and beaten egg.
Cook 1 minute.
Add potatoes, carrots and diced hard-cooked eggs.
Blend and serve hot.

title: split pea soup
directions: Cover peas with cold water and simmer 2 minutes.
Remove from heat, cover and let stand 1 hour.
Add bone, onion, salt, pepper and marjoram.
Bring to boil, cover, reduce heat and simmer (don't boil) 1 1/2 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Remove bone; cut off meat and shred.
Return meat to soup and add vegetables.
Cook uncovered 30 to 40 minutes.

title: best hush puppies
directions: Cook meal and water over medium heat until stiff and begins to roll into a ball (about 6 minutes).
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop from tablespoon into hot oil.
Cook until golden brown.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Cream together the shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg; beat well.
Sift together the dry ingredients and add alternately with applesauce to creamed mixture.
Add raisins and nuts.
Drop from spoon on greased cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Boil
potatoes just until tender.
Cool, peel, chop and set aside.
Fry
bacon until crisp; drain and reserve 4 tablespoons of the
fat.
Crumble
the
bacon
and
mix it with the potatoes, pimento,
onion,
celery, eggs, salt and pepper in a 2-quart casserole.

title: appalachian favorite pancakes
directions: Beat egg.
Add buttermilk and oil and stir.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add dry ingredients to wet ingredients.
Stir until semi-smooth (still some lumps).
Heat electric skillet to 350°.
Add oil (about 4 tablespoons or 1/4 cup).

title: congo bars for large crowd
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheet, large size.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together in one bowl.
Cream butter, slowly adding brown sugar and eggs.
Mix with flour mixture until creamy.
Add chocolate chips.
Place in cookie sheet.
Bake for 35 minutes until brown.
Cool.
Cut into 48 bars.
Can freeze bars after cool.
Also could add M&M's.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together all ingredients except 1/3 of Cool Whip.
After blended well, stir in remaining Cool Whip and pour into baked pie shell and chill.

title: sweet 'n sour carrot salad
directions: Mix carrots, pepper and onion.
Heat rest of ingredients and pour over carrot mixture.
Chill 24 hours.

title: elizabeth's cole slaw
directions: Bring to a boil 1 teaspoon sugar, salt, dry mustard, celery seed, peanut oil and vinegar.
Pour over cabbage, onion and sugar mixture.
Let stand for 4 hours before serving.
Will be good for 4 or 5 days.

title: pork roast with kraut
directions: Place the roast in deep baking pan and cover with salt, pepper and kraut.
Cover and bake at 350° for 3 hours.
Remove top of roaster for last 30 minutes of baking.
Slice or shred pork before serving.

title: raw fries
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons margarine in heavy skillet.
Arrange potatoes in 3 layers.
Sprinkle each layer with salt and pepper. Dot top with 2 tablespoons margarine.
Cover; cook over medium heat for 20 minutes.
Uncover, turn and cook until potatoes are brown.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: toffee
directions: Butter square pan (9 x 9 x 2-inches).
Spread pecans in pan. Heat sugar and butter to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil over medium heat, stirring constantly, for 7 minutes.
Immediately spread mixture evenly over nuts in pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over hot mixture; place foil over pan so chocolate will melt. Spread chocolate evenly over candy.

title: creamy buttermilk dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender or food processor; cover and process until smooth.
Cover and refrigerate at least an hour before serving.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Press into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 400° for about 45 minutes to an hour.

title: oatmeal crunchies
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add brown sugar, shortening, egg and vanilla; beat well.
Stir in oats and nuts.
Form dough into small balls and dip tops in a little additional sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: corn shuffle
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, combine both cans of corn and muffin mix.
Melt margarine and add with sour cream to mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 350 for exactly 1 hour.

title: duck feet soup
directions: Butcher ducks; reserve feet.
Soak feet in salt water for 2 days to clean off all excess deposits.
Boil 4 quarts of water; add potatoes, carrots and onion and simmer until onion is tender. Add feet and simmer 1 more hour.

title: pineapple dressing
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs and pineapple.
Fold in bread cubes.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Serve with baked ham or alone.

title: rutabagas
directions: Peel and cube the rutabagas.
Boil until tender; drain. Add the butter and sugar.
Beat with a mixer until mashed. Season to taste.

title: cinnamon bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg; continue beating.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Add alternately with flour.
Mix until blended.
In a well-greased loaf pan, pour half the batter in, then sprinkle with half the sugar-cinnamon mixture. Repeat with remaining batter and cinnamon layers.
Swirl through batter with knife to bottom of pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix all ingredients. Cover and refrigerate for 1 to 2 hours before serving. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook fryer with seasonings (salt, pepper, parsley flakes, chives and bay leaves).
When chicken is tender, remove from bones and cut up.
Saute bell pepper, onion and celery.
Add chicken, along with 2 cans of mushroom soup, pimentos and mushrooms.
Cook spaghetti in broth with added water.
Mix all together in large baking dish with 1 cup cheese.
Cover with more cheese.
Heat in a 350° oven.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Lightly grease 10-inch pie plate.
Cook ground beef and onion until brown; drain.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Spread into pie plate and sprinkle with cheese.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth (15 seconds in blender on high speed).
Pour into pie plate.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: picante sauce
directions: Mix all together and cook approximately 3 hours.
Cold pack for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: grandpa's favorite cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Place 3 tablespoons of vegetable oil in an 8 or 9-inch cast-iron skillet and preheat skillet while preparing ingredients.
Crack eggs into large mixing bowl and beat slightly; add buttermilk, 1/4 cup vegetable oil and salsa and mix well by hand.
Add dry ingredients and stir until smooth.
Pour into hot skillet and bake for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate-syrup brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Spread in a buttered 9-inch pan.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for about 40 minutes.

title: dee's bar-b-que shrimp
directions: Mix pepper, lemon juice, garlic, dressing and butter on top of room temperature shrimp.
Bake at 350 to 400 degrees for about 20 minutes (no longer).

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken; tear off meat.
Cook rice in the chicken broth substituting for water.
Will make two 9 x 11-inch casseroles. Mix 1/2 of chicken, rice, soups and onions; pour in casserole dishes.
Place several pats of butter on top and season.
Bake at 400° for about 30 minutes.

title: homemade play dough
directions: In a saucepan, mix all of the ingredients.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes, stirring constantly, until it forms a big ball.
Cool and store in airtight containers.
Keep in refrigerator for longer use.

title: pistachio sheet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth with electric mixer.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan or two 8 x 8-inch pans.
Sprinkle the nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
While cake is baking, blend the following together for topping.

title: sandy's appetizer
directions: Mix together and place in a small baking dish or pie plate. Sprinkle with paprika and bake 25 minutes at 325°.
Serve on crackers.
Good on Triscuits.

title: frozen lemon custard
directions: Beat milk until stiff; add 1 cup sugar.
Beat until stiff. Add lemon juice and rind.
Pour over vanilla wafer crumbs. Freeze.
Makes 12 servings.

title: creole red beans and rice
directions: Combine all ingredients except rice in a large kettle with 8 quarts of water.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 4 to 6 hours, stirring occasionally.
Mash some of the red beans on side of kettle when tender.
Cook rice according to package directions. Serve beans over white rice.
Serve with tossed green salad, hot French bread and butter and red wine and fruited jello for dessert.

title: pralines
directions: Melt 1 1/2 cups sugar in a large saucepan.
At the same time, in another pan, cook the 3 cups sugar, milk and butter.
(Do not boil.)
When sugar has melted, turn down heat and pour this sugar mixture into the melted sugar in the large pan.
Stir hard and fast.
Continue cooking until it forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water.
Add pecans.
Stir well.
Drop by spoon onto wax paper.

title: cranberry tea
directions: Boil cranberries and water together with the cloves and cinnamon.
Boil for 10 minutes.
Let juice cool.
Strain by pressing through a sieve to remove cranberry seeds.
Add frozen lemonade and orange juice concentrates.
Mix all together.
Can be stored in the refrigerator for up to a month or freeze in 1 cup containers.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix partially cooked noodles with all other ingredients, except cheese.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake in 325° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: alphabet soup
directions: Place roast in large pan.
Cover with water and salt a little. When it begins to start boiling, spoon scum from top.
Continue to simmer meat for 1 1/2 hours.
Cover pan loosely so steam can escape.
Add tomatoes, water, onion, carrots, celery parts, parsley, broth and water.
Cook for another hour or until meat is tender.
Remove meat and carrots.
Strain broth.
Add cooked alphabets and meat, broken up.

title: moroccan pasta
directions: Cook pasta according to package. In large saucepan over medium heat, cook red pepper, onion, zucchini, salt and curry in hot oil for 3 minutes or until crisp-tender. Stir in broth. Bring to boil; boil for 1 minute or until slightly thickened. Drain pasta and add vegetable mixture with raisins.

title: taco soup
directions: In large Dutch oven, brown beef and onion.
Drain fat.
Add all ingredients and bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, at least 30 minutes.
Serve with shredded cheese and tortilla chips.

title: easy-bake potatoes
directions: Scrub and dry potatoes and cut into 2 1/2-inch chunks. Arrange in single layer in baking pan.
Melt butter with garlic in it.
Remove garlic and drizzle butter over potatoes.
Season and cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Remove cover and bake 20 minutes longer.

title: thai-style cucumber salad
directions: Dissolve sugar in boiling water in a small bowl.
Add vinegar; cover and chill 2 hours.

title: preachers casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter in deepest frying pan you have.
Brown hamburger meat in sauteed mixture.
Add mushroom soup, tomato soup and 3/4 of chow mein noodles.
Pour all in a large casserole.
Sprinkle remaining chow mein noodles on top and bake at 350° to 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: german potato salad (hot)
directions: Peel potatoes and slice very thin.
Heat all other ingredients in a 2-quart kettle.
Add potatoes and simmer until liquid is almost gone.

title: miss penny's strawberry pie
directions: Mix cheese, sugar and Cool Whip. Add chopped berries.
Pour into a graham crust.
Freeze. When ready to serve, let thaw for a few minutes.

title: crunchy apple rice salad
directions: Combine rices, water, oil and cinnamon in medium size saucepan over medium heat.
Cook until water is absorbed, 15 to 20 minutes. Turn off heat and cover for 5 minutes.
Put rice mixture in large salad bowl and toss in apples, parsley and currants.
Serve hot or cold.
Yield:
2 servings.
Heart healthy and low-fat.

title: hash brown potato melt
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat 1 tablespoon of the oil in 12-inch oven-proof skillet over moderate heat for 1 minute.
Add onion and green pepper and saute, stirring occasionally, for 5 minutes. Stir in potatoes and remaining oil, then flatten the mixture to a uniform thickness.
Reduce heat and cook, uncovered, without stirring, for 5 minutes.
Mix milk, cheese, salt and pepper in small bowl; pour over potato mixture and transfer to oven.
Bake uncovered for 20 to 25 minutes or until potatoes are tender, bubbling and tipped with brown.
Serves 4.

title: baked cheese grits
directions: Cook grits according to directions on box.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cornbread dinner
directions: Fry sausage with onion. Add remaining ingredients. Mix all together and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: white christmas pie
directions: In saucepan, mix together the sugar, flour, gelatin and salt. Stir in milk. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, just until mixture boils. Place pan in a bowl of ice and water or refrigerate, stirring occasionally, until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from a spoon.
Stir in vanilla and almond extract. In a bowl, beat egg whites and cream of tartar until foamy. Beat in 1/2 cup sugar, one tablespoon at a time. Continue beating until stiff and glossy.
Do not underbeat.
Fold gelatin mixture into meringue. Beat whipping cream in chilled bowl until stiff.
Fold whipping cream and coconut into meringue.
Mound into pie shell. Refrigerate until set, at least 2 hours.

title: sausage skillet
directions: Saute sausage until brown.
Remove from skillet and pour off all but 2 tablespoons fat.
Saute onion in fat until yellow; add cabbage, sprinkle with water and cook.
Return sausage to onion and cabbage mixture.
Add rice.
Heat for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Blend soup, milk and pepper.
In 1 1/2-quart casserole dish alternate in layers potatoes, onions and sauce.
Dot top with 1 tablespoon butter.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes or until done.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: hush puppies
directions: In mixing bowl, stir together egg, buttermilk, onion and 1/4 cup water; set aside.
In large mixing bowl, combine cornmeal, flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and 1 teaspoon salt.
Add egg mixture to cornmeal mixture; stir just until moistened.
Drop batter by tablespoonfuls into deep fat (375°).
Fry about 2 minutes or until golden brown, turning once.
Drain on paper towel.
Serve hot with butter or margarine if desired. Makes 24.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook ground chuck in medium skillet over medium heat until browned.
Drain and pat dry with paper towels.
Wipe skillet with a paper towel.
Return meat to skillet and stir in tomatoes, water, garlic and Italian herb seasoning.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Cook noodles according to package directions, omitting salt and fat.
Drain well and set aside.
Cook spinach according to directions, omitting salt and fat.
Drain well and squeeze moisture from spinach.
Combine spinach and next 4 ingredients, stirring until well combined.
Set mixture aside.

title: zebra brownies
directions: Make brownie mix according to directions; set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients in a bowl; set aside.
Spray Pam on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add 1/2 of the mixed brownie batter.
Pour all of the cream cheese filling and smooth over, then add remaining brownie mixture.
Cut through mixture with a knife, turn pan and cut through again several times.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and refrigerate.
Cut into squares.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add oil, water and pumpkin pie mix.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Makes 3 small or 1 large loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pans.

title: cherry nut cookies
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar.
Beat in egg and vanilla until smooth.
Blend in flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir in walnuts and cherries.
Shape the dough into a roll about 14 inches long.
Wrap in foil or plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cut squash into 1/4-inch slices and boil in water for ten minutes; drain well.
Melt margarine in 9 x 13 baking dish.
Crush crackers into crumbs and mix with melted margarine.
Add squash and remaining ingredients and mix well.
Cover dish with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove foil and sprinkle with cheese and return to oven for 10 minutes to melt cheese.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Drain.
Combine soup, eggs, cheese and mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Add broccoli and pour into buttered casserole.
Bake in 350° oven until set (approximately 45 minutes).
Casserole is done when knife comes out clean after inserting.
Makes 4 servings.

title: broccoli brunch
directions: Cut round circles of bread and remove crust.
Put crust scraps in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine rest of ingredients and pour on top.
Refrigerate at least 6 hours (can be made a night ahead of time).
Bake uncovered 1 hour at 350°.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt margarine and add peanut butter. In large bowl (I use a large wash pan), mix Rice Krispies with powdered sugar.
Pour the peanut butter and margarine over the Rice Krispies mixture. Mix with hands and make into balls.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix and bake in casserole for 1 hour at 325°.
