title: philippine lumpias
directions: Saute garlic, onions, and meat in as little vegetable oil as possible, until onions become transparent. Add soy sauce and simmer for about 15 minutes. Add all the vegetables and simmer for another 10 minutes. Drain and cool for about one hour.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Slice all vegetables.
Mix together sour cream and Wish-Bone. Toss with vegetables.
Place in refrigerator and let marinate at least 5 hours.

title: potatoes on the grill
directions: Peel and slice potatoes about 1/4-inch thick.
Onion about the same, if desired.
Line foil pan with large pieces of foil.
Spray with Pam.
Layer potatoes and onion with butter, salt, pepper and cheese in foil pan.
Add about 1/2 or 3/4 cup milk.
Cover with foil.
Cook on medium heat for about 30 to 45 minutes or until tender.

title: creamy fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruit.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and sugar. Pour over fruit.
Add marshmallows and nuts.
Mix well.
Chill.

title: potato chip en casserole
directions: Fry pimento, onions and pepper until light brown in butter. Combine ingredients, place in buttered casserole and crush a few chips on top.
Cook 1/2 hour in moderate oven (350°).

title: pineapple cake
directions: Cook cake layers and cool.
Mix together sour cream and sugar. Let set for 5 minutes or until no longer grainy.
Add drained pineapple, then stir in Cool Whip.
Use pineapple juice to pour over cake layers.
(I cut my layers to make 4 layers.)
Frost cake when cool and refrigerate.

title: sweet & sour chicken nuggets
directions: Drain the pineapple and reserve juice. Set aside. In a skillet, saute green pepper and onion in oil until crisp-tender. Remove and keep warm. Add broth, syrup, vinegar and soy sauce to the skillet. Bring to a boil.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients together. Cut into 1/2 cup lard and 2/3 cup milk.
Roll on wax paper with little flour.
Cut with glass. Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: marinated cucumber salad
directions: Combine first four ingredients in large shallow dish.
Set aside.
Combine next 6 ingredients, mixing well; pour over vegetables, tossing.
Cover and chill 8 to 10 hours.
Drain and serve in bowl lined with lettuce leaves.
Makes 6 servings.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Buy round loaf of bread.
Take out all the soft bread.
Use this to dip with.
Put the dip into the hollowed out loaf (bowl) when ready to serve.

title: roast garlic
directions: With point end up, cut off dry leaves to expose tips of individual cloves.
Put in ovenproof dish, cut side up.
Dot with butter.
Drizzle olive oil over heads.
Sprinkle with dried thyme and pepper.
Cover and bake for 30 minutes at 275°.
Uncover and bake for 1 1/2 hours basting every 15 to 20 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Wash, peel and slice apples.
Arrange in greased 8-inch pan.
Top with crumb mixture made of flour, sugar, baking powder and egg.
Pour butter over all.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake 40 minutes.

title: pescado a la naranja(fish in orange juice)
directions: Thaw frozen fish.
Arrange fish in a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
In a small skillet, cook onion and garlic in oil until onion is tender, but not brown.
Stir in cilantro or parsley, salt and pepper.
Spread mixture over fish.

title: "cool-ossal"(raised doughnuts)
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water; add 1 teaspoon sugar.
Scald milk; add butter, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Add flour to make a soft, but not sticky dough.
Roll out immediately on a floured cloth 1/2-inch thick.
Cut in 1 x 3-inch strips.
Let rise until light.
Fry in deep fat, moderate heat.
Roll in granulated sugar while warm.

title: tomatoes vinaigrette
directions: Combine all ingredients except greens.
Chill several hours or overnight, stirring occasionally.
Arrange greens on salad plates. Spoon tomatoes over greens.
You may want to pour a little of the liquid over the greens as well.
Or, these tomatoes can be served without greens as a side dish.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain.
Return pasta to the hot kettle or Dutch oven.
Add Parmesan cheese, light cream and margarine.
Toss gently until pasta is well coated. Sprinkle with pepper.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 main dish servings.

title: tender crust dinner rolls
directions: Soak yeast in 1/4 cup warm water for 5 minutes.
Combine milk, sugar and salt; stir.
Beat in butter, eggs, 1 cup flour and softened yeast mixture with rotary beater until smooth.
Add remaining flour until dough leaves sides of bowl.
Knead until smooth and elastic and no longer sticky.
Place in greased bowl; grease top of dough.
Cover with waxed paper; let rise in warm place (80° to 85°) until double (1 to 1 1/2 hours).
Punch down. Form into rolls of desired shape.
Place on greased baking or muffin pans.
Let rise until light and doubled (30 to 40 minutes). Bake at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: dolores waldrum's minted lemonade *
directions: Bring to a boil
the
water
and sugar; boil 5 minutes. Pour mixture over a
handful of crushed mint.
Add lemon juice and orange juice.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Strain to remove mint.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Put in saucepan the sugar, milk and shortening and bring to a full rolling boil.
Remove from heat and add rolled oats, cocoa, vanilla and nutmeats or coconut.
Drop spoonfuls on wax paper.
Let set.

title: tomato soup dip
directions: Place the first 4 ingredients in a saucepan; melt over low heat.
Stir; cool.
Add rest of the ingredients; mix well.
Pour into containers; will set like aspic.
I like to pour dip into prepared cabbages and peppers.
Cover with wrap; refrigerate overnight.
Tastes great served with crackers and vegetable flowerets.
Will serve large groups.

title: jello cookies
directions: Beat together the first 4 ingredients.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Roll into balls; flatten with glass dipped in sugar. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix eggs and sugar. Add soda to buttermilk. Add to sugar and eggs. Add vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients.
Stir into wet mixture. Add prunes.
Pour into greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Pour sauce over while cake is hot in pan.

title: seven-up salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Add marshmallows and cheese; stir to partly dissolve.
Add pineapple, Seven-Up and nuts.
Chill until firm.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Work butter until creamy.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Beat well. Add flour and salt; mix to a smooth dough.
Stir in nuts.
Chill for several hours or overnight.
Heat oven to 350°.
Break off bits of dough and shape into 1-inch balls.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes.
While warm, roll in confectioners sugar.
When cooled, roll again in sugar.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Bring syrup and sugar to boil.
Remove from stove and add peanut butter, corn flakes and salt.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper and cool in refrigerator for a couple of hours.

title: pedialyte-homestyle
directions: Blend and stir until dissolved.
Keep refrigerated.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together cream cheese, Cheddar cheese, pimentos, seasoned salt and onions.
Form into ball and roll into pecans.
Cover with plastic wrap and place in refrigerator until serving.
Serve with any type of crackers.

title: mary kissinger's scalloped corn
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour into a buttered pan.
Dot generously with butter.
Bake at 350° until firm.
Takes about 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: strawberry ice cream
directions: Use desired amount of crushed fruit (strawberries or peaches). Pour mixture into freezer.
Add milk to fill line in gallon ice cream freezer.

title: aunt maggie's chocolate cake
directions: Cream 1 stick of the butter, Crisco and 1 cup sugar.
Add cocoa paste.
Sift flour and soda together; add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Add eggs and vanilla last; beat well.
Bake in 3 (9-inch) layers at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: herb butter
directions: Blend until light and fluffy.

title: cinnamon french toast
directions: Mix eggs and milk in medium size bowl with wire whisk.
Dip cinnamon bread in batter with fork.
Cook on stove until crisp and brown or to your liking.

title: buttermilk sauce
directions: Blend together sugar and butter.
Add buttermilk, light corn syrup and baking soda.
Cook to a full rolling boil.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Pour over carrot or applesauce cake while hot.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Place dry soup in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add 1 cup water and rice.
Stir to mix soup, water and rice.
Place pieces of chicken over rice mixture.
Salt and pepper chicken to taste. Pour cream soup over all, add remaining water.
Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove foil and bake 1/2 hour more.

title: fruit dip
directions: Whip together in a medium bowl.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: pork chop potato bake
directions: Brown chops.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt; set aside.
Combine soup, milk, sour cream, pepper and salt.
Stir in potatoes, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can onions.
Spoon into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with chops.
Bake covered at 350° for 40 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake uncovered 5 minutes longer.

title: miracle cobbler
directions: Melt 1 cube of butter/margarine in bottom of a cake pan.
Add flour, sugar, milk and baking powder.
Add 1 can of peaches with liquid and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: sweet potato puff
directions: Boil the sweet potatoes with their skins on.
Then peel the skins off.
Mix together the brown sugar, butter and vanilla. Mash the sweet potatoes and add to brown sugar mixture.
Add tapioca to thicken if too thin.
Roll large marshmallows in mixture to coat, then roll in unsweetened coconut and place in a buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° until coconut is brown.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix ingredients; pour into freezer.
Finish filling it with homogenized milk.

title: salad nicoise
directions: Boil potatoes until tender; cool.
Add beans to the same water; boil until crisp-tender, about 7 minutes.
Drain and cool under water.
Arrange potatoes, beans, olives, eggs and tomato on a large platter.
Spoon tuna in center.
Whisk vinegar, mustard, salt and pepper to taste in a small bowl.
Gradually pour in oil, whisking until emulsified.
Whisk in parsley.
Drizzle over salad.

title: "bug tops"
directions: Fry a piece of bologna in skillet (do not cut bologna).
Let it curl up.
Spoon in already creamed potatoes.
Top with grated cheese.

title: ground meat and rice
directions: Fry ground meat, with salt and pepper to taste, in cooking oil until it changes color.
Add chopped onion, chopped celery and green bell pepper, chopped.
Add a little water.
Cover and cook until vegetables are tender.
Prepare rice.
Spread rice over the meat mixture.
Cover and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add grated cheese on top.
Return to oven with lid on and turn oven off until cheese melts.

title: peanut butter fudge(sugar-free)
directions: Mix all together and roll into a roll.
Roll in Grape-Nuts cereal and freeze.
It tastes like Baby Ruth.

title: old fashioned dark fruit cake
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and eggs. Sift together flour, salt, cinnamon, cloves and allspice. Mix together in a dish pan the cherries, pineapple, raisins, fruit cake mix, chopped dates and pecans. Add the creamed mixture alternately with flour mixture and 1 1/2 cups orange juice. Pour over fruit and mix well (by hand). Divide into 2 well-greased and floured tube pans. Bake at 250° for approximately 2 hours. After 1 hour of baking, cakes can be decorated on top.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown sausage, drain and crumble. Separate crescent rolls.
Place on ungreased pizza pan and press down to cover bottom of pan.
Layer meat, potatoes and Cheddar cheese.

title: chocolate toffee crescent bars
directions: Press rolls into lipped cookie sheet.
Melt margarine.
Slowly add brown sugar and vanilla; boil for 1 minute.
Pour over dough. Top with pecans.
Bake at 375° for 14 to 18 minutes.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Swirl cool.
Cut into bars.

title: sausage with lima beans and tomatoes
directions: Brown sausage.
Pour off grease.
Add tomatoes (broken up). Add thyme, bay leaf and bouillon cube.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Add lima beans.
Heat through.
Serves 4.

title: aunt leedee's carrot medley
directions: Clean and cut carrots lengthwise into 3-inch pieces.
Boil until tender.
Wash and slice mushrooms and saute in butter or oil.
Add chibolini to the mushrooms and cook until tender.
Drain carrots and add to the mushroom and chibolini mixture.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Remove to serving dish.
Serves 8.

title: divinity candy
directions: Cook sugar, salt and water to soft ball stage.
Pour over Marshmallow Creme and vanilla.
Beat and drop on wax paper.
Nut or coconut may be added.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Melt butter in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle crushed graham crackers over.
Add condensed milk, chocolate chips and nuts. Press.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: impossible turkey pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Grease a 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate. Sprinkle turkey, mushrooms, onions, salt and cheese in pie plate. Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, about 1 minute, with hand beater or 15 seconds in blender on high.
Pour mixture into pie plate.
Bake at 400° until knife comes out clean from the center. Cool 5 minutes, cut wedges and serve with salad.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together and add salt and pepper to taste.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Stir real good at 1/2 hour of baking; finish baking the other 1/2 hour.

title: ann's vanishing oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Beat together butter and sugars until creamy. Add eggs and vanilla. Beat well. Add flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt. Mix well. Stir in oatmeal, raisins and/or nuts. Mix well. Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown. Cool on cookie sheet for 1 minute, then move to a cooling rack. Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: sugared pecans
directions: Melt margarine.
Stir
in
sugar and spices.
Mix well. Pour over nuts
in
large
flat	pan and mix to coat.
Bake at 275° for 30 minutes.
Stir every 10 minutes.
Store in tightly covered tin.

title: delicious apple cake
directions: Mix apples and sugar together and let stand for 1 hour.
In same bowl add flour, soda, salt, oil, nuts and eggs (one at a time).
Mix well and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until tests done.
I bake in large loaf pan and requires no icing. Freezes beautifully.
I cut in required pieces and freeze.
When thawed is same as freshly baked.
Always thaw in the wrappings until nice and soft.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 13 x 9-inch pan, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over margarine; pour Eagle Brand milk over crumbs.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Press down.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cut.

title: betty jo's barbecue or aka sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add rest of the ingredients; simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve on rolls or hamburger buns.

title: denver sandwiches
directions: Partially fry diced bacon.
Add minced onion; cook until tender.
Mix eggs with milk and seasonings.
Pour over bacon and onion.
Fry on one side until brown.
Turn, fry on other side, cut into six pieces.
Butter slices of bread.
Put egg filling on six slices of bread; cover with the other six slices.
Makes six sandwiches.

title: onion rings
directions: Peel and cut onion into 1/4 inch slices.
Separate slices and place in pan.
Cover onions with milk and marinate for 1/2 hour. Dip in slated flour.
Fry in hot fat until golden brown.
Serve hot.

title: quick pickled beets
directions: Drain beets and save 1 cup of juice.
Bring sugar, vinegar and spices if used, to a boil.
Cut up beets and add to liquid, bring to a boil again.
Remove from heat.
Store in refrigertor.
Can be eaten after one day.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Cut into bite size pieces.
Place broccoli in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with water chestnuts and onion soup mix.
Pour butter over and sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: fudge muffins
directions: Melt butter and chocolate in large pan.
Beat in sugar, salt and flour.
Add eggs, one at a time, stirring in but not beating. Add vanilla and nuts.
Fill muffin tins slightly over half full. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: williamsburg sally lunn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350° for 10 minutes before Sally Lunn is ready to be baked.
Grease a 10-inch tube cake pan or Bundt pan. Heat the milk, shortening and 1/4 cup water until very warm, about 120°.
Shortening does not need to melt.
Blend 1 1/3 cups flour, the sugar, salt and dry yeast in a large mixing bowl.
Blend warm liquids into flour mixture.
Beat with an electric mixer at medium speed about 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Gradually add 2/3 cup of remaining flour and eggs and beat at high speed 2 minutes.
Add remaining flour and mix well.
Batter will be thick but not stiff.
Cover and let rise in warm, draft-free place (about 85°)
until double in bulk, about 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: broccoli topped tuna bake
directions: Prepare Creamettes elbow macaroni according to package directions.
Drain.
Reserve 1/2 cup Cheez Whiz.
In large bowl, combine Campbell's cream of mushroom soup, milk and remaining Cheez Whiz; stir in macaroni, tuna and pepper.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake in 375° oven for 25 minutes; stir.
Arrange broccoli on top of macaroni mixture.
Top with reserved Cheez Whiz. Bake 5 minutes or until hot.
Makes 8 servings.

title: classic lasagne
directions: In large heavy pan, lightly brown beef and onion in oil.
Add tomatoes, paste, water, salt, sugar, garlic powder, pepper and oregano.
Simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally, about 30 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook lasagne as directed, drain.
In 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan, spread about 1 cup sauce, then alternate layers of noodles, sauce, Ricotta, Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese, ending with sauce, Mozzarella and Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes until lightly browned and bubbling.
Allow to stand for 15 minutes.
Cut in squares to serve.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Mix oleo, sugar and Crisco.
Sift flour and baking powder; separately cream, oleo, sugar and Crisco with 5 eggs, added one at a time.
Add milk and flavoring, beating as you go, then add dry ingredients.
Add coconut.
Bake at 325° in tube pan for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cranberry-banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a medium bowl, blend butter and sugar. Add beaten egg and beat until smooth. Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and soda. Add to creamed mixture all at once. Mix with spoon until flour is absorbed. Fold in bananas, cranberries and walnuts. Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake 65 to 70 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean. Cool slightly. Remove from pan. Can be frozen up to 2 months.

title: delicious potato pancakes
directions: Coarsely shred potatoes and onions into a large bowl with cold water.
In colander, drain.
Wrap in towel; squeeze to remove water.
In same bowl, beat eggs.
Add potatoes, onions, flour, salt, pepper and nutmeg; mix well.
Put salad oil in a large skillet over medium heat until hot.
Drop mixture by large spoonfuls; flatten with pancake turner.
Cook until golden brown, turn over and brown other side.

title: beef stew
directions: Cook steak in pan until tender.
Pour all ingredients into pot with steak until vegetables are tender.
Thicken with corn starch or flour.

title: italian beef
directions: I like to use and cook this wrapped in aluminum foil or a cooking bag.

title: barbecue pork
directions: Place pork roast in crock-pot or slow cooker.
Cover and cook on low approximately 8 hours until done.
Pour out liquid.
Allow roast to cool and remove all visible fat.
Tear or cut roast into strips.
Put back in crock-pot with the sauce and cook until hot.

title: yam sunbursts
directions: Cut oranges into halves; squeeze, reserving 1/4 cup juice. Carefully remove pulp from orange shells.
Make scalloped design on edges of orange shells, using small end of melon baller.

title: honey glazed ham
directions: Score the ham, making diamond shapes 1/2-inch deep. Place on rack in a well-greased foil roasting pan. Add water to pan. In a small bowl, combine the honey, brown sugar, cloves and mustard. Pour over ham. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 2 hours, basting with pan juices. Add additional water to pan if necessary.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix margarine, flour and pecans with fork and press in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°. Cool. Combine sugar, cream cheese and 1 cup Cool Whip in a bowl; spread over crust. Mix pudding and milk. Allow to set. Spread over cheese layer. Top with remaining Cool Whip. (Pecans may be sprinkled over the top.) Refrigerate at least a few hours.

title: copper penny carrots
directions: Cook carrots in boiling water until just tender, not mushy. Drain. Place carrots in a large bowl with the onion and green pepper.
In a saucepan mix together the soup, sugar, salad oil, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, celery or caraway seed, mustard, salt and pepper to taste.
Heat until sugar is dissolved and all is smooth.
Pour the hot mixture over the carrot mixture in the bowl.
Cover well and refrigerate at least 12 hours.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Cut crescent roll into three pieces.
Place wiener in crescent roll and roll crescent around the wiener.
Bake until golden brown.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Melt the chocolate bars in the microwave for about 1 minute. Fold melted chocolate into Cool Whip; do not beat or blend it completely together!
You should still be able to see spots of just chocolate and just Cool Whip so that there will be pieces of chocolate in it.
Pour into pre-baked pie shell and freeze for at least 4 to 5 hours.

title: angel food frosting
directions: Cook flour and milk until it resembles thick paste.
Cool. Add remaining ingredients and beat at high speed until fluffy, like whipped cream.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all and chill for 1 hour.

title: crunchy brownie bars
directions: Combine flour, soda and salt; stir in oats and brown sugar. Add margarine and pat mixture in bottom of ungreased 11 x 7-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
While bottom is baking, prepare brownie mix.
Spread batter over crunchy layer.
Return to oven and bake until brownies are done, approximately 40 minutes. Frost when brownies are cool.

title: skewered beef and chicken
directions: Trim fat from steak and chicken; cut into 2-inch cubes.
Shake remaining ingredients in covered container.
Pour over meat; cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Turn several times. Thread meat on skewer with choice of vegetables (i.e. cherry tomatoes, mushrooms or onions).
Grill 15 to 20 minutes for medium.

title: persimmon pudding(heritage recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degree.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13 inch baking dish.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Turn temperature down to 325 degrees and bake for 45 minutes.

title: cole slaw
directions: Beat the mustard, celery seed, sugar, vinegar, pepper, salt and evaporated milk together.
Mix with grated cabbage and apple.

title: cherry nut cake
directions: Combine cream cheese, margarine, sugar and vanilla, mixing at medium speed on electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs one at a time, mixing well after each.
Sift together 2 cups flour and baking powder.
Gradually add to cream cheese mixture; mix well. Toss remaining flour with cherries and pecans.
Fold into batter. Grease 10-inch tube or fluted tube pan or 9-inch spring-form pan with ring insert.
Sprinkle with finely chopped pecans.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool.
Glaze with combined powdered sugar and milk.
Garnish with additional pecan halves and maraschino cherry halves, if desired.

title: yvonne's lime jelled salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup hot water.
Save juice from drained pineapple.
If, when ready to use the juice, it doesn't quite come to a full cup, add a little water to make up the difference. While Jell-O is cooling, mix remaining ingredients thoroughly.
Add to Jell-O mix; pour into mold.
Serves 10.

title: coo-cae dutch spice bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add milk and make a smooth batter.
Pour into greased loaf pan(s) until batter reaches 2/3 of the way up the side of the pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted in middle of bread comes out clean.
(No fat and easy!)

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts and cut up in small pieces. Mix cream chicken soup and sour cream in with chicken. Put in a casserole dish. Put crushed
Ritz crackers in with 1 stick melted butter and pour on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: wild rice with mushrooms and almonds
directions: Mix all ingredients, except stock, and saute in heavy frying pan until rice turns yellowish, stirring frequently.
Add stock and bake in tightly covered casserole for 2 hours at 325°.

title: herbed tomatoes
directions: Place sliced tomatoes in a large flat serving dish.
Mix the remaining ingredients together and pour over tomatoes.
Cover and refrigerate at least 6 hours.

title: tuna tree
directions: Mix together.
Serve in tree-shaped pan.
Decorate with cherry tomatoes, parsley and lemon star.
Makes a great holiday party appetizer.
Serve on crackers.

title: old settler's beans
directions: Brown and drain ground chuck and onion. Mix all ingredients together. Cook in crock pot on low 6 to 8 hours. Serve with corn bread or corn chips.

title: lime punch
directions: Keep all ingredients cold until ready to make.
Mix all ingredients together.
Sherbet will float.
Garnish unmelted sherbet with a lemon and parsley.

title: egg rolls (shrimp)
directions: Mix the above together.
Add 1 teaspoon mixture to each egg roll wrapper.
Fry in oil until lightly brown.

title: salmon stew
directions: Drain, skin and debone salmon (only use pink meat of salmon). In a large saucepan saute diced onion in melted margarine until tender.
Stir in salmon and milk.
Heat over medium heat until hot.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Spread rolls into jelly roll pan.
Bake according to directions on package.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and Hidden Valley mix.
Spread over baked rolls.
Chop vegetables.
Sprinkle over top of cream cheese mixture.
(Use broccoli, cauliflower, green pepper, onion and carrots.)
Sprinkle 8 ounce package Cheddar cheese over top.
Cut into squares.
Refrigerate.

title: bernice's best noodle pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles as package directs. Drain.
Add butter.
Beat eggs well.
Gradually add sugar; then vanilla, raisins and cinnamon.
Mix with noodles.
Bake in buttered casserole, covered, about 40 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Serve hot or cold.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups of sugar, cornstarch, flour and salt in medium saucepan.
Gradually stir in boiling water.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil and is thick and clear.
Stir a little of this hot mixture into the beaten egg yolks.
Return to saucepan; cook and stir for 2 minutes longer. Remove from heat.
Add butter, lemon peel and lemon juice.
Pour into cooled, baked 9-inch pie shell.

title: peanut butter & corn flakes
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil in a small size saucepan. Add peanut butter and mix well.
Stir in corn flakes.
Drop with a spoon onto wax paper or dump into a cake pan.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs.
Beat well.
Add zucchini and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Blend well and add nuts.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans (2 pans).
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: calico bean pot
directions: Cook bacon in quart casserole on high 6 to 7 minutes or until crisp.
Remove bacon.
Place onion in bacon pot and cook 2 to 3 minutes on High.
Add remaining ingredients and mix lightly.
Cook on High 12 to 15 minutes.

title: mexican spoon bread
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients well. Sprinkle chilies and half of cheese into mix. Pour into greased baking dish and sprinkle the rest of the cheese on top. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes. Cool 10 minutes and cut into squares.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Put all together in one bowl and mix.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: south of the border pizza
directions: Roll dough and place on a well greased pizza pan sprinkled with corn meal.
Bake at 350° until browned.
Mix hamburger meat, onions, salsa and green chilies.
Spread over crust and top with cheese.
Bake until cheese is melted.
Top with lettuce and tomato.

title: party potato casserole
directions: Place in a 1-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle paprika on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cover with foil until last 10 minutes.
This freezes well.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Melt butter; saute onion on low heat.
Beat flour into mixture.
Add salt and pepper.
Add milk, stirring constantly until smooth.
Add cheese chunks; stir until smooth.
Place drained carrots in a large, glass baking bowl.
Pour cheese mixture over carrots and stir.
Sprinkle a few parsley
flakes over casserole.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: ham-pineapple bake
directions: Place ham slices in shallow baking pan.
Arrange pineapple slices on top.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake, uncovered, in 325° oven for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: gone all day stew
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in covered 3-quart casserole at 275° for 4 to 5 hours, until meat is tender.
Serves 6.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Start mixer and leave running.
Combine ingredients in order. Bake in ungreased tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: apple crisp
directions: Work with your fingers until crumbly,
Spread over apples, bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot with cream.

title: 2 by 4 soup
directions: Brown ground beef, add rest of ingredients with water and cook until done.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Cook onions in butter until transparent.
Add all vegies, chicken stock and chicken.
Add salt and pepper.
Simmer 1/2 hour until potatoes are tender.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: Combine zucchini and salt in colander.
Let stand 15 minutes and drain, squeezing out excess liquid with the back of a spoon. Combine with remaining ingredients, except oil.
Drop by teaspoonful into hot oil.

title: southern fried squash
directions: Batter with corn meal and flour mixed. Fry in 10-inch skillet until brown and tender.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Spread softened ice cream over the cookie layer.
Freeze again.
Spread fudge ice cream topping over frozen ice cream layer.
Freeze again.
Spread Cool Whip over chocolate layer.
Put in freezer until ready to serve and enjoy.

title: spiced apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large bowl, cream together oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
In separate bowl, have dry ingredients sifted together.
Add dry ingredients slowly to creamed mixture, blending constantly.
Stir batter until smooth, then add apples and nuts.
Continue mixing until apples and nuts are completely blended into batter.
Pour batter into Bundt cake pan and bake for 50 minutes.
Cool slightly before icing.

title: vera's jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add pineapple, strawberries, bananas and walnuts.
Pour 1/2 of mixture in pan until jello sets then spread with sour cream.
Spread other 1/2 of mixture on top.

title: jiffy corn bread muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients, adding muffin mix last.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Makes 18 muffins.

title: potato salad
directions: Dice potatoes.
Put potatoes in water and salt.
Boil until done.
Pour off water and let cool.
Add eggs, pickles, mustard and mayonnaise.
Mix well and serve hot or cold.

title: quick shrimp bisque
directions: Pour soups and milk in a 2-quart saucepan and stir over medium heat
until blended.
Add shrimp and seasonings.
Stir and heat until bubbly.

title: fudge candy
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and milk; boil for 6 minutes.
Add marshmallow cream, chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour into a buttered dish.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Cook in frypan the meat, celery, onions, green pepper and all other ingredients.
Mix together.
Put 1/2 ingredients in baking dish, then 1 package cheese; place other 1/2 ingredients on top, then other package cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 to 3/4 hour.

title: peanut butter cup cookies
directions: In mixing bowl, beat margarine, peanut butter and both sugars until creamy.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat well.
In another bowl combine flour and soda.
Add to peanut butter batter and mix well. Place in greased miniature muffin pans by teaspoonfuls.
Bake at 350° about 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and immediately push 1 peanut butter cup into each muffin cup.
Cool in refrigerator until shine disappears from chocolate.
Gently lift out of pan with knife.
Yields approximately 24.

title: parmesan fried fish
directions: Dry fish.
Combine flour and garlic salt and set aside.
Blend egg and milk; set aside.
Combine crumbs, cheese and parsley. Coat fillets in flour, then egg, then crumbs.
Fry over medium heat in 1/4 cup oil for 4 to 5 minutes per side.
Drain on paper towel.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: baked squash
directions: Wash and cut up squash.
Boil until tender; drain and mash. Add all ingredients except 1/2 of butter.
Pour mixture in baking dish; spread remaining butter over top.
Sprinkle top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° approximately 1 hour or until brown on top.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add rest of ingredients.
Roll in small balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
After cooling, roll in confectioners sugar or put sugar in Baggie and shake cookies.

title: great potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes; drain and cool slightly.
Slice potatoes in large bowl.
In small bowl, combine mayonnaise, sour cream, yogurt, onions, pickles, mustard, horseradish, garlic and seasonings.
Pour over potatoes and toss to coat.
Gently stir in eggs.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: messy cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix first 4 ingredients and press into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the last 3 ingredients and pour over the cake dough. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: yellow cake dessert
directions: Mix the cake mix according to package directions. Bake on a cookie sheet pan (12 x 17 or 12 x 18-inch).
Let cake cool.
Mix the pudding according to directions and whip until thick.
Pour over cooled cake.
Have the cream cheese at room temperature and mix with the pineapple.
Whip.
Pour over pudding layer.
Spread the Cool Whip over the cake and sprinkle with coconut.
Keep refrigerated.

title: angel delight
directions: Mix and press into a 9 x 13-inch microwave-safe dish.
Cook at 70% power for 4 to 6 minutes.
Cool.

title: autumn pork chop dinner
directions: In skillet heat oil and brown chops; set aside.
Toss cabbage with parsley and brown sugar; place in baking dish.
Top with potatoes and beans.
Arrange chops on vegetables.
Sprinkle with lemon pepper and apple juice.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Combine crumbs and butter and sprinkle on top.
Return to oven 5 minutes.
Makes 2 servings.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook macaroni or noodles according to package directions. Drain well. Combine with corned beef, cheese, soup, milk and onion. Place in greased 2-quart casserole, top with buttered bread crumbs and bake at 375° for 1 hour. Serves 4-6.

title: harvey wallbanger pie
directions: In medium saucepan, combine sugar, gelatin and salt, stir in orange juice, water, egg yolks and lemon juice, blend well; cook and stir over medium heat until gelatin dissolves and mixture is slightly thickened.
Remove from heat, stir in Galliano and vodka, chill until partly set.
Beat egg whites to soft peaks, gradually add 1/4 cup sugar; beat until stiff peaks.
Fold in egg white mix to partly set.
Beat 1 cup whipping cream, fold into gelatin and chill.
Beat 1 1/2 cups whipping cream and spoon onto pie and chill.
Decorate with orange slices.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat all eggs and sugar together. Pour into an unbaked pie crust. Sprinkle nutmeg on top of mixture. Bake 45 minutes or until done at 350°.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken 20 minutes.
Rinse in cold water to cool.
Slice or cut into strips or cubes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake in a 375° oven for 30 minutes.

title: lemon salad
directions: Prepare jello as usual until it starts to set, then add other ingredients and let set.

title: hot sausage appetizers
directions: Mix together. Form into balls and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: seven minute icing
directions: Place all ingredients except vanilla in a double boiler; mix thoroughly.
Cook, beating steadily until frosting peaks, about 7 minutes.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and beat until thick.

title: aggression cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together with hands.
Roll dough into balls.
Butter bottom of glass and press into sugar.
Press each cookie dough ball onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Roll hamburger into small meatballs.
Bake in oven at 400° about 30 minutes.

title: shrimp jambalaya
directions: Cook celery, green pepper and onion in	half
the butter or margarine, until tender but not brown; add	garlic	and ham; cook about
5 minutes longer.
Add
remaining butter,
shrimp, salt, hot
pepper
sauce,
chili powder and
sugar
and
cook, tossing often with fork until shrimp are
pink.
Add
tomatoes and heat. Stir in rice and serve immediately.
Enjoy!
Bake on medium-low heat for approximately 45 minutes.	Serves 4 to 6.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: In a large bowl, mix pudding mix and milk.
Add sweetened condensed milk.
Fold in 1/4 whipped topping.
Line a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish with wafers.
Top with strawberries (sliced).
Pour pudding mix over strawberries.
Place another layer of wafers on top of pudding, then top with remaining whipped topping.
Also suitable for banana, coconut and pineapple pudding.
Serves 10.

title: beef chop suey
directions: Fry meat in butter.
Add all the rest of ingredients and cook until tender.
Thicken with 1/3 cup water and 2 teaspoons cornstarch and 2 teaspoons soy sauce.
Simmer.
Cook rice, add soy sauce to taste.
Serve with cheese, pickles, radishes and crackers.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread layer of refried beans.
Combine sour cream, taco mix and mayonnaise.
Spread thin layer over beans.
Top with layers of tomatoes, lettuce, green onions, cheese and olives.
Chill.
Serve with corn chips.

title: cranberry sauce salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
While hot, add cranberry sauce and heat until smooth.
When slightly thickened, fold in celery, pineapple and nuts.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef, onions, garlic and shortening.
Drain off excess fat and stir in the tomato sauce, tomato ketchup, oregano leaves, salt and pepper.
Simmer, uncovered, for 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.

title: over fun cake
directions: Cook pineapple and sugar for 5 minutes in a small pan.
Pour over cake.
Mix together the cream cheese and pudding; pour over pineapple.
Slice bananas and put on for next layer.
Add Cool Whip, nuts and coconut to make final topping.

title: cookie jar gingersnaps
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in the egg and molasses.
Combine flour, baking soda, ginger, cinnamon and salt; gradually add to creamed mixture.
Roll teaspoonfuls of dough into balls.
Dip one side in sugar; place, with sugar side up, on a greased cookie sheet.

title: baked cabbage
directions: Cut the cabbage into wedges and parboil in the water in a covered saucepan for about 4 minutes.
Drain and place the cabbage in a buttered or greased 2-quart casserole.
Dot with the butter or melt and pour over evenly.
Blend flour, salt, pepper, sugar and milk.
Pour mixture over the cabbage and top with the grated cheese.
Bake at 350°
for 35 minutes or until golden brown on top and bubbling around the edges.
Makes 4 servings.

title: corn bread jack-o-lantern
directions: You will need an art-n-craft mini Jack-O-lantern pan and Pam spray.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar and salt.
Heat butter, cocoa and Coke.
Add marshmallows and bring to a boil. Pour over flour mixture and mix well.
Pour in oblong pan and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cranberry fruit salad
directions: Mix cranberries and sugar; mix well.
Set overnight.
Drain and then mix all ingredients to chill!

title: oven rice(great with roasts, etc.)
directions: Wash and drain rice.
Brown rice in margarine, then add other ingredients and bake in covered casserole dish for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: italian chicken
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and heat until margarine is melted.
Place chicken in 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour sauce over chicken and bake uncovered at 325°
for 1 hour.

title: italian chicken cacciatore
directions: Clean, dry and roll chicken in seasoned flour, salt and pepper.
Then fry in large skillet in hot oil until chicken browns.
Add all other ingredients, except wine.
Simmer until sauce is thick and chicken is tender.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage until done, stirring; crumble.
Drain on paper towels; set aside.
Spread each slice of bread with butter.
Cut into cubes.
Place bread cubes in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Sprinkle with sausage; top with cheese.
Combine remaining ingredients; beat well and pour over mixture.
Chill overnight. Remove from refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes. Serve hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: corn chowder
directions: Add first five ingredients to the boiling water, cover and simmer until all vegetables are done (10-15 minutes) DO NOT DRAIN. Add corn.
Mix until smooth, then add to vegetables.
Heat DO NOT BOIL.
Small pieces of meat or ham may be added.

title: beef in creamy mushroom sauce
directions: Stir cornstarch into water and keep aside.
Cook steak strips, then add onion, garlic, red peppers, salt and pepper.
When cooked, add mushrooms, brandy and bouillon granules.
Simmer 3 minutes.
Stir in cornstarch mixture and simmer until thickened. Stir in chives and serve over noodles.
Makes 6 servings, 3 grams fat per serving.

title: crock-pot clam chowder
directions: In skillet saute bacon and onion until golden brown; drain. Put into crock-pot with clams.
Add all remaining ingredients, except cream.
Cover; cook on HIGH 3 to 4 hours or until potatoes are tender.
During the last hour of cooking, combine 1 cup of milk with the cornstarch; add that and the remaining milk and blend thoroughly.
Heat through until chowder is thickened and bubbly, stirring frequently.

title: easiest dessert in the world
directions: Add pudding to pineapple. Add Cool Whip and mix well.
Fold in marshmallows.

title: pound cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt together.
Add eggs, shortening and milk and mix, then add vanilla and lemon flavoring. Put in greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour or stick toothpick in middle.
If nothing comes off of the toothpick, it is done.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: pecan brittle
directions: Spice it with humor,

title: spinach dip
directions: Thoroughly drain and squeeze spinach.
Cut mayonnaise with sour cream as desired.
Thoroughly mix spinach, mayonnaise, sour cream and dressing together.
Cut a large round hole in bread. Fill with dip.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix cake as directed, pour into greased pan. Sprinkle rhubarb over batter. Pour 1 pint whipping cream over all. Bake at 350 degrees until set.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and drain spinach, being sure to squeeze out all liquid, then mix all ingredients and chill.
Serve with a variety of fresh vegetables.

title: date bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Mix thoroughly butter, sugar and eggs. Stir in Bisquick, nuts and dates.
Bake 25-30 minutes on greased cookie sheet.
Cool about one hour.
Cut in bars and roll in confectioner's sugar.

title: microwave cheese potatoes
directions: Scrub unpeeled potatoes and slice.
Layer potatoes and sprinkle with celery and onion salt.
Sprinkle cheese and drop pads of butter on top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Microwave, covered, for 16 to 18 minutes, turning several times during cooking.
Allow to stand for 5 minutes after cooking.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Grease and flour large angel food cake pan.
Separate eggs in different bowls.
Sift flour and measure.
Add baking soda and sift 2 more times.
Cream butter and sugar thoroughly.
Add egg yolks, one at a time and beat after each addition.
Add sour cream and beat also.
Add flour and baking soda mixture to the creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Beat the egg whites until stiff.
Fold the beaten egg whites into the mixture.
Pour into angel food pan. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: one pot italian spaghetti
directions: Cook ground beef and onion in large skillet. Drain. Stir in tomato sauce, and spaghetti sauce. Add salt, sugar, water and uncooked spaghetti. Heat to boiling stirring often. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer over low heat about 15 minutes or until spaghetti is tender.

title: pineapple punch
directions: Place tea in a large bowl; add lemon juice, orange juice, lime juice, sugar and mint.
Chill these ingredients for about 2 hours. Shortly before serving, strain the punch and add the pineapple and juice, ginger ale, plain soda and crushed ice.
Makes 18 servings.

title: tuna cakes
directions: Mix tuna, dressing, mustard, vegetables, pimiento and seasonings.
Add 1/2 cup bread crumbs.
Shape mixture into 15 (2-inch) balls.
Roll in remaining bread crumbs.
Coat well.
Pat balls in small patties.
Refrigerate 30 minutes.
Heat oil in a large skillet on medium-high heat.
Add tuna patties.
Cook 5 minutes on each side or until golden brown.
Add oil as needed. Drain on paper towels.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sugar free pumpkin pie
directions: Mix can of pumpkin, milk and pumpkin pie spice together very well. Add pudding mix; mix quickly into pumpkin mixture. Pour into crust. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: spaghetti with ground turkey tomato sauce
directions: Bring a large pot of water to boil.
Lightly bruise 3 garlic cloves and set aside.
Mince the remaining 3 garlic cloves. Coarsely chopped onion.
In a small bowl, combine the turkey, crushed garlic, 1/2 teaspoon of oregano, 1/2 teaspoon of salt and 1/4 teaspoon of pepper.
In a medium saucepan, warm the oil over medium heat; add turkey mixture, the onion and garlic cloves and cook, stirring frequently to break up mixture, until just turning brown.
Add tomatoes (undrained), tomato paste, bay leaf and the remaining dry ingredients.
Bring to a boil; break up tomatoes. Simmer 20 minutes on low.
About 10 minutes before sauce is done, add spaghetti to water.
Serve sauce over spaghetti.

title: cream chicken over egg noodles
directions: Wrap 1 slice of bacon around each breast and place in a baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cook at 250° for 3 hours.
Serve over egg noodles.

title: holiday breakfast bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Add blended eggs and oil.
Add remaining 5 ingredients.
Makes 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour to 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: In skillet, cook sausage until brown.
Drain.
Separate crescent dough into 8 triangles.
Place on ungreased 12-inch pizza pan with points toward center.
Pat dough to fit bottom and sides of pan, sealing perforations.
Spoon
sausage over dough. Sprinkle with potatoes.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
In bowl, beat together eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over preceding ingredients and top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in 375°
for 25 minutes.

title: strawberry angel delight
directions: Variation:
Substitute lime gelatin for strawberry and 1 (20 ounce) can crushed pineapple in syrup for strawberries and syrup.

title: sesame seed cookies
directions: To beaten eggs, add shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Mix well. Gradually add flour and baking powder, blending until the flour is absorbed.
Rinse and drain the sesame seed well.
Place them in a pie plate.
Flour hands and pull off small pieces of dough.
Roll between palms until the size desired, about 2-inches long and 1/2-inch wide.
Then roll into the sesame seed.
If they will not stick to dough, add a little water to keep the seeds moist.
Place close together on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 5 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream all together first four ingredients.
Pour into baked pie shells.
Top with crumbled peanuts.
Put in refrigerator and let set.
Makes two pies.

title: slumgullion
directions: Grind beef and pork together.
This recipe makes a very large casserole full, so cut it down to your own individual proportion.

title: cake frosting
directions: Mix half the sugar with butter until fluffy.
Add egg white and beat, then remaining sugar a little at a time.
Add 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.

title: chocolate cheese cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients to form crust.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes on a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream together the cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled crust.
Mix pudding and milk.
Spread on top of cheese mixture.
Top with rest of Cool Whip and a few nuts.

title: olene's fruit salad
directions: Mix together and chill.
Serves 16 or more.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: pea salad
directions: Drain beans, corn and peas.
Combine in bowl beans, corn, peas, celery, green onions and pimentos.
In a two-cup pitcher, combine oil and vinegar.
Add sugar.
Mix until sugar dissolves.
Pour over salad.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: lemon bars deluxe
directions: Sift together 2 cups of the flour and 1/2 cup powdered sugar. Cut in margarine until mix clings together.
Press into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: zucchini sausage bake(low-cal)
directions: Brown sausage, drain.
Toss with 1 tablespoon flour.
Spread in 11 x 7-inch dish.
Cook zucchini and onion in microwave.
Stir in oleo.
Toss with remaining flour.
Spoon half over sausage.

title: ann's sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in unbaked 10-inch pie shell. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: caramel bars
directions: Add to the cake mix 1/3 cup evaporated milk and margarine. Spread 1/2 of mixture in a 9 x 13-inch lightly greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
While baking, melt caramels with 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Take out of oven; sprinkle with chips and nuts. Drizzle with melted caramels; top with rest of cake mix.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: florida snowballs
directions: Cream	sugar,	shortening
and
butter
together.
Add vanilla, almond extract and chopped nuts.
Add flour and salt. Cream
together;
roll into ball by the teaspoonfuls.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while hot.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix all together, adding ginger ale just before serving. Makes 3 1/2 quarts.

title: chicken divan
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 12 x 8-inch (2-quart) baking dish.
Cook broccoli as directed on package; drain.
Arrange broccoli in prepared baking dish.
Layer chicken over broccoli. In small bowl, combine soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice; mix well. Spread crumbs and margarine; sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, or until thoroughly heated.
Serves 6.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add the beaten eggs, sour cream and vanilla.
Mix well, then add flour which has been sifted with baking powder and soda.
Cream all together until smooth.
Chill dough in refrigerator for about 1 hour.
Take out chilled dough and cut into desired shapes.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes, depending on thickness of dough.

title: sour cream chicken
directions: Melt margarine or butter.
Add stuffing mix to margarine. Layer chicken in dish.
Mix sour cream and mushroom soup.
Spread sour cream and soup on chicken.
Spread stuffing on top.
Cook for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Mix together 1/2 cup sugar, 1/2 cup flour, cinnamon and margarine.
Continue mixing until crumbly; sprinkle over blueberries.
Bake in 400° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: divinity
directions: Cook sugar, syrup, water and salt.
Do not stir after sugar is dissolved.
Cook until boiling syrup when dropped from spoon in cold water becomes very hard almost brittle ball.
Pour slowly into beaten egg whites and beat until it holds its shape when dropped from a spoon.
Add nuts just before dropping from spoon. Can also be poured into greased rectangular pan and cut into squares after it sets.

title: hot wassail
directions: Heat to boiling.
Add cinnamon stick (put all spices in cheesecloth bag).

title: vegetable chili
directions: Combine all ingredients; bring to a boil, then simmer for 45 minutes.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a shallow baking dish. In mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar and milk.
Pour evenly over butter.
Combine berries, sugar and water.
Spoon evenly over flour mixture.
Do not stir.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: banana split dessert
directions: For first layer, mix vanilla wafers, 1/2 cup powdered sugar and the melted margarine together and spread in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: salmon loaf
directions: In a small bowl combine first three ingredients.
Add next four ingredients.
Stir in bread crumbs.
Add egg.
Mix well.
Shape into loaf and place in greased 1-quart baking dish.
(I bake mine in small greased loaf pan.)
Bake 25 minutes in preheated 350° oven.
Serves 2 or 3.

title: chocolate mint fudge
directions: Boil first five ingredients over medium heat in a heavy saucepan for 5 minutes (rolling boil).
Remove from heat.
Stir in morsels and vanilla.
Stir until morsels melt and fudge looks glazed.
Pour into greased pan.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: rock candy
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in a large heavy saucepan.
Stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Boil, without stirring, until temperature reaches 310° or until drops of syrup form hard brittle threads in cold water.
(Candy thermometer recommended.)
Remove from heat.
When boiling stops, add flavoring and food coloring.

title: dark chocolate cake
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
Add oil, eggs and vanilla. Then slowly add boiling water as you mix them all together.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: strawberries 'n cream dessert
directions: Cut cake and line dish with slices.
Melt marshmallows in milk; pour over cake.
Spread thawed strawberries over this; cover all with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: fat man cake
directions: Combine margarine with sugar and eggs.
Blend in remaining ingredients; pour into well greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Open oven door and shake pan several times.
Continue baking for 20 minutes.
Serve warm.
Has brownie like texture and requires no icing.

title: chow-chow
directions: Grind vegetables.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup salt.
Let stand overnight; rinse and drain.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling; simmer for 3 minutes.
Seal in hot jars.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix thawed lemonade with Eagle Brand milk at low speed with mixer.
Add Cool Whip and mix thoroughly.
Pour into pie crust and chill.

title: spinach and pasta casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook spaghetti and drain.
In a bowl combine spinach, Ricotta cheese, eggs and salt.
Beat with electric mixer until blended.
Coat a shallow 10-inch casserole dish with cooking spray.
Place spaghetti in casserole; top with Ricotta mixture.
Spread spaghetti sauce over top, then sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over sauce.
Cover and bake 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, water and cornstarch until thick.
Add jello and mix.
Pour over strawberries and mix.
Pour into baked pie shell for deep dish pie.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Stir in soup and mushrooms.
Cook beans with salt, pepper and dill seed in enough water to cover for 5 minutes.
Drain beans.
Combine rest of the ingredients except for cheese and cream.
Put in a baking dish and pour cream over and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 18 minutes.
Serves 18.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in 1 tablespoon salt until sharp knife cuts through cooked potatoes.
Peel and cut to bite-size.
Mix salt, pepper, paprika, sugar, vinegar and water.
Pour and mix over warm potatoes.
Refrigerate overnight.
Add onion, eggs, pickle and celery.
Mix mayonnaise in carefully.
Salt and pepper may be added to taste.

title: crispy cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and onion as thinly as possible.
Sprinkle on sugar.
Mix together and bring to a boil the vinegar, salad oil, sugar, salt, mustard and celery seed. Pour hot mixture over vegetables.
Do not stir.
Let stand at room temperature 4 to 6 hours.
Stir and refrigerate.
Stays crisp for days.

title: tropical cheesecake
directions: Cream confectioners sugar and cream cheese together.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Then add crushed pineapple.
Pour the mixture into the graham cracker pie shell.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: date bars
directions: Prepare Date Filling; cool.
Heat oven to 400°.
Grease square pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inch.
Mix brown sugar, margarine and shortening. Mix in baking mix and oats.
Press half of the crumbly mixture in pan; spread with filling.
Top with remaining crumbly mixture; press gently into filling.
Bake until light brown, 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into bars, about 2 x 1 1/2-inch.
Makes 2 dozen cookies.

title: king size sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: alma's cherry dream salad
directions: Mix pineapple, pie filling, condensed milk and nuts in a large bowl.
Fold in whipped topping.
Fold in marshmallows.
Place in a mold or a 9 x 13-inch pan.
This may be served immediately or chilled or frozen for later use.
This yields 12 to 15 servings. It is delicious.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine first seven ingredients;
add milk and melted butter; mix well.
Pour into
1 1/2 quart casserole.
Bake at 350 degrees about one hour or until mixture is firm.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: chicken and creamy garlic sauce by ragu(serves 4)
directions: In 12-inch nonstick skillet, heat oil over medium heat and lightly brown chicken. Stir in Ragu Cheese Creations! pasta sauce and tomato. Simmer, covered, stirring occasionally, 10 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Add taco seasoning, 1 cup water and chopped onion.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Stir well until all mixed and hot.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into dish lined with tortillas.
Add another layer of tortillas; then pour remaining mixture.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cranberry slush
directions: Freeze and serve with 7-Up or Squirt.

title: shoe string salad
directions: Mix with Miracle Whip until very moist.
Chill just before serving.
Add 1 can shoestring potatoes.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix ingredients together. Refrigerate 1 hour to mix flavors. Serve with corn chips or nachos.

title: steak and potato bake
directions: Place round steak in large cake pan.
Cover with sliced potatoes,
sweet
onion and sliced carrots.
Add mushroom soup mixed
with
1 can water.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° until tender.

title: barbecue meatball appetizers
directions: Mix beef, onion, egg, bread crumbs, allspice, garlic, milk, salt and pepper.
Form into walnut sized meatballs.
Place on a jelly roll or shallow pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
In a frying pan or 2-quart saucepan, combine jelly and chili sauce. Place meatballs in pan.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Serve warm.
(May be made several days ahead to serve for a party.)
Makes approximately 25 meatballs.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine cornstarch, sugar, lemon juice and beaten egg yolks. Add water and boil 4 minutes.
Make meringue of egg whites and 6 tablespoons sugar.
Bake at 425° for 4 to 5 minutes.

title: cream cheese dip
directions: Cream the cheese and Miracle Whip.
Add Worcestershire sauce. Add a small amount of milk (if needed to make it smooth).
Add onion.
Serve with chips.
Serves 1 1/2 cups.

title: no-bake chocolate nut rum balls(makes 3 dozen)
directions: Combine crushed wafers, confectioners sugar, 1 cup walnuts and cocoa.
Add corn syrup and rum; mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll half in granulated sugar and the other half in the remaining chopped nuts.
Moisten cut sides of cherry halves with corn syrup and press one on each sugar-coated rum ball.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Melt butter (or oleo) in large Dutch oven.
Cook chopped onions, garlic, green pepper and celery until clear.
Add crawfish and cook another 10 to 15 minutes.
Add all soups and Ro-Tel, blending well.
Cook until crawfish turn pink and then turn off heat.
Garnish with green onions, etc.
(Freezes well.)

title: shrimp victoria
directions: Saute shrimp for about 10 minutes in butter over medium heat. Add onion and mushrooms.
Sprinkle flour lightly over mixture. Cook on low heat approximately 5 more minutes, then add sour cream.
Heat slightly on low heat.
Serve hot over rice or toast points.

title: sausage-noodle bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 2-quart baking dish.
Combine soup and milk in a saucepan until well blended.
Cook slowly until well heated.
Add 1 cup cheese and stir until melted.
Add sausage, noodles, green peppers and pimiento.
Heat until blended. Pour into baking dish.
Top with remaining cheese and crumbs. Cover and bake 20 minutes.
Remove cover and bake until top is golden brown, approximately 15 minutes.

title: crab casserole
directions: Empty soup into saucepan; add milk, stir and bring to bubbling on medium heat.
Add cheese and stir milk until melted.
Fold in crab meat.
Heat thoroughly. Pour into casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumbs and bake in 400° oven until browned.
Serves 4.

title: orange cake
directions: Beat peach pie filling until small pieces.
Add orange cake mix, eggs (beaten) and sour cream.
Bake for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: sweetened whipped cream
directions: Use small mixer bowl to combine cream, confectioners sugar and vanilla; beat until stiff.
Serve cold.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Cream the shortening, then add sugar gradually and continue creaming it until it is light and fluffy. Blend in eggs.
Sift together dry ingredients. Combine pumpkin and milk. Add dry ingredients alternately with pumpkin mixture to the egg mixture, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Stir in chopped nuts. Bake in 2 greased layer pans at 350° for 30 minutes. Frost cake with your favorite buttercream icing using orange juice for the liquid and grated orange rind for added zest.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients with hands.
Form into balls.
Makes 65 to 70 balls.
Melt chocolate or chocolate chips and paraffin.
Dip balls in chocolate.
Place on cookie sheet that has been lined with wax paper.
Cool.

title: stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes until done, either in the oven or the microwave. Cut the top off of the potatoes. Scoop out the center of the potatoes into a large bowl. To the potato, add butter, salt, pepper and garlic salt. Add cheese (as much as you like), bacon bits and diced onions. Use as much or as little of these items as you like. Mix well. Gradually add the sour cream; mix until the mixture is almost creamy. Spoon the mixture back into the potato shells. Microwave 1 to 2 minutes before serving. Extras may be refrigerated for later.

title: puff pastry
directions: To prevent crust from getting "soggy" with a cream pie, first sprinkle crust with powdered sugar.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: In skillet, in 1 tablespoon hot oil, stir-fry half of the chicken until browned.
Remove.
Repeat with remaining chicken.
In remaining 1 tablespoon hot oil, stir fry vegetables with ginger and garlic powder until tender-crisp.
Add soup, soy sauce and vinegar. Heat to boiling.
Return chicken to skillet.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4. Preparation Time:
15 minutes.
Cooking Time:
25 minutes.

title: oatmeal bread(makes 4 medium loaves)
directions: Add the molasses, yeast, water and salt to the oatmeal mix. Add flour gradually.
Knead slightly.
Let rise covered, until doubled in bulk.
Knead thoroughly on floured surface and put in buttered and floured bread pans.
Let rise until double.
(You may use regular or quick rise yeast.)
Bake at 375° (preheated) for about 40 minutes.
It feels solid when it is done.

title: roast beef
directions: Put roast, fat side down, on microwave roasting rack in shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle mushrooms over top of roast. Cover roast with waxed paper.
Cook on 80 for 10 to 12 minutes. Turn over and spoon juices over top.
Cover and cook on 70 for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: the oatmeal cookie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In bowl melt margarine, then add sugar, egg, vanilla, flour, baking powder, salt, milk and oatmeal (any flavor you like).
Mix well.
Drop spoonfuls of mixture onto greased cookie sheet (2-inch cookies).
Cool until edges are light brown, 10 to 15 minutes.
Cookie is done when center is firm when touched with finger.
Eat and enjoy.
Yields 12 (2-inch) cookies.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, stir first 5 ingredients until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into frozen crust.
Put a small amount of foil around edge of pie shell.
Bake in oven for 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.
(Be careful not to overbake.)
Cool and serve.

title: peanut butter temptations
directions: Cream together butter, peanut butter, sugar and brown sugar. Add eggs and vanilla.
Add flour.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Put in miniature muffin pans.
Leave in ball form.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: northern italian broccoli salad
directions: Parcook fresh broccoli or defrost frozen spears.
When cool, marinate in remaining ingredients about 1 hour.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix and spread over Marshmallow Creme.

title: orange bread
directions: Squeeze juice from orange and add boiling water to make 1 cup. Put orange rind, raisins and nuts through food chopper.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Roll washed and dried chicken in flour and brown in 1/3 cup oil.
Remove as browned to shallow roasting pan, arranging skin side up.
Preheat oven to 350° while making sauce.

title: fresh blueberry pie
directions: Line cooled pie shell with 2 cups blueberries.
To make sauce, cook remaining blueberries with sugar, cornstarch, salt and water over medium heat until thickened.
Remove from heat; add butter and cool.
Pour over berries in shell.
Chill until serving time. If desired, serve with whipping cream.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Put potatoes in 1 1/2 to 2-quart ovenproof casserole with 1 tablespoon oil.
Mix other ingredients, except corn flakes, and pour over potatoes.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.
Remove and sprinkle top with corn flakes.
Dot with butter, bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add onions and pepper.
Add spices, tomato sauce, mushrooms and pepperoni.
Stir.
Cover and simmer for 1/2 hour.
Cook noodles as directed on package.
Drain noodles; wash with cold water.
Drain again and add to skillet. Warm, then add 1 cup cheese.
Warm for 1 minute.
Pour into 2 (9 x 13-inch) greased baking dishes.
Divide olives and lay on top both dishes.
Cover each with 1 cup cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake both dishes or freeze unbaked.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix together salt, cucumbers and onions. Cover with ice for 3 hours. Drain well. Mix together with remaining ingredients. Heat to a boiling point. Seal in prepared canning jars.

title: recipe for a happy marriage
directions: For extra flavor, add happy memories and dash of recreation. Stir well and remove any specks of jealousy, temper or criticism. If you like a sweeter product, simply add more love.
Keep warm with a steady flame of devotion.
Never serve with a cold shoulder or a hot tongue.

title: miniature cheesecakes
directions: Will need paper liners for muffin tins.

title: hawaiian salad
directions: In a saucepan, combine pineapple, sugar, and salt.
Cook 10 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix gelatin and water.
Let cool until syrupy, then combine with pineapple mixture.
Mix whipped topping as directed on package.

title: pasta and bean soup
directions: Soak beans 8 hours or overnight.
Rinse and drain.
Combine beans, water, salt and carrot.
Simmer in a 6-quart pot 2 hours or until beans are tender. Combine onion, celery, garlic, tomatoes, bay leaf, oregano, salt, pepper and 1/4 cup water. Bring to a boil.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Cook macaroni according to directions and drain. Cube carrot and combine all ingredients.
Heat before serving.
Makes 3 1/2 quarts.

title: quick peanut butter cups
directions: Combine butter, confectioners sugar and peanut butter in bowl; mix well.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let stand for 5 minutes. Spread melted chocolate over top.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Cut into squares.

title: italian meat sauce
directions: Saute onions and garlic in olive oil.
Brown hamburger and pour off excess oil.
Pour onions, garlic and olive oil into hamburger.
Add tomatoes and spices.
Simmer uncovered or with lid cracked 3 hours or until sauce is thickened.
Stir occasionally. Remove bay leaves.
Serve over hot spaghetti.
Add Parmesan cheese.

title: chicken breasts-oven baked
directions: Line long baking dish with dried beef.
Wrap chicken breasts with strips of bacon and place on the beef.
Mix the soup and sour cream; pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 275° for 2 to 3 hours.
Wonderful over rice.

title: szechwan beef and snow peas
directions: Slice beef across grain into thin strips.
Combine 1 tablespoon each, cornstarch and soy sauce with sherry and garlic.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, combine remaining cornstarch, soy sauce, red pepper, and 3/4 cup water; set aside.
Remove tips and strings from snow peas.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil in wok or large skillet over high heat.
Add beef and stir-fry 1 minute; remove beef from skillet.
Heat remaining oil in same wok/skillet, add snow peas and onion, sprinkle salt lightly over vegetables and stir-fry 3 minutes.
Add beef, soy mixture and tomato.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens.
Serve with rice.

title: pumpkin cake(yields 1 cake)
directions: Mix flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt in separate bowl.
Beat eggs, oil and sugar until well mixed.
Add flour mixture and stir in pumpkin.
Bake in 350° oven in a greased and floured Bundt pan for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Drain the pork and beans, chickpeas and butter beans.
Brown first 3 ingredients in skillet.
Do not drain grease.
Add remaining ingredients; cover.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour, or in crock-pot on low for 6 hours.

title: easy muffins
directions: Sift flour and sugar.
Add egg, milk and oil.
Stir well.
It may be rough textured.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: grandma's meat loaf
directions: Mix together and form a loaf.
Ice with ketchup.
Salt and pepper.
Add water around loaf until pan is half full.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 400°.

title: crock- pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Spray crock pot with cooking spray.
Combine milk, egg, salt and pepper.
Mix with wire whisk.
Add cheese and macaroni, stirring gently to mix.
Cover and cook on low for 3 1/2 to 4 hours, or until custard is set and macaroni is tender.
Serves 8.

title: cherry wink cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Blend Crisco and sugar, then add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Blend in dry ingredients and gradually add nuts and cherries.
Drop by rounded teaspoons into crushed cornflakes. Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Top with 1/4 cherry if desired. Bake for 12 to 15 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: sausage stroganoff
directions: Combine
sausage,
onion and green pepper in a skillet. Cook over
medium
heat
until
sausage
is brown and onion is tender. Drain off pan drippings.

title: summer pudding
directions: You will also need a 4 or 5-cup bowl.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream together cream cheese, oleo and powdered sugar.
Add vanilla.
In another bowl, mix puddings and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Fold in cream cheese mixture.
Mix well.
Have Oreos crushed.
Spread mixture in 9 x 14-inch pan.
Spread Oreos over top.
Chill well.

title: spicy broccoli and rice
directions: Remove the outer leaves from medium-sized heads of cabbage (about 8 pounds) and wash them in water, to be very fine, rejecting only the thickest part of the stem.
Measure 2 tablespoons salt in a dish.
Place a layer of shredded cabbage on the bottom of an earthern crock; sprinkle on the salt and pound down with a wooden potato masher until well packed.
Add another layer of cabbage, with salt, and proceed as before, until crock is nearly full.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine
peanut
butter and sugar.
Fold in egg whites. Drop by	teaspoonful
onto
baking
sheet lined with Reynolds Wrap. Flatten slightly with prongs of fork.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Remove to wire racks to cool.

title: quickie pickles
directions: Boil together sugar and vinegar; set aside to cool.
Mix cucumbers with all other ingredients and then add to sugar and vinegar.
Put in refrigerator and serve after 2 hours.

title: girls' day three layer jello salad(pretty salad for valentine's day or christmas day)
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water. Cool. Blend in cream cheese and lemon juice. Chill until syrupy.
Fold in the whipped cream and chill in a 2-quart casserole.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown
hamburger;
add	taco
sauce,
enchilada
sauce, mushroom
and chicken soup.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Break tortillas in long casserole dish.
Top with hamburger, sauce mixture and onion.
Bake
until bubbly in the middle.
Sprinkle cheese on top and melt.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: french coffee cake
directions: Mix together the milk, flour and yeast mixture and let rise about 1 hour in a warm place.
Add the sugar, butter, salt and eggs.
Add the flour. Grease a spring-form pan and sprinkle bottom with nuts.
Put in dough.
Let rise to top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn upside down and spread with butter frosting.

title: chili dip
directions: In a 9-inch pie plate layer ingredients: cream cheese, chili and cheeses.
Microwave 5 minutes.

title: one-pot pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops.
Pour off fat.
Add all other ingredients. Cover and simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: partridge berry pie
directions: Mix ingredients all together in large bowl.
Pour into pie shells.
Place in refrigerator or freezer.

title: day-after turkey divan
directions: Arrange broccoli in single layer in shallow baking dish, 9-inch square.
Top with turkey or chicken pieces.
Blend soup and milk.
Pour over meat. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in a 450° oven until cheese and sauce are melted and slightly browned, about 15 minutes.
Serve over hot cooked white rice.

title: brandy slush
directions: Put in bucket or pail and freeze.
Stir occasionally.

title: pepper steak(202 calories per serving)
directions: Trim excess fat from steak; cut meat into 2 x 1/4-inch strips. In medium skillet, brown meat strips in hot shortening; drain off excess fat.
Drain tomatoes, reserving liquid.
Add reserved tomato liquid, onion slices, garlic clove, beef bouillon, Worcestershire sauce, salt and dash of pepper to browned meat strips.
Cover tightly and simmer mixture over low heat for 50 minutes.
Stir in green pepper strips and tomato wedges.
Cook meat mixture, covered, until green pepper is tender, about 6 to 8 minutes.
Remove meat and vegetables to serving bowl with slotted spoon.
Reserve cooking liquid to pass, adding additional hot water to make 1/2 cup, if necessary.
Makes 6 servings.

title: triple cheese spread(can be made days ahead)
directions: Let ingredients stand at room temperature all day.
When softened, beat with electric mixer.
Serve with crackers, breadsticks, etc.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Chop up onion and celery (boil in small saucepan with small amount of water until tender).
Cook cornbread.
Cool chicken breasts and debone.
In large mixing bowl put onions and celery, pull cornbread apart in small chunks.
Add to bowl, pull bread apart, add to bowl.
Add eggs (beaten) to mix. Add salt, pepper and sage (to taste).
Add chicken broth (hot) enough broth to soften, approximately half of big pot.
Add chicken last.
Put in large roaster pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until brown.

title: failure-proof fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk, butter and salt in saucepan; bring to a vigorous boil, stirring often.
Reduce heat; simmer 6 minutes.

title: monster cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients in order and drop by tablespoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 minutes. Makes about 12 to 13 dozen.
Freezes well.
Can do half the recipe.

title: oatmeal bars
directions: Put remaining oat mixture on top.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in a 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole dish at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: tomato pie
directions: Combine Bisquick and milk; press into a 9-inch pie pan to make crust.
Add enough tomatoes to fill crust.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and spices.
Combine mayonnaise and cheese; spread over top of tomatoes.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco.
Add sugar and beat until mixture is smooth.
Add yolks and beat well.
Combine flour and soda; add to the creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in vanilla and add coconut and chopped nuts.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into 3 (9-inch) cake pans and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pecan torte
directions: Mix flour, pecans and margarine until flaky in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes until brown (350° oven); cool.

title: easy pot roast
directions: Place meat in small roasting pan and sprinkle with onion soup. Then spread on mushroom soup (right from the can).
Cover and place in a slow 275° oven for 5 hours.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: 7 Cream butter in a large bowl gradualy adding sugar.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients gradualy to creamed mixture.
Chill dough.
Roll on lightly floured surface to 1/8th inch.
Cut with cookie cutters. Sprinkle with granulated sugar if desired.

title: strawberry supreme
directions: After blending to the desired consistency, add 1 package strawberry supplement.
Blend just to mix.
Do not overblend.

title: mock apple pie
