directions: Bring to a boil the water, sugar, butter and cream of tartar. Drop the crackers in pan and let boil 2 minutes without stirring. Cool.
Pour into crust.
Dot with butter and the cinnamon.
Bake 10 minutes at 400° and reduce heat to 350° for 20 minutes.
You can put a top crust on, if desired.

title: garden salad
directions: Mix salad oil, mustard, salt, black pepper, cider vinegar, white sugar and celery seed and bring to a boil.
Pour over cabbage and other ingredients while hot; set aside and chill before serving.
Good the next day also.

title: charm house molasses muffins
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add molasses.
Combine soda and buttermilk; add to mixture, blending well.
Combine flour and spices; add to molasses mixture.
Stir in raisins, mixing well. Fill greased muffin tin 2/3 full and bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Makes 3 1/2 dozen.
This batter will keep in refrigerator for two weeks if kept tightly closed.

title: jan hagel
directions: Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: lemon-lime jello
directions: Dissolve lime jello in hot water.
Let partially set.
Add pineapple; let set until hard.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Saute
celery
and
onion in butter.
Add mushrooms and mushroom
soup.
Cook
and drain broccoli.
Melt garlic cheese in double boiler and combine all ingredients.
Serve hot with Fritos or other chips.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix and bake in 8 x 8-inch pan sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.
One serving = 1 bread, 1/4 fat and 15 optional calories.

title: green bean salad
directions: Drain beans and rinse well.
Drain and rinse again.
Add pepper and onion.
Mix other ingredients and add to beans.
Mix well and let stand overnight.

title: blueberry crumble pie
directions: Mix together sugar, margarine and eggs in a large bowl.
Add the blueberries and crushed saltines; mix well.
Pour into the pie shells and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: low-fat carrot - pineapple muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
In large bowl, stir together pineapple, yogurt, Egg Beaters, liquid Butter Buds and vanilla. Stir in brown and white sugar until blended.
Combine dry ingredients just until moistened.
Stir in carrots and raisins. Spoon batter into lined muffin cups.
Spray with nonfat cooking spray.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 17 minutes or test with toothpick. Yields 24 muffins.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Let set 12 hours.
Will make 9 loaves (3 at a time).

title: super crisp country fried chicken
directions: Combine milk and egg in medium bowl. Set aside. Combine remaining dry ingredients in paper or plastic bag. Add chicken, a little at a time.
Shake to coat. Dip chicken in egg-milk mixture. Shake in flour a second time.
Skillet or deep fry in Crisco.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, vanilla and salt together.
Pour hot milk in and beat.
Pour in unbaked shell; sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then 325° until done.

title: low-fat oatmeal cookies
directions: In a large bowl, mix dry ingredients (flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt).
In another bowl, mix shortening, applesauce, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Add flour mixture.
Mix well. Fold in oats and raisins.
Drop from teaspoon.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mom's chicken and rice casserole
directions: In a 9 x 14-inch pan, layer with cut up chicken pieces.
Mix together remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until rice and chicken are done.

title: blackberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, salt, water and 1 cup berries in saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thick. Add rest of berries and butter.
Mix well and cool.
Just before serving, pour into baked pie shell.
Top with whipped cream.

title: apple-saucy oatmeal cookies(dietetic)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Drop by rounded tablespoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake about 20 minutes or until light golden brown.
Makes 2 dozen cookies.

title: dump cake
directions: Spoon or dump cherry pie filling evenly into bottom of 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan.
Spoon pineapple evenly over pie filling.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over pineapple.
Pour melted margarine over cake mix. Sprinkle coconut and pecans over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until browned (a dip of ice cream or Cool Whip may be served on top).

title: cafe vienna
directions: Blend in a blender until powdered.
Store in an airtight container or pretty jar.
Use 2 rounded teaspoons to 6 to 8 ounces boiling water (approximately 1 cup mix).
Pack jar of mix with a couple of pretty mugs in a basket for a welcome gift.

title: how to make a healthy milkshake
directions: To freeze bananas, choose those generously flecked with brown spots.
Peel, break about six pieces and freeze in an airtight container overnight.
Frozen bananas keep well for two or three weeks

title: sauerkraut and pork
directions: Brown onions in shortening.
Add paprika and meat.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook over low heat until meat is done.
Add kraut.
Cook until kraut is browned.
Add sour cream.

title: cream cheese squares
directions: Combine cake mix, margarine and 1 egg.
Press into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix 2 eggs, powdered sugar and cream cheese until smooth.
Pour over top of first layer.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: savory spuds
directions: Oil potatoes.
Pierce several times with fork.
Wrap in double thicknesses of foil.
Place directly on coals, turning several times, about 1 hour.

title: lentils mexican style
directions: Boil lentils in water for 30 minutes and drain off extra liquid.
Combine all ingredients.
Simmer over low heat for 30 minutes or until lentils are tender.
Serve over pasta or rice. Serves 4 to 6.

title: chili and egg casserole
directions: Layer rice, eggs, chili and cheese. Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: filipino sweet rice
directions: Wash and cook Mochi rice. When done, transfer rice into large mixing bowl. Cut up butter into hot rice and mix well. In another bowl, mix brown sugar, water and canned Eagle Brand condensed milk; mix well. Add coconut. Pour this into the rice and mix well. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until crust forms around edges.

title: reuben spread
directions: Mix together in a 9 x 13 inch pan and bake at 375 degrees for 20 minutes.
Use as a spread for party rye bread.

title: fruit dip
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve 1/4 cup juice.
Mix cream cheese, marshmallow cream, pineapple and 1/4 cup juice.
Chill and serve as a dip for fresh fruit.

title: sour cream jello
directions: Mix water and jello; add strawberries and pineapple.
Stir until strawberries are thawed.
Add bananas and nuts.
Pour 1/2 of mixture in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Place in freezer until set.
Spread sour cream on set jello and top with remaining jello.
Refrigerate until set (overnight).

title: hamburger pie
directions: Mix hamburger, ketchup and onion.
Add milk, Potato Buds and egg.
Mix well.
Pat into a pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour. Make 4 servings of mashed potatoes.
Spread over hamburger mixture. Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes more to melt cheese.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar in large bowl with mixer on medium speed until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping.
Spread on bottom of crust.
Pour 1 cup milk into bowl. Add pudding mixes.
Beat with wire whisk for 3 minutes.
(Mixture will be thick.)
Stir in pumpkin and spices with whisk until well mixed.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate 4 hours or until set.
Garnish with additional whipped topping, if desired. Store leftover pie in refrigerator.
Makes 8 servings.

title: tuna salad summer dinner
directions: Brush fish with oil.
Sprinkle with white pepper and a little ginger.
Broil 5 to 10 minutes or until flaky.
Mix together soy sauce and water to make topping.
Pour over fish or use to dip fish into it.

title: rhubarb surprise cake
directions: Bring rhubarb, sugar and water to a boil.
Remove from heat and add dry strawberry Jell-O.
Put 2 cups miniature marshmallows on bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan, greased and floured.

title: fresh raspberry pie
directions: Prepare pastry.
In mixing bowl, combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add to berries, toss gently to coat fruit.
Fill 9-inch pie plate. Dot with butter and adjust top crust.
Seal and flute edge. Cover edge with foil.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Remove foil, bake 20 to 30 minutes more.
Cool on wire rack.

title: italiano casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion, garlic salt and spices.
Drain. Combine in 1 1/2-quart casserole with soup, water and cooked noodles.
Top with cheese.
Cover and bake 20 minutes at 350°. Uncover and bake 10 more minutes.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix together hamburger, milk, onion, cracker crumbs, salt and pepper.
Form into walnut sized balls and place in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine vinegar, ketchup, brown sugar and Worcestershire sauce and pour over meatballs.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 50 balls.

title: fruit pizza
directions: You can add any additional fruit.

title: chopped beef log
directions: Add Parmesan cheese to cream cheese.
Stir in other ingredients.
Form into a log on waxed paper.
Chill overnight. Serve with crackers.

title: cinnamon-nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place raisins in 1/2 cup boiling water; cool.
Drain raisins; reserve water.
Cream the shortening, sugar and molasses.
Sift flour, salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon together.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture alternately with reserved raisin water, mixing well.
Fold in raisins and nuts. Spoon batter into 6 greased and floured soup cans.
Bake for 30 minutes or until bread tests done.

title: chicken and green bean casserole
directions: Cook rice with chicken broth that you have left after cooking chicken.
Precook green beans with seasoning.
Then combine all ingredients and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: party lady locks
directions: Cream together first 4 ingredients.
Add flour and water.
Mix thoroughly.
Chill dough 2 hours.
Sprinkle board with 1/4 cup confectioners sugar, mixed with 2 tablespoons flour.
Roll dough about 1/8-inch thick.
Cut strips 1/2 x 5-inches.
Wind part way up ungreased lady lock mold.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove and use rest of dough.

title: monkey cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray tube pan with nonstick spray. Mix cinnamon and sugar.
Set aside 1 cupful.
Quarter the biscuits and roll in cinnamon and sugar mixture and pile in cake pan.
Melt margarine and pour the cup of cinnamon with sugar mixture that was set aside into the margarine.
Add chopped nuts and bring to a rolling boil.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake 35 minutes.
Let cool in pan for 10 to 15 minutes before turning out on a cake plate.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Cook zucchini in water 5 minutes; drain.
Cool.
Cut zucchini lengthwise, scoop out seeds and part of pulp and drain.
Set aside.
Put shells in lightly oiled baking pan.

title: southern black-eyed peas
directions: Wash the peas, soak them overnight or at least 5 to 6 hours in fresh, cold water.
Drain off soaking water, put peas in a large pot containing at least 2 quarts of water.
Add onions, green pepper, celery and ham bone or bacon.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Cook about 2 hours or until peas are tender enough to mash easily.
Add water as needed while cooking.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together very well. Grease and heat skillet or pan that you use to cook the cornbread. Sprinkle the skillet or pan with a small amount of cornmeal. Pour mixture into skillet or pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: butterhorns
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine milk, shortening, sugar and salt; cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast mixture and mix well.
Add eggs, then flour; mix to smooth, soft dough.
Knead on lightly floured surface.
Place dough in greased bowl, turning once to grease surface.
Cover and let rise until double in bulk.

title: corn soup
directions: Saute onion, celery and green pepper in margarine for about 10 minutes.
Add corn and milk; simmer for about 15 minutes.
Add 1 teaspoon of dried parsley.
Serve hot.

title: heavenly chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour, chopped pecans and oleo together.
Pat with fingers into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Set aside and let cool.

title: cranberry pie
directions: Grease well a 10-inch pie plate.
Spread cranberries over bottom of plate.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar and nuts.
Set aside.
Beat eggs well.
Add 1 cup sugar gradually, mixing thoroughly.
Add flour, melted butter and shortening.
Beat well. Pour this batter over top of berries.
Bake in a slow oven at 325° for 60 minutes and crust is golden.
Cut like pie.
Serve warm or cold with generous scoops of vanilla ice cream.

title: brownie delight
directions: Mix brownie mix according to box. Mix chocolate pudding according to box. Combine cream cheese, sugar, milk and 1/2 container Cool Whip. After brownies have cooled, layer them in the bottom of a 9 x 9 pan. Layer cream cheese mixture on top of brownies. Add chocolate pudding on top of cream cheese mix. Top with remaining Cool Whip. Sprinkle with pecans (optional).

title: marjorie's bean salad
directions: Mix all together.
Marinate for several hours for best results.
I like it best if marinated overnight.

title: cheddary scalloped potatoes
directions: In skillet, heat over medium heat, the margarine and cook onion until tender.
Stir in soup, milk, salt and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Add potatoes.
Reduce heat to low.
Simmer for 5 minutes.

title: apricot congealed salad
directions: Heat crushed pineapple and juice.
When hot, remove from heat and add jello.
Let dissolve and cool.
Add buttermilk, Cool Whip and pecans.
Spread in medium casserole dish and refrigerate overnight.

title: corn relish
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil over medium heat. Reduce heat, cover and simmer 10 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruits and mix.
Let stand several hours or overnight.
Serves 8.

title: macaroons
directions: Mix all.
Drop by spoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Watch carefully.

title: corn meal mush
directions: Sprinkle meal into rapidly boiling water.
Add salt and heat, stirring over very low heat, about 1/2 hour until quite thick. Spoon into bowls, top with butter and serve hot for old-fashioned breakfast.
Serves 4.

title: cracked sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar, oleo, egg and vanilla.
Add flour, baking soda, salt and cream of tartar.
Form into balls.
Dip in granulated sugar; place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: frosty fruit punch(for 12)
directions: Bring sugar and water to a boil.
Cook for 4 minutes.
Cool and add fruit juices, ice water and ice tea.
Mix well and then chill.
Can be served with fruit filled ice cubes.

title: river rat pecan pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in bowl and mix well.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Add milk and mix well.
Stir in pecans and vanilla.
Mix well and pour in a 9-inch pie shell.
Cook in a 400° oven for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and cook an additional 35 to 40 minutes or until filling is puffed in center and is well browned.
Let cool before cutting.

title: flakey pie crust
directions: Add 1/2 shortening to flour and salt mixture with pastry blender, then add the other half.
Add water and milk mixture one tablespoon at a time with a fork.
Makes one top and bottom 9 inch crust.

title: date balls
directions: Combine oleo, dates and sugar.
Cook over low heat until sugar dissolves and dates are mushy.
Add chopped pecans, Rice Krispies and vanilla.
Roll in balls while warm, then in powdered sugar.

title: michelle's meatballs
directions: Mix ingredients.
Roll into meatballs and fry in olive oil. Cook in sauce.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix well and pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle pecans on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cream cheese salad
directions: Cream the cream cheese.
Add to Cool Whip.
Fold in pineapple and nuts.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cut flour, Crisco and salt together in bowl until it looks like cornmeal.
Add milk to eggs.
Roll out on floured board and cut into strips.
Let dry 30 minutes before placing over your boiled and deboned chicken.
Cook 20 minutes without taking off lid.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: Peel, pit and mash avocados; add lemon juice, salt and pepper and set aside.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning; set aside.

title: mud (no bake) cookies
directions: Boil sugar, milk, cocoa and butter for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter, vanilla, salt and uncooked oats. Mix well.
Drop on wax paper or well-greased cookie sheet quickly. Let cool.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease 9-inch square pan.
Beat egg in mixing bowl; add remaining ingredients and stir until blended. Pour into prepared pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 12 servings.

title: okra gumbo
directions: Combine ingredients together and cook on low, covered, until okra is ready.

title: corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Generously grease a 10-inch skillet. Heat in oven 10 minutes.
Combine cornmeal, eggs and buttermilk. Do not overmix.
Add sugar and oil.
Pour batter into heated pan. Bake 25 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream the butter or margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, milk and baking powder; mix thoroughly.
Crush vanilla wafers and add to mixture.
Mix until smooth and creamy. Stir in pecans and coconut.
Pour into 9-inch greased and floured pan and bake 30 minutes, until done.
Frost with glaze.

title: holiday punch
directions: Make paste of all ingredients.
Add water to make 4 1/2 quarts.

title: chicken rice
directions: Combine the ingredients, except Chinese noodles.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Cover top with Chinese noodles.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cinnamon salad
directions: Heat water with cinnamon candies slowly to dissolve candies. Dissolve gelatin in hot liquid.
Blend in lemon juice and raisins. Cool until slightly thickened.
Pare, core and dice apple.
Fold apple and nuts into thickened gelatin.
Chill until firm.

title: mushroom and nut spread
directions: Melt butter in large skillet over medium heat.
Add mushrooms, onion and garlic.
Saute until most of liquid has evaporated. Remove from heat.
Coarsely chop almonds and hazelnuts; remove 2 tablespoons and set aside.
Continue chopping slowly adding oil until mixture is blended.
Add with seasonings to mushroom mixture and blend thoroughly; stir in remaining 2 tablespoons nuts.
Mold into loaf and sprinkle with sesame seed.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: grandma's caramel corn
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, Karo syrup, butter, cream of tartar and salt.
Boil rapidly on medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture reaches 260°.
Remove from heat.
Stir in soda, stirring mixture thoroughly.
Immediately pour over popped corn in a large bowl, stirring until well coated.
Place coated corn in a large buttered roasting pan or sheet cake pan.
Bake caramel corn for 1 hour in preheated 200° oven, stirring 3 or 4 times.
Keep in a tightly covered container.
If it becomes sticky, place in oven again for a little while.

title: marlene's lo-cal dressing
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 1.

title: deluxe potatoes
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients and put in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Crush corn flakes and put on top; pour over 1/4 cup melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Beat egg whites with water until foamy.
Add nuts and stir well, until all are coated.
Mix spices and salt with sugar; pour over sticky nuts, stirring until all are well coated.
Spread on cookie sheet that has been sprayed with a cooking spray.
Bake 1 hour in 225° oven, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain.
Add eggs, Parmesan cheese and butter. Put in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown meat, pepper and onion. Add sauce mix.
On top of the spaghetti, spread cottage cheese. Pour sauce over that.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Add cheese; bake until melted.

title: patty's potato soup
directions: If using bouillon cubes, prepare as directed on package.
Dice potatoes and carrots; add to broth.
Add salt and pepper, if desired.
Boil 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Add chopped parsley and crushed red pepper.
Using a mixer, blend for 1 minute.
Serve with a parsley garnish.

title: chutney chicken salad
directions: Toss together chicken, apple, raisins, pineapple, celery and onion.
In small bowl, stir mayo, chutney and curry.
Add mixture to chicken and stir.
Let sit in refrigerator for 4 hours before serving.

title: french dressing
directions: Combine ingredients, toss with salad.

title: million dollar cookies
directions: Cream sugars with margarine.
Add oil and egg.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop on cookie sheet by tablespoonfuls and flatten with glass.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: hot chocolate
directions: In a saucepan, heat the heavy cream to scalding until tiny bubbles form around the edge of pan. Remove from heat and stir in chocolate pieces until they melt and mixture is smooth. Add the sugar and vanilla; stir until smooth. Pour in the milk. Return the saucepan to the stove and heat on medium until the mixture is hot and steaming. Do not bring to a boil. Top with marshmallows or whipped cream and sprinkle with cinnamon, if desired.

title: mushroom soup roast
directions: Put roast in skillet.
Brown on both sides.
The darker the better the gravy.
After browned put in oven pan.
Mix mushroom soup and 1 can milk.
Pour over the roast.
Take package of onion soup mix and pour all over roast.
Cook at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: mashed potato candy
directions: Mash potatoes (cool).
Mix potatoes, sugar and cornstarch on a light floured surface.
Roll out like a pie crust.
Spread creamy peanut butter over entire surface.
Roll up like jelly roll and put into the refrigerator for an hour.
After chilled, slice and serve.
Also you can roll in egg shape and dip in melted chocolate for Easter
(Easter eggs).

title: no bake chocolate macaroons
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and milk in saucepan and bring to a boil. Remove from heat and add cocoa, coconut, oats and vanilla.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Combine pumpkin, egg, oil and sugar.
Sift dry ingredients together and add slowly to pumpkin mixture.
Dust raisins and nuts with flour. Fold into mixture last.
Bake in large tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: tyler's french toast
directions: In shallow bowl, beat eggs, milk, sugar and cinnamon.
Dip bread in egg mixture, coating both sides.
In a skillet, cook bread on both sides in a small amount of butter, margarine or Pam over medium heat until golden brown.
Add more butter as needed. Serve with maple syrup. Makes 5 servings.

title: hot sausage and mozzarella roll
directions: Thaw dough.
Cook sausage and onion in large skillet for 10 minutes, stirring often.
Cool.

title: frittata parmesan
directions: Saute zucchini and onion in margarine in 10-inch skillet. Combine eggs, milk, salt and dash of pepper.
Stir in 1/2 cup tomatoes and Parmesan cheese.
Pour egg mixture into skillet. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until eggs are set.
Top with additional cheese, if desired.

title: chocolate popcorn
directions: Spray a large cookie sheet with nonstick spray coating; set aside.
In a large microwavable bowl, combine coating and peanut butter.
Microwave on High for 2 to 3 minutes or until chocolate is melted, stirring after every minute.

title: pepper relish
directions: Cover ground peppers with boiling water and simmer for 10 minutes.
Drain.
In a saucepan, combine ground onions, vinegar, water, salt and sugar.
Heat until spices dissolve.
In a heavy pot,
pour over peppers and heat until boiling.
Continue to boil for 15 minutes.
Put into hot canning jars and seal.
Makes about 7 pints.

title: eastern shore shrimp
directions: Combine all ingredients except shrimp and flour.
Dip each peeled and deveined shrimp in egg mixture, then in corn flour, then in egg and then in corn flour (double coating).
Drop in deep fat and fry until golden brown.
Do not overcook!!!!

title: lisa west's broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine.
Add soup, milk and cheese and simmer until mixed.
(For microwave, mix all together and heat on High for 5 minutes or mixed, stirring occasionally.) Add broccoli and rice.
Bake in casserole dish for 30 to 40 minutes at 350° (or microwave on High for 15 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes).

title: italian bisquitis
directions: Beat eggs and sugar; add oil, butter, baking powder, anise flavoring and anise seed.
Beat well.
Then add flour a little at a time and mix well.
Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour baking pan.
Pour batter evenly in pan.
Bake for 30 minutes, until top is brown.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend well.
Apples are especially good.
They taste like caramel apples.

title: bubble bread
directions: Thaw bread.
Roll in balls the size of walnuts.
Melt butter and roll balls in it.
Then dip in sugar and cinnamon mixture. Drop into Bundt pan.
Let rise to double size.
Then pour Karo syrup over top.
Bake 35 minutes at 325°.

title: marvelous mud pie
directions: Soften ice cream and spread into chocolate crust.
Place in freezer for about 1 hour.
Warm fudge sauce until pourable. Remove ice cream filled crust from freezer and put a layer of fudge sauce over entire pie.
Return pie to freezer for 15 minutes.
Top pie with whipped cream and slivered almonds.
Keep pie in freezer for at least an hour before serving.
Remove from freezer about 15 to 20 minutes before cutting.
Serves 8.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken in boiling water (save juice), remove bones and skin from chicken.
Cut chicken into small pieces.
Place chicken pieces in bottom of baking dish.
Pour broth over chicken.
Spread soup over broth.
Mix Bisquick mix, milk and margarine until smooth. Pour over top of chicken dish and bake at 350° until brown.
You may also add a small can of carrots and peas.

title: dinosaur cookies
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Divide into 4 balls and work a different color of food coloring into each.
Let children make into shapes (like they would with play dough); place each shape on a tin foil covered cookie sheet.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in a 300° oven.

title: quick fruit cobbler(dump cake)
directions: Spoon pie filling into a lightly greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Spoon pineapple on pie filling.
Sprinkle cake mix evenly over pineapple.
Drizzle butter over cake mix.
Sprinkle pecans on top.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 22 minutes.

title: cheesy corn casserole
directions: Mix together and pour into dish.
Top with cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: quick oatmeal bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water (110°).
Combine 1 1/2 cups water, oats, shortening, molasses and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add softened yeast; mix well.
Blend in eggs.
Add flour; mix thoroughly until dough is blended.
(It will be softer than kneaded dough.)
Place in a greased bowl; turn once to grease surface.
Cover.
Store in refrigerator at least 2 hours.
Shape in 2 loaves on well floured surface; place in greased 9 x 5 1/4 x 2 3/4-inch loaf pans; cover.
Let rise in warm place (80° to 85°) until double, about 2 hours.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: easy refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; let rise.
Add half the flour (3 1/2 cups) and beat for 2 minutes with electric mixer.
Add egg, shortening and remaining flour.
Beat again for 2 minutes. Cover with damp cloth and place in refrigerator.
Push down occasionally.
Two hours prior to baking, cut off the amount needed and return rest to fridge.
Shape into rolls and let rise 2 hours.
Place in greased pan and bake at 350° until brown.

title: cry babies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Measure shortening, sugar, molasses and egg into a large bowl.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Stir in flour, soda, salt, ginger and buttermilk alternately, 1/3 at a time (mix after each addition).
Batter should hold its shape but not be stiff.
If it is too soft, stir in a bit more flour.
Drop dough by teaspoonful 2 inches apart onto lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake until almost no imprint remains when touched with finger, 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from baking sheet.
Cool on wire rack.
Drizzle with Lemon Icing while warm.

title: hamburger soup
directions: In large saucepan, brown ground beef, onion and celery; drain. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover; simmer over low heat 5 to 10 minutes or until carrots are tender and soup is thoroughly heated.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Heat oven to 250°. Put peanuts in pie tin in oven while syrup is cooking.

title: easy macaroni salad
directions: In a large bowl, stir mayonnaise, vinegar, mustard, sugar, salt and pepper until smooth.
Add macaroni, celery, green peppers and onion.
Toss to coat well.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours to blend flavors.
Makes 5 cups.

title: no peek casserole
directions: Put the ingredients into a crock-pot and cook on low for 10 to 12 hours.
Serve over noodles, topped with sour cream.

title: amish cinnamon bread(making your own starter)
directions: Do not use metal spoons or bowls for mixing.

title: baked corn
directions: Beat eggs with hand beater.
Add flour, sugar and milk.
Beat. Melt butter and add to corn.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add to egg mixture.
Bake uncovered in greased glass dish at 350° for 40 minutes in pan of hot water.

title: sweet & sour meatballs
directions: In mixing bowl combine onion mix and 1/2 c. water.
Beat in eggs with fork.
Add ground beef and mix well.
Shape into 40 balls.
Combine sauerkraut, cranberry sauce, chili sauce, 3/4 c. water and brown sugar.
Pour half of this mixture into bottom of 9 X 13 glass baking dish.
Set rest aside.
In a hot skillet brown meatballs.
Arrange balls atop sauerkraut in dish.
Pour remaining sauerkraut mix over the top.
Cover with foil and bake 20 minutes at 325°.
Uncover and bake 20 minutes longer.
Serve hot over cooked rice.
10 to 12 servings.

title: carrot relish
directions: Mix and cook all ingredients 15 minutes after it begins to boil.
Then can and seal.

title: salmon au poivre with dijon butter
directions: Place salmon on greased rack of broiler pan; squeeze juice from lemon half over fish and broil 5 to 8 minutes; turn and drizzle with more lemon juice.
Continue broiling
5 to 8 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork; don't overcook.
Meanwhile in a small saucepan melt the butter and whisk the mustard in until well blended; keep warm.
When salmon is done, sprinkle evenly with crushed peppercorns and dill weed, and drizzle melted butter sauce over all.
tags: lemon juice from half of a fresh lemon

title: chocolate chip-oatmeal cookies
directions: Stir softened margarine until smooth and creamy.
Blend in sugars and vanilla; stir until smooth.
Add egg, blending in but not whipping.
Add flour, oatmeal, salt and baking soda.
Stir until well blended.
Add chocolate chips and stir.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool on a wire rack.
Makes approximately 4 dozen cookies.

title: cinco de mayo chicken salad
directions: Cut chicken in 1/4-inch cubes. Combine picante, cumin and salt in skillet. Cook about 4 minutes; stir until done. Put in covered dish and chill. Mix sour cream, mayo, avocado and celery in 6-cup container. Add chicken mixture and stir well. Spoon salad on lettuce. Sprinkle bacon on top. You may substitute pecans or sliced almonds for bacon.

title: frozen lemon cream pie
directions: Mix butter, graham crackers and 1/4 cup sugar and pat as crust in pie pan.

title: farm house barbecue muffins
directions: Separate dough. Flatten into circles; press in bottom of greased muffin cup. In a skillet, brown ground beef. In a small bowl, mix ketchup, brown sugar, vinegar and chili powder. Stir until smooth. Add to meat and mix well. Put in cups; sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes. Cool.

title: chicken or turkey croquettes
directions: Melt the butter in saucepan and add onion, stirring until wilted.
Sprinkle with flour and stir with a wire whisk as you add the chicken broth.
Stir rapidly.
Stir in chicken and add salt and pepper, nutmeg and Tabasco.
Remove from heat, add yolks return to heat.
Cook about 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Spoon in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish that has been buttered.
Cover with buttered wax paper.
Chill overnight.

title: bread pudding
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients; spread in a large baking dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix pudding with 2 1/2 to 2 3/4 cups of milk to make a thin pudding.
Drizzle over cooled bread pudding.

title: orange julius
directions: Mix orange juice concentrate with sugar, milk, water, vanilla and ice in the blender.
Blend on high for 90 seconds.
Serve at once.

title: company mashed potatoes
directions: Peel, cook and mash potatoes. Beat together with cream cheese and sour cream. Add salt and
pepper.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch buttered casserole. Sprinkle with 4 tablespoons butter, cubed. Sprinkle with paprika.
Refrigerate.
When ready to cook, bring to room temperature and bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: hush puppies - mis
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt; sift together into deep bowl.
Stir in cornmeal; add eggs one at a time and beat with wooden spoon until smooth.
Pour in 3/4 cup buttermilk and stir until absorbed.
If too dry, add more buttermilk until holds shape in a spoon.
Beat in onions and garlic.
Preheat oven on lowest setting.
Line cookie sheet with paper towels and set in middle of oven.
In a deep fryer heat oil 2 to 3 inches until reaches 375°. Shape rounded tablespoonful of batter and put into oil.
Deep fry 4 to 5 at a time, turning frequently.
Cook about 3 minutes.
Put on lined cookie sheet.

title: porky potatoes
directions: Wash pork chops and pat dry.
Place in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Salt and pepper them.
Place potato slices on top of pork chops.
In small bowl combine the melted butter and flour.
Stir and add Parmesan cheese; mix well.
Add milk and mix.
The mixture will be lumpy.
Spoon some of the lumps over the potatoes, then pour the rest of the mixture on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 20 to 30 minutes or until potatoes are brown.

title: quick peanut blossoms
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients until well blended.
Pinch off pieces of dough and roll into 1-inch balls.
Place them 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 11 minutes (or until golden brown).
Remove from cookie sheet and push kiss into center.
Cool, then enjoy!

title: baked persimmon pudding
directions: Mix these ingredients
in
the	order written.	Lightly grease (with butter) and flour a
x
13-inch
pan.
Pour in mixture and bake at 350° for 1 hour to 1 1/2 hours.

title: strawberry lite pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip and yogurt.
Put in pie crusts and top with fresh strawberries.

title: chocolate chiffon pie
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients, stirring out any lumps. Soften gelatin in the cold water and add to pudding when removed from the stove.
Cool to room temperature.
Beat egg whites and sugar until very stiff. Fold in pudding.
Pour into baked pie shell and chill in refrigerator. Garnish with whipped cream.

title: whale stew
directions: First, get a 60,000 gallon kettle and boil the whale 6 days or until tender.
Add onions, potatoes, carrots, salt and pepper. Cook until potatoes are tender.

title: roasted new potato salad
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cover potatoes with cold water; bring to a boil with 1/4 teaspoon salt and a few leek trimmings.
Cover; cook for 15 to 18 minutes, until potatoes are almost cooked. Drain.
In a metal baking pan, toss potatoes in the olive oil and roast for 30 to 40 minutes, until golden.
Clean corn; wrap in foil.
Roast in oven with potatoes.
Let corn cool; slice kernels off cob.
Toss all ingredients with Pear Vinaigrette; salt and pepper to taste.

title: french fried shrimp
directions: Combine pancake mix, salt, pepper and cold water in bowl. Beat with rotary beater for 2 minutes.
Dip shrimp in batter. Drain.
Fry in hot deep fat (375°) for 2 to 3 minutes.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Serve with cocktail sauce.
Lobster and scallops can be used in place of shrimp.
Makes 6 servings.
